<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<bible xml:lang="bko" backtTranslaltionDefaultLanguage="en" oxes="2.0">
  <book id="1CO" stage="Rev" version="C">
    <Annotation class="History">
      <Message author="JSW" created="2009-10-02 03:49:14Z" when="2009-10-02 03:49:14Z" stage="Draft">1st draft by CEG from HCE, NLT, NRSV, CEV (April-July 2005); if questions on exegesis, first consult Exegetical Summaries; advisor check in Darwin, Aug 2005 with Mus, June, Tresi &amp; Adriana; plus read-thru with Barbara's written comments; UNS checked by Mus &amp; June 16-18 Sept 2005 in Kupang; UNS suggestions evaluated by Chuck Oct 2005; BT by Chuck Oct 2005; consultant checked by Marge Crofts 13-17 Oct 2005 in Kupang; final read thru for NT by Chuck, Adriana;</Message>
      <Message author="Chuck Grimes" created="2014-02-24 10:52:34Z" when="2014-02-24 10:52:34Z" stage="Consult">Consultant Check: 13-17 October 2005 in Kupang; Consultant: Marge Crofts, approved. Report: Report KM Roman1.doc; to Chuck Helong 1 Cor-CEG.doc.</Message>
      <Message author="Chuck Grimes" created="2015-01-15 10:35:40Z" when="2015-01-15 10:35:40Z" stage="Consult">Smoothing read through for Kupang mini-Bible done at UBB with Chuck, Lena, Rina, and Oma. BackTrans cleaned up a bit too.</Message>
    </Annotation>
    <p class="Header" usfm="h">1 Korintus</p>
    <p class="Title Secondary" usfm="mt2">Paulus pung surat partama<bt>Paul's first letter</bt></p>
    <p class="Title Secondary" usfm="mt2">kasi orang parcaya di kota Korintus<bt>to the *believers in the city of Korintus</bt></p>
    <p class="Title Main" usfm="mt">1 Korintus<bt>1 Korintus</bt></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Saloom<bt>Saloom [shalom greetings]</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <c n="1" />
      <v n="1" />Ini surat dari beta, Paulus. Tuhan Allah su pili ame sang beta ko jadi Yesus Kristus pung utusan. Deng bu Sostenes ju ada titip salam kasi bosong.<bt>This letter is from me, Paulus. God has chosen me to be Yesus Kristus' *apostles/emissary (commisioned for a task). And older brother Sostenes also sends greetings to you-pl. [NOTE: Use of /bu/ indicates Sosthenes is well-known to readers.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="kleetós: Called to do a particular"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">kleetós: Called to do a particular job, through a particular event of calling theleématos: God's desire or design or plan<span class="Italic">(1) (1) </span>NRSV: Paul, called to be an apostle of Christ Jesus by the will of God, and our brother Sosthenes,</Message></Annotation><v n="2" />Beta tulis ini surat kasi bosong, andia Tuhan Allah pung orang parcaya di kota Korintus. Dia su pili ame sang bosong ko jadi Dia pung orang barisi, tagal bosong su parcaya sang Yesus Kristus. Dia ju bekin bosong jadi barisi sama ke samua orang parcaya laen dong di mana sa. Te dong ju su minta tolong sang kotong pung Bos Yesus Kristus, yang Tuhan Allah su janji memang dari dolu ko mau kirim datang. Ais Dia sama-sama jadi kotong deng dong pung Bos, yang hak parenta sang kotong samua.<bt>I am writing this letter to you-pl, that is God's believers in the city of Korintus. He has chosen you to be/become His clean/holy/pure people, because you have believed in Yesus Kristus. He also make you be/become clean/holy/pure like all other believers wherever (they are/in other places). Cuz (elaboration) they have also asked for help from our-inc Bos, Yesus Kristus, whom God promised beforehand from long ago to send here [NOTE: full long form explication here of "Christ" following TBT article.] So then He at the same time is our-inc and their Bos, who has the say-so/ordering rights over all of us-inc.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="heegiasménois: this is an act of"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">heegiasménois: this is an act of God too, by virtue of your relationship with Christ. The two should be connected kleetóis: same emphasis as in 1. Pragmatically, however, the invitation would have happened before the response to it with the concomitant setting apart for God, so the two phrases probably need to be reversed<span class="Italic">(2) (2) </span>epikalouménois tò ónoma: call on someone for help (Joel 2:32) NRSV: To the church of God that is in Corinth, to those who are sanctified in Christ Jesus, called to be saints, together with all those who in every place call on the name of our Lord Jesus Christ, both their Lord and ours:<span class="Italic">(2)</span></Message></Annotation><note reference="1:2" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Utusan dong pung Carita 18:1; Yoel 2:32</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="3" />Beta sambayang sang Tuhan Allah, kotong pung Bapa, deng Yesus Kristus, kotong pung Bos. Beta minta ko Dong kasi tunju Dong pung hati bae sang bosong, ko biar bosong bisa idop aman, dame, deng tanáng.<bt>I pray to God, our Father, and Yesus Kristus, our Bos. I ask for Them to show Their goodness/grace/kindness/generosity to you, so that you can live in peace1 (external security), peace2 (relational), and peace3 (inner) [NOTE: I've done a fairly extensive word study on /eirene/ and find no lexical or contextual support for those who want to limit it to "inner peace" here. I wonder if their blindly following a tradition of limiting it to that sense that came in along with Freud. These 3 different lexical items in Kupang nicely reflect the 3 primary senses of /eirene/ (and /shalom/)]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="eireénee: peace is more than absence"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">eireénee: peace is more than absence of war or a peaceful feeling inside; it is a total state of well-being or good spiritual health that God gives to a person. Its Scriptural antecedents are in Hebrew "shalom", everything going okay for someone NRSV: Grace to you and peace from God our Father and the Lord Jesus Christ.<span class="Italic">(3)</span></Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Paulus ucap sukur tagal orang Korintus dong<bt>Paulus give thanks because of the Korintus people</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="4" />Tiap kali beta inga sang bosong, beta ba'omong deng beta pung Tuhan bilang, &lt;&lt;Makasi bam-banya kasi sang itu orang Korintus dong pung parcaya!&gt;&gt; Te Tuhan su kasi tunju Dia pung hati bae sang bosong, tagal bosong parcaya tarús sang Yesus Kristus, yang Dia su kirim datang.<bt>Each time I remember/think of you, I speak with my God2 saying, &lt;&lt;Thank you so much for the *faith/belief of those Korintus people!&gt;&gt; Cuz (elaboration) God2 has shown His goodness/grace/kindness/generosity to you, because you continue to believe in Yesus Kristus, whom He sent [short explication] [EXEG: “thanks to my God always for you, because of the grace … in Christ Jesus.” 1) thanks for you (we have to specify ‘for what?’). In vs. 10 he goes on to list the dirty laundry, so what is he actually grateful for here? We see vs. 4 as broad intro, getting into more specifics in 5-9. So the broadest thing in 4 is “(believing) in YK” At least through the eyes of the RLs here. Fee alludes to the broad sense of their tie with Christ, and TN explicitly talks about their being united with Christ. Uma BT talks about “your connection with Christ”. We have other ways of saying that, but they don't work in this context.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="ucap sukur = fixed phrase"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z">ucap sukur = fixed phrase</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="NRSV: I give thanks to my"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">NRSV: I give thanks to my God always for you because of the grace of God that has been given you in Christ Jesus,</Message></Annotation><v n="5" />Ais Dia su kasi bosong mampu kasi jalan samua macam tugas, tagal bosong ta'ika deng Dia. Itu bekin bosong jadi kaya dalam bosong pung hati. Andia ko bosong mangarti batúl hal-hal yang pantíng so'al Dia pung jalan idop. Bosong ju tau cara apa yang paling bae ko kasi tau orang so'al Kristus.<bt>So He has made you able to carry out all kinds of work/responsibilities, because you are bound/linked with Him. That has made you be/become rich in your livers. That is why you truly understand the things that are important about/regarding His life way. You also know what is the best way/s to tell/inform people about Kristus.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="CEV undertranslated here"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z">CEV undertranslated here</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="lógooi, gnoósei: Christian speaking or preaching,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">lógooi, gnoósei: Christian speaking or preaching, the content of the message, and knowledge about spiritual realities, not just information or technical ability NRSV: for in every way you have been enriched in him, in speech and knowledge of every kind-<span class="Italic">(5)</span></Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Andia ko bosong tau hal-hal yang"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z">Andia ko bosong tau hal-hal yang pantíng so'al Dia pung jalan idop yang bosong parlú mangarti, deng cara paling bae ko kasi tau orang.</Message></Annotation><v n="6" />Itu hal dong samua kasi tunju bilang, hal-hal yang botong su kasi tau sang bosong so'al Kristus tu, su ba'akar kuat di bosong pung hati. Andia ko bosong masi yakin bilang, itu hal dong batúl.<bt>All those things show that, the things/matters which we-exc have told you-pl about Kristus, are strongly rooted in your livers. That is why you are still sure/confident that those things are true. [NOTE to daughter translations: if /ba'akar/ doesn't work as rooted, consider an equivalent of /tatanam/ "planted in the heart" which works in several languages.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="ebebaioóthee: has taken roots, is well"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">ebebaioóthee: has taken roots, is well founded, has become certain NRSV: just as the testimony of Christ has been strengthened among you<span class="Italic">(6)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="7" />Jadi bosong su tarima samua hal yang bae, yang Tuhan pung Roh bagi kasi Dia pung orang dong. Sonde kurang satu apa ju. Ais bosong batunggu-tunggu itu hari, yang nanti Tuhan buka kasi tunju kotong pung Bos Yesus Kristus, sang samua orang.<bt>So (consequently), you have received every good thing, which God2 gives/divides out to His people. (You) are not lacking/short in anything. So you keep/eagerly waiting for that day, when later God2 will reveal/unveil showing our-inc Bos, Yesus Kristus, to all people. [EXEG: Even though it is the same Gk root, most commentators feel that Gk /xarismati/ is broader here than what we translate as /karunya/ in chaps 12-14 (see Ex. Summ., including the lexical renderings). The Gk word /pneuma/ is not a part of this, so watch out for noise from the English ‘spiritual gift’ since ‘from the Spirit’ is not part of the meaning of the Gk. In the broad context the point is these gifts/blessings come from God. That is the sense that they are spiritual and not material.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="*** (2009) note added"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z">*** (2009) note added</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="apekdekhoménous: active waiting, not just killing"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">apekdekhoménous: active waiting, not just killing time NRSV: so that you are not lacking in any spiritual gift as you wait for the revealing of our Lord Jesus Christ.<span class="Italic">(7)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="8" />Kristus tu, yang mau kasi kuat sang bosong ko bosong batahan tarús sampe Dia datang kambali di ini dunya. Deng bagitu, bosong sonde jato, deng sonde ada orang yang bisa lempar sala sang bosong.<bt>That Kristus is the one who is going to strengthen you to keep on enduring until He comes back to this world. In that way, you do not fall (morally, socially, spiritually), and there is nobody who can accuse you of doing wrong. [DISCOURSE: (referent tracking): 'Lord Jesus Christ' redundant with v.7 --&gt; Pron.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="NRSV: He will also strengthen you"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">NRSV: He will also strengthen you to the end, so that you may be blameless on the day of our Lord Jesus Christ.</Message></Annotation><v n="9" />Kotong bisa parcaya sang Tuhan Allah pung Kata-kata, te apa yang Dia omong, Dia bekin jadi. Ais, su pasti Dia mau bekin ini hal dong kasi sang bosong. Te Dia yang buka jalan ko bosong bisa kanál bae-bae deng Dia pung Ana, andia kotong pung Bos Yesus Kristus.<bt>We-inc can believe/trust in God's Words, cuz (elaboration) what He says, He makes happen/brings into being. So then, surely He wants to do these things for you-pl. Cuz He is the one who opens the way for you to be able to know his Offspring well, that is our-inc Bos, Yesus Kristus.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="pistòs: faithful; could be translated by"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">pistòs: faithful; could be translated by the impersonal VP in Pidgin koinoonían: sharing, partnership, close association -- a working relation, not "fellowship" as a church word<span class="Italic">(9) (9) </span>NRSV: God is faithful; by him you were called into the fellowship of his Son, Jesus Christ our Lord.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Bosong jama'at musti jadi satu; jang tapica-pica<bt>Your-pl *congregation must be/become one/united; don't be split up/divided</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="10" />Sodara sayang dong! Dalam ini hal, beta ba'omong bawa kotong pung Bos Yesus Kristus pung nama. Jadi beta minta deng sunggu-sunggu ko bosong barenti bakanjar su. Ma usaha ko bosong idop satu hati, deng jang tapica-pica. Bosong musti pikir panjang sama-sama, ko biar bosong dapa mangarti bilang, bosong ada pegang tujuan yang sama.<bt>Dear siblings! In this matter, I am speaking bringing our-inc Bos, Yesus Kristus' name. So (consequently), I ask with all earnestness for you to stop arguing. But make an effort so you-pl live one livered (in accord, harmony, same purpose), and don't split up/become divided. You must think long together (think through, examine implications), so that you come to understand that you are holding the same goals/purpose.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="parakaloo: strongly urge dià tou onómatos:"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">parakaloo: strongly urge dià tou onómatos: using the authority, speaking on behalf of. Kind of like the luna telling the workers what the boss wants done<span class="Italic">(10) (10) </span>tooi autooi noí: the same way of thinking (people often say how military people, or bureaucrats, or policemen all think the same way) schísmata: dissensions, disunities, divisions, separate groups<span class="Italic">(10) (10) </span>kateertisménoi: put back together, used in Mark 1:19 of mending ripped nets. It often implies that something needs fixing NRSV: Now I appeal to you, brothers and sisters, by the name of our Lord Jesus Christ, that all of you be in agreement and that there be no divisions among you, but that you be united in the same mind and the same purpose.<span class="Italic">(10)</span></Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Dalam ini hal, beta ada ba'omong"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z">Dalam ini hal, beta ada ba'omong &lt;atas nama&gt; kotong pung Bos Yesus Kristus.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="11" />Te ada orang dari susi Kloe pung isi ruma yang datang lapor sang beta bilang, bosong saparu ada bakanjar tarús.<bt>Cuz (elaboration) there are people/person from older sister Kloe's household who have come and reported to me that some of you are arguing continually.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="adelphoí mou: redundant from 10 edeeloóthee:"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">adelphoí mou: redundant from 10 edeeloóthee: it is reported to me (not an accusation, but just the information, impersonal)<span class="Italic">(11) (11) </span>érides: strong arguments, quarreling (probably about who was the best leader) NRSV: For it has been reported to me by Chloe's people that there are quarrels among you, my brothers and sisters.<span class="Italic">(11)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="12" />Beta pung maksud bagini: bosong saparu ada bilang, &lt;&lt;Beta ni, Paulus pung orang!&gt;&gt; Deng ada saparu yang bilang, &lt;&lt;Beta ni, Apolos pung orang!&gt;&gt; Deng ada saparu lai yang bakastau bilang, &lt;&lt;Beta ni, iko Om Pe'u!&gt;&gt;<bt>My meaning/intention is like this (=what I mean is this): some of you are saying, &lt;&lt;I here am Paulus' person!&gt;&gt; And there are some who say, &lt;&lt;I here, am Apolos' person!&gt;&gt; And there are still others who inform (people) saying, &lt;&lt;I here, follow/obey Uncle Pete!&gt;&gt;</bt><note reference="1:12" class="Note General Paragraph" usfm="f">Alkitab bahasa Yunani tulis bilang, &lt;&lt;Kefas&gt;&gt;. Kefas tu, Petrus pung nama laen.<bt>The Yunani language Bible writes saying, &lt;&lt;Kefas&gt;&gt;. That Kefas, is Petrus' other name.</bt></note>Yang laen lai bilang, &lt;&lt;Beta ni, dengar sang Kristus sa!&gt;&gt;<bt>Still others say, &lt;&lt;I here, listen/obey only to Kristus!&gt;&gt;</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="egoò eimi Paúlou: I follow Paul,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">egoò eimi Paúlou: I follow Paul, Paul is my leader, my teacher NRSV: What I mean is that each of you says, “I belong to Paul,” or “I belong to Apollos,” or “I belong to Cephas,” or “I belong to Christ.”<span class="Italic">(12)</span></Message></Annotation><note reference="1:12" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Utusan dong pung Carita 18:24</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="13" />Bosong pung pikiran karmana? Kristus pung kelu sonde bisa tabagi-bagi. Ko, bosong ada pikir bilang, itu beta yang mati di kayu palang kasi sang bosong? Sonde, ó! Ko, waktu dong sarani sang bosong, dong pake beta pung nama ko kasi maso bosong jadi beta pung orang, ko? Sonde mungkin, to?<bt>What is your thinking/understanding? // What are you thinking!? Kristus' family cannot be split up. Or, (perhaps) you are thinking, that it was me who died on the *cross (crossed wood) for you? Not, ó! Or, when they *baptised you, they used my name to bring you in becoming my person, or (what)? No way, right?</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="meméristai: Christ's people divided up into"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">meméristai: Christ's people divided up into groups or factions or cliques eis tò ónoma Paúlou: so as to take on the name of Paul, be known as his associate, because it was his name rather than Christ's that was invoked in the baptism<span class="Italic">(13) (13) </span>NRSV: Has Christ been divided? Was Paul crucified for you? Or were you baptized in the name of Paul?</Message></Annotation><v n="14" />Beta minta tarima kasi sang Tuhan Allah, te waktu beta di sana deng bosong, beta sonde sarani orang. Cuma bu Krispus deng bu Gayus sa yang beta sarani.<bt>I give thanks to God, cuz (elaboration) when I was there (remote) with you-pl, I didn't baptize people. Only just older brother Krispus and older brother Gayus were ones that I baptised.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="NRSV: I thank God that I"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">NRSV: I thank God that I baptized none of you except Crispus and Gaius,</Message></Annotation><note reference="1:14" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Utusan dong pung Carita 18:8, 19:29, Roma 16:23</note><v n="15" />Deng bagitu, sonde ada orang yang bisa bilang, &lt;&lt;Dong sarani sang beta pake Paulus pung nama, ais beta jadi Paulus pung orang.&gt;&gt;<bt>In that way, there is nobody who can say, &lt;&lt;They baptized me using Paulus' name, so I am Paulus' person.&gt;&gt;</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="NRSV: so that no one can"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">NRSV: so that no one can say that you were baptized in my name.</Message></Annotation><v n="16" />(Ee, beta baru inga. Beta ju sarani orang saparu di Stefanus pung isi ruma. Ma beta sonde inga kalo ada orang laen lai yang beta sarani, ko sonde.)<bt>(Ee, I just remembered. I also baptised some people in Stefanus' household. But I don't remember if there are any other people that I baptised, or not.)</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="implicit communicator intent and contextual implicature"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">implicit communicator intent and contextual implicature is needed: "Oh, yeah, ..." NRSV: (I did baptize also the household of Stephanas; beyond that, I do not know whether I baptized anyone else.)<span class="Italic">(16)</span></Message></Annotation><note reference="1:16" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">1 Korintus 16:15</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="17" />Te Kristus sonde utus sang beta ko pi sarani orang. Beta pung tugas poko' tu, andia kasi tau orang so'al Dia pung Kabar Bae. Ma kalo beta ada kasi tau orang bagitu, Dia sonde suka beta omong pake bahasa tinggi ko kasi tunju beta pung pintar, ko, kasi tunju alasan yang hebat dong. Te kalo beta omong bagitu, itu kasi kurang kuasa dari carita so'al Kristus pung mati di kayu palang.<bt>Cuz (elaboration) Kristus did not commission me to go *baptise people. My main job/responsibilities are to tell people about His *Good News. But if/when I am telling people like that, He doesn't like me to talk using high/eloquent language to show my own cleverness, or, show/point out impressive reasons. Cuz (elaboration) if I talk like that, it reduces the power/authority of the story about Kristus' death on the cross. [EXEG: See Ex.Summ. for complexity and range of Gk phrase “wisdom of speech”. We bring out two main aspects, both of which seem to be intended. Cf. chapter 14 also.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="NRSV: For Christ did not send"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">NRSV: For Christ did not send me to baptize but to proclaim the gospel, and not with eloquent wisdom, so that the cross of Christ might not be emptied of its power.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Kristus tarima Dia pung kuasa dari Tuhan Allah<bt>Kristus receives His power/authority from God</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="18" />Ada orang yang pikir bilang, samua hal yang botong carita so'al Kristus pung mati di kayu palang tu, bodo talalu. Ma orang macam bagitu, nanti tapisa buang dari Tuhan. Padahal buat kotong, Kristus pung mati tu, ada kasi tunju Tuhan pung kuasa ko kasi salamat sang kotong dari kotong pung sala-sala.<bt>There are people who think that everything that we-exc tell about Kristus' death on the cross, is really stupid/dumb/ignorant. But people of that sort, will later be separated off/cut off from God2. Whereas for us-inc, Kristus' death, shows God2's power/authority to save us from our *sins/wrongs. [KM: be destroyed pairs against be saved]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="*** KT perish (frm John &amp;"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z">*** KT perish (frm John &amp; 2 Cor; see note as Jn 3:16)</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="apollyménois: in the process of being"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">apollyménois: in the process of being destroyed, on their way to be destroyed Not just "die".<span class="Italic">(18) (18) </span>logical connection NRSV: For the message about the cross is foolishness to those who are perishing, but to us who are being saved it is the power of God.<span class="Italic">(18)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="19" />Itu sama ke Tuhan pung jubir Yesaya, parná tulis bilang,<bt>That is like what God2's spokesperson, named Yesaya, once wrote saying,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">&lt;&lt;Tuhan Allah bilang,<bt>&lt;&lt;God says,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">&lt;Samua hal yang orang yang pintar dong mangarti,<bt>&lt;Everything that clever/knowledgeable people understand,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Beta nanti bongkar buang samua,<bt>I will dismantle/demolish/expose it all,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 3" usfm="q3">ko jadi hal yang sonde ada pung arti.<bt>so that it becomes something that has no meaning.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Dong pung pintar karmana macam ju,<bt>And whatever kinds of cleverness they have,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Beta nanti angka buang samua,<bt>I will throw it all away,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 3" usfm="q3">ko jadi hal yang sonde ada pung guna.&gt;&gt;&gt;<bt>so it becomes something which is useless.&gt;&gt;&gt;</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="gégraptai: can a book &quot;say&quot; something?"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">gégraptai: can a book "say" something? or only a person? If so, it was Isaiah. "Befo time" is necessary to distinguish the Bible in use in Paul's time from the Bible as we know it NRSV: For it is written, “I will destroy the wisdom of the wise, and the discernment of the discerning I will thwart.”<span class="Italic">(19)</span></Message></Annotation><note reference="1:19" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Yesaya 29:14</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="20" />Dolu Tuhan memang ada omong bagitu. Ais sakarang, su jadi karmana? Orang yang pintar dong, jadi karmana? Guru agama dong, jadi karmana? Deng orang yang jago baparkara dong, jadi karmana? Coba dengar, é! Tuhan su bekin sang dong sama ke orang bodo! Dia su cabu buang samua akal yang ba'akar di ini dunya, deng bekin ke sonde ada pung arti apa-apa.<bt>Formerly God2 really did say that. So now, what has happened? What has become of those wise/clever/knowledgeable people? What has become of those teachers of religion? What has become of those champion litigators/disputers/debaters? Listen up, é! God2 has made them (become) like stupid/dumb/ignorant people! He has pulled out (unplugged) all ideas/schemes which are rooted in this world, and made them as if they have no meaning whatsoever.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="ofek ~ ofe = mess up"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z">ofek ~ ofe = mess up (s.t. on desk)</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="emoóranen: an abstract thing like wisdom"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">emoóranen: an abstract thing like wisdom can't be stupid; it takes a person to qualify for that. So we need two sentences, one for the people, another to show that what the people think they know comes merely from this world. The aorist probably refers to a single event, Christ's death, that has already happened Can an idea or an abstraction be called "stupid," or only a person? Check basilect.<span class="Italic">(20) (20) </span>NRSV: Where is the one who is wise? Where is the scribe? Where is the debater of this age? Has not God made foolish the wisdom of the world?</Message></Annotation><note reference="1:20" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Ayub 12:17, Yesaya 19:12, 33:18, 44:25</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="21-22" />Tuhan Allah pung pintar tu, hebat talalu. Te biar manusia anggap diri pintar, dong pung akal sandiri sonde cukup ko dong bisa kanál batúl sang Tuhan. Biar bagitu, ma Tuhan su pake Dia pung pintar ko buka jalan kasi manusia. Te dolu Dia su pikir bilang, &lt;&lt;Biar manusia sangka Beta pung utusan dong orang bodo sa, ma karmana-karmana ju, Beta musti utus orang ko pi kasi tau sang dong hal yang batúl so'al Beta.&gt;&gt; Te Tuhan su putus mau pake pasán yang Dia pung utusan dong bawa, ko orang bisa parcaya sang Dia. Dia mau pake itu jalan ko kasi salamat orang dari dong pung sala-sala.<bt>[Adapted from HCE] God's cleverness is really incredible. Cuz (elaboration) even though humans consider themselves clever, their own ideas/schemes are not enough/sufficient for them to be able to truly know God2. Even though that is the case, nevertheless God2 has used His cleverness to open the way for humans. Cuz (elaboration) formerly He had thought that, &lt;&lt;Even though humans assume/consider My emissaries to just be stupid people, nevertheless, regardless, I must commission/send with purpose people to go tell them things that are true about Me.&gt;&gt; Cuz (elaboration) God2 has decided to use the message/instructions which His emissaries were carrying, so people could believe in Him. He wanted to use that way/means to save people from their wrongs.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="&lt;&lt;Ada lebe bae Beta utus orang"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z">&lt;&lt;Ada lebe bae Beta utus orang ko kasi tau manusia hal yang batúl so'al Beta, biar dong sangka Beta pung utusan dong orang bodo sa.&gt;&gt; Tuhan Allah tu, pintar talalu. Te Dia sonde kasi biar orang di ini dunya cari jalan sandiri ko dong bisa kanál batúl sang Dia. Tagal manusia pung akal sandiri dong sonde cukup. Ma kalo Tuhan, Dia pikir bagini: &lt;&lt;Biar manusia sangka Beta pung utusan dong orang bodo sa, ma karmana-karmana ju, Beta musti utus orang ko pi kasi tau sang dong hal yang batúl so'al Beta.&gt;&gt; Te Tuhan su putus mau pake pasán yang Dia pung utusan dong bawa tu, ko orang saparu parcaya sang Dia. Dia mau pake itu jalan ko kasi salamat orang dari dong pung sala-sala.<span class="Italic">(21)</span></Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="biar lai = walauPUN ; karmana-karmana"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z">biar lai = walauPUN ; karmana-karmana</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="NRSV: For since, in the wisdom"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">NRSV: For since, in the wisdom of God, the world did not know God through wisdom, God decided, through the foolishness of our proclamation, to save those who believe.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Ma manusia anggap Tuhan pung jalan tu, bodo. Andia ko dong sonde mau toe deng Dia pung utusan. Te orang Yahudi dong cuma mau minta tanda-tanda heran sa, ko dong bisa lia Tuhan pung kuasa. Deng orang Yunani dong cuma mau dengar hal-hal pintar yang maso akal sa, iko dong pung pikiran sandiri.<bt>But humans viewed that way of God2's as stupid. That is why they didn't want to pay any attention to His emissaries. Cuz (elaboration) the Yahudi people only just wanted to ask for various *miracles/amazing signs, so they could see God2's power. And the Yunani people only want to hear clever things that make sense, according to their own thinking. [EXEG: playing on particular cultural stereotype associated with the Greeks here, so not taken as 'gentiles'; Note: NLT connects this verse nicely with context as above.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="seemeia: miracle, amazing thing that shows"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">seemeia: miracle, amazing thing that shows that God is at work reason why Jews and Greeks want particular demonstrations, as in John 5 and many other passages<span class="Italic">(21) (21) </span>NRSV: For Jews demand signs and Greeks desire wisdom,</Message></Annotation><v n="23" />Biar bagitu, ma botong yang jadi Tuhan pung utusan dong, cuma pi jalan kasi tau orang bilang, &lt;&lt;Tuhan su kirim Kristus, itu Orang yang Dia su janji memang dari dolu ko mau kirim datang. Ais orang laen dong paku bekin mati sang Dia di kayu palang.&gt;&gt; Waktu orang Yahudi dong dengar itu carita, dong mau tola buang sa, te iko dong pung pikiran, Orang yang Tuhan mau kirim datang tu, sonde bisa mati bagitu. Waktu orang Yunani dong dengar itu carita, dong pikir, &lt;&lt;Carita paling bodo, é!&gt;&gt;<bt>Even that being the case, nevertheless we-exc who are God2's apostles/emissaries, only go around telling people that, &lt;&lt;God2 sent Kristus, the Person whom He promised beforehand from long ago to send. So/Then other people nailed Him to death on a/the cross.&gt;&gt; When Yahudi people hear that story, they just want to reject it (out of hand), cuz (elaboration) according to their thinking, that Person whom God2 is going to send, could not die. When the Yunani people hear that story, they think, &lt;&lt;What a stupid story, é!&gt;&gt; [EXEG: Follows HCE. See also Ex. Summ. “It hindered the Jews from believing since the claim that Jesus was the Christ was refuted by the crucifixion [Vn]”; The cross was an offense to Jews because they felt that God’s highest blessing rested on the Messiah, but God’s curse rested on anyone hanging on a cross. ES. This translation sounds like the Jews thought the Messiah was immortal. Suggestion: “could not die in that manner”. Fixed Amarasi check, Feb 2014.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="heeméis dè: we apostles, not you"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">heeméis dè: we apostles, not you or people in general reason why the Jews can't relate to the message<span class="Italic">(23) (23) </span>NRSV: but we proclaim Christ crucified, a stumbling block to Jews and foolishness to Gentiles,</Message></Annotation><v n="24" />Ma ada orang yang Tuhan Allah su pili memang ko jadi Dia pung milik. Dong saparu dari orang Yahudi, deng saparu dari orang bukan Yahudi. Iko dong tu, Kristus pung mati su kasi tunju sang dong bilang, Tuhan pung kuasa bésar talalu, deng Dia pung pintar tu, hebat talalu.<bt>But there are people who God has chosen beforehand to be/become His possession. Some of them are from the Yahudi people, and some are from non Yahudi people. According to those ones, Kristus' death has already shown/revealed to them that God2's power/authority is really great, and His cleverness is really incredible. [EXEG: Fee, TN, CR, context of vs.23.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="NRSV: but to those who are"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">NRSV: but to those who are the called, both Jews and Greeks, Christ the power of God and the wisdom of God.</Message></Annotation><v n="25" />Biar manusia dong anggap Tuhan pung jalan bodo, ma Dia masi lebe pintar dari dong. Deng biar dong sangka Tuhan sonde ada pung kuasa apa-apa, ma Dia pung kuasa masi lebe bésar dari dong.<bt>Even though humans view/consider that way of God2's to be stupid, nevertheless, He is still more clever/wise than they. And even though they assume/God2 has no power/authority whatever, nevertheless His power/authority is still greater than theirs.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Chiastic relative to the preceding verses,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">Chiastic relative to the preceding verses, so might want to reorder the two clauses. Power ... wisdom : wisdom ... power in this verse. [No need.] NRSV: For God's foolishness is wiser than human wisdom, and God's weakness is stronger than human strength.<span class="Italic">(25)</span></Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="26" />Sodara sayang dong! Ko bosong bisa mangarti beta pung omong ni, inga bosong pung dudu-badiri waktu Tuhan pili ame sang bosong ko jadi Dia pung milik. Iko manusia pung nilei, di bosong pung teng-tenga sonde ada banya orang yang pintar, sonde banya orang yang ada pung pangaru, deng sonde banya orang dari kelu yang ada pung nama bésar.<bt>Dear siblings! So that you-pl can understand what I am saying here, remember your situation (doublet idiom: sitting-standing) when God2 chose you to become His possession. According to human assessment/evaluation/judgement, in your midst there are not many people who are clever, there are not many people of influence, and there are not many people from families who have important names.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="pangaru = yang ada pegang kuasa"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z">pangaru = yang ada pegang kuasa di ini dunya</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="NRSV: Consider your own call, brothers"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">NRSV: Consider your own call, brothers and sisters: not many of you were wise by human standards, not many were powerful, not many were of noble birth.</Message></Annotation><v n="27" />Ma Tuhan pili mau pake orang yang manusia anggap paling bodo, ko bekin malu orang yang anggap diri pintar. Deng Dia ju pili mau pake orang yang manusia anggap sonde ada pung kuasa apa-apa, ko bekin malu orang yang anggap diri ada pung kuasa.<bt>But God2 chooses to use people whom humans view/consider to be the most stupid/ignorant, to shame people who consider themselves to be clever/smart. And He also chooses to use people whom humans view/consider to have no power/authority whatever, to shame people who consider themselves to have power/authority.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="NRSV: But God chose what is"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">NRSV: But God chose what is foolish in the world to shame the wise; God chose what is weak in the world to shame the strong;</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="ko buka talanjang manusia pintar pung"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z">ko buka talanjang manusia pintar pung bodo ; Ma Tuhan pili mau pake orang yang manusia anggap paling bodo, ko bongkar buang hal yang manusia anggap pintar, deng bekin malu sang dong. Deng Dia ju pili mau pake orang yang manusia anggap sonde ada pung kuasa apa-apa ko kasi ancor buang hal yang manusia anggap ada pung kuasa, deng bekin malu sang dong.</Message></Annotation><v n="28" />Ais Dia pili ame orang kici yang sonde ada pung nama deng yang manusia suka anggap reme sang dong. Te Tuhan mau pake sang dong ko bekin orang yang anggap diri hebat, jadi sama ke dong sonde ada pung arti apa-apa lai.<bt>So then He chooses small/insignificant people who have no name/reputation and who humans like to look down on/belittle them. Cuz (elaboration) God2 wants to use them to make people who consider themselves impressive/great/incredible, to become like they have no more significance/meaning. [NOTE: reordered for KM worldview]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="NRSV: God chose what is low"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">NRSV: God chose what is low and despised in the world, things that are not, to reduce to nothing things that are,</Message></Annotation><v n="29" />Ko nanti, kalo orang mangada sang Tuhan Allah, sonde ada satu orang ju yang bisa puku dada bilang, dia tu, hebat.<bt>So that later, when people face God, there will not be even one person who can beat his chest saying that he is great.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="puku dada = note spelling of"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z">puku dada = note spelling of this lexeme</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="NRSV: so that no one might"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">NRSV: so that no one might boast in the presence of God.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="30" />Te Tuhan Allah sandiri sa yang buka jalan ko bosong bisa maso jadi Yesus Kristus pung orang. Tuhan yang bekin Yesus jadi Orang yang kasi Dia pung pintar sang kotong. Yesus tu, yang buka jalan ko kotong bisa badame deng Tuhan Allah. Yesus tu, yang bekin kotong bisa idop lurus deng barisi. Deng Dia yang kasi lapás sang kotong dari sala pung kuasa.<bt>Cuz (elaboration) God himself is the one who opened the way so you-pl could enter becoming Yesus Kristus' people. God2 is the one who Made Yesus be the Person who gives His cleverness/wisdom to us-inc. That Yesus, is the one who opened the way so we-inc could be have a right relationship (make peace after relationship is damaged) with God. That Yesus, is the one who makes us able to live straight (righteous) and clean/holy/pure. And He is the one who has freed/rescued us-inc from the power of sin.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="apolýtroosis: setting us free (a little"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">apolýtroosis: setting us free (a little different from sooteería - gets us out from under the influence of sin, rather than absolving us of guilt), also used of political liberation Treat as a key term: apolytroosis with this rendering<span class="Italic">(30) (30) </span>NRSV: He is the source of your life in Christ Jesus, who became for us wisdom from God, and righteousness and sanctification and redemption,</Message></Annotation><v n="31" />Itu sama ke yang su tatulis di Tuhan pung Tulisan Barisi bilang,<bt>That is like what has been written in God2's Holy Writings saying,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">&lt;&lt;Sapa yang suka angka puji,<bt>&lt;&lt;Whoever likes to lift praise,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">lebe bae dong angka puji sang apa yang kotong pung Bos bekin.<bt>it would be better if they lift praise for what our Bos has done.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Jang angka-angka dong pung diri sandiri!&gt;&gt;<bt>Don't/They shouldn't elevate/boast/praise themselves!&gt;&gt;</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="kauchásthoo: show happiness openly with words."><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">kauchásthoo: show happiness openly with words. In this verse it is positive, and does not imply putting anybody else down NRSV: in order that, as it is written, “Let the one who boasts, boast in the Lord.”<span class="Italic">(31)</span></Message></Annotation><note reference="1:31" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Yeremia 9:24</note></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Kotong musti kasi tau taráng-taráng sang samua orang, so'al Tuhan Yesus pung mati di kayu palang<bt>We-inc must tell everybody clearly/openly about the Lord Yesus' death on the cross [CR, Amarasi 2014]</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <c n="2" />
      <v n="1" />Sodara sayang dong! Dolu waktu beta datang di bosong, beta buka kasi tau sang bosong Tuhan pung rahasia yang dolu manusia sonde mangarti. Ma beta sonde bawa itu kata-kata ko omong sombong. Deng beta ju sonde pake bahasa yang tinggi-tinggi ko kasi tunju beta pung pintar sandiri.<bt>Dear siblings! Previously when I came to you-pl, I opened/revealed/explaining to you God2's *secret/s [NOTE: this word can be somethng that was not known or understood in the past but can be revealed or known at a later time, as in Colossians], which humans formerly did not understand. But I didn't bring those words to speak arrogantly. And I also didn't use high language to show (off) my own cleverness.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="hyperocheèn: superiority in the way I"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">hyperocheèn: superiority in the way I delivered the message NRSV: When I came to you, brothers and sisters, I did not come proclaiming the mystery of God to you in lofty words or wisdom.<span class="Italic">(1)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="2" />Waktu beta ada sama-sama deng bosong, beta pung pikir bagini: beta cuma mau kasi tunju satu hal sa, andia Yesus Kristus. Dia tu, Orang yang Tuhan Allah su janji memang dari dolu ko mau kirim datang. Ma waktu Yesus datang, orang dong paku bekin mati sang Dia di kayu palang. Te cuma itu hal sa yang beta tau deng batúl.<bt>When I was together with you, My thinking was like this: I only wanted to show/make known just one thing, that is Yesus Kristus. He is the Person whom God has promised beforehand from long ago to send. But when Yesus came, people nailed Him to death on the cross. Cuz (reinforcement) only just that thing, is what I know for sure/fully.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="NRSV: For I decided to know"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">NRSV: For I decided to know nothing among you except Jesus Christ, and him crucified.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="3" />Tempo hari, waktu beta ada sama-sama deng bosong, beta rasa kurang mampu, deng beta ju taku deng gamatar.<bt>At that (past) time, when I was together with you, I felt less than fully able, and I was also fearful and shaking/trembling (from cold, sickness, fear, or anxiety).</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="NRSV: And I came to you"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">NRSV: And I came to you in weakness and in fear and in much trembling.</Message></Annotation><note reference="2:3" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Utusan dong pung Carita 18:9</note><v n="4" />Beta pung cara omong deng beta pung pasán, sederhana sa. Te beta sonde coba pake kata-kata yang lebe-lebe ko kokoe sang bosong. Sonde! Ma waktu beta ada omong, su jalás bilang, Tuhan pung Roh Barisi ada ator sang beta, deng Dia pung kuasa ada di beta.<bt>My way of speaking, and that message of mine, were just simple. Cuz (elaboration) I didn't try to use words which were excessive/over the top/fancier than necessary, to persuade/cajole you. No! But when I was speaking, it was clear than God2's *Holy Spirit was overseeing/regulating/controlling me, and His power/authority was in/at me (=I had it).</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="sederhana = biasa-biasa, sonde lebe-lebe? ;"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z">sederhana = biasa-biasa, sonde lebe-lebe? ; kokoe = some mesolectal speakers not know</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="NRSV: My speech and my proclamation"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">NRSV: My speech and my proclamation were not with plausible words of wisdom, but with a demonstration of the Spirit and of power,</Message></Annotation><v n="5" />Te beta pikir, sonde bae kalo bosong parcaya sang Tuhan Allah, tagal bosong dengar manusia pung kata-kata yang pintar sa. Ada lebe bae bosong parcaya sang Tuhan, tagal Dia ada kasi tunju Dia pung kuasa sang bosong.<bt>Cuz (elaboration) I thought, it's not good if you believe in God, just because you heard human's clever words. It would be better if you believe in God2, because He is showing/demonstrating His power/authority to you.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="NRSV: so that your faith might"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">NRSV: so that your faith might rest not on human wisdom but on the power of God.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Tuhan Allah ajar sang kotong so'al hal-hal pintar yang batúl<bt>God teaches us-inc about things/matters that are truly clever</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="6" />Padahal waktu botong ba'omong deng orang yang pung parcaya su dewasa, botong ajar pake kata-kata yang maso akal. Ma bukan yang maso akal iko manusia di ini dunya pung pikir, ko, iko apa yang orang pegang parenta dong suka ajar sakarang. Te dong tu, nanti ilang buang.<bt>Besides, whereas, however, when we were speaking with people whose belief was already mature/adult/fully developed, we taught using words that make sense (idiom: enter the brain). But not (ones) that make sense according to human's in this world's thinking, or, according to people who are in positions of authority/government like to teach nowadays. Cuz (elaboration) those will later disappear/vanish. [NOTE to daughter translations: CHECK referent of "those" in last sentence; people?/teachings?]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="mantap = BI ; dewasa ="><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z">mantap = BI ; dewasa = adult, mature</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="teleíois: spiritually mature, trust firmly in"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">teleíois: spiritually mature, trust firmly in Christ, products of Christian growth aióonos: the present age, the way things are in this period of time<span class="Italic">(6) (6) </span>katargouménoon: the rulers are on the way out, being brought to nothing, disappearing, passing from the scene NRSV: Yet among the mature we do speak wisdom, though it is not a wisdom of this age or of the rulers of this age, who are doomed to perish.<span class="Italic">(6)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="7" />Ma botong cuma ajar hal-hal pintar yang turun datang dari Tuhan Allah. Te dolu-kala waktu dunya balóm jadi, Tuhan sambunyi itu hal dong. Ma sakarang Dia su putus ko mau buka itu rahasia kasi kotong, ko biar kotong ju dapa bagian dalam Dia pung nama yang hebat.<bt>But we only taught clever things which were handed down from God. Cuz (elaboration) long ago, before the world came into being, God2 had hidden those things. But now He has decided to reveal those secrets to us-inc, so that we-inc can also take part/have a share in His great/incredible name/reputation. [EXEG: Gk: glory here] [EXEG: CR, Ex.Summ. Tagbanwa BT; Gk. “before the ages” fixed CR, Amarasi 2014.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="proóorisen: decide ahead of time doxa:"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">proóorisen: decide ahead of time doxa: tie 'glory' into context<span class="Italic">(7) (7) </span>NRSV: But we speak God's wisdom, secret and hidden, which God decreed before the ages for our glory</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="ko kotong bisa jadi hebat. //"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z">ko kotong bisa jadi hebat. //</Message><Message author="Chuck Grimes" created="2010-10-29 06:18:49Z">,</Message></Annotation><v n="8" />Ma orang yang sakarang ada pegang parenta, dong sonde mangarti Tuhan pung pintar yang batúl. Te kalo dong mangarti, sonde mungkin dong paku bekin mati kotong pung Bos yang hebat tu di kayu palang.<bt>But people who are now in authority/governing/ruling, they don't really understand God2's true cleverness. Cuz (elaboration) if they understood, they would surely not have nailed to death that incredible Bos of ours on the cross. [EXEG: Gk: lord of glory here]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="NRSV: None of the rulers of"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">NRSV: None of the rulers of this age understood this; for if they had, they would not have crucified the Lord of glory.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="9" />Di Tulisan Barisi ada tatulis so'al Tuhan pung rahasia yang dolu tasambunyi bilang,<bt>In the *Scriptures (Holy Writings) it is written about God2's secrets which used to be hidden saying,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">&lt;&lt;Ada hal yang manusia pung mata balóm parná lia,<bt>&lt;&lt;There are things that human eyes have never seen,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">deng ada hal yang manusia pung talinga balóm parná dengar,<bt>and there are matters that human ears have never heard,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">yang manusia sonde bisa pikir ame.<bt>which humans cannot (possibly) comprehend (SVC=think about thoroughly/successfully).</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Padahal Tuhan su sadia memang itu hal samua,<bt>However, God2 has prepared beforehand all those things,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">kasi orang yang sayang sang Dia.&gt;&gt;<bt>for people who love Him.&gt;&gt;</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="CEV missed the thrust and focus"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z">CEV missed the thrust and focus of the quote from the context of "mystery"</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="NRSV: But, as it is written,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">NRSV: But, as it is written, “What no eye has seen, nor ear heard, nor the human heart conceived, what God has prepared for those who love him”</Message></Annotation><note reference="2:9" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Yesaya 64:4</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="10" />Memang dolu orang sonde mangarti itu hal dong, ma sakarang Tuhan Allah su pake Dia pung Roh ko kasi tabuka itu hal kasi sang kotong.<bt>It is true that formerly people did not understand those things, but now God has used His Spirit to unveil/reveal those things to us-inc.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Ma Tuhan Allah pung rahasia yang"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z">Ma Tuhan Allah pung rahasia yang tatutu dari dolu tu, Dia su pake Dia pung Roh ko kasi tabuka sang kotong.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Naa, Tuhan pung Roh tu, mangarti samua hal. Te Dia ju pareksa sampe alus-alus Tuhan pung dalam hati.<bt>Naa, that Spirit of God understands all things. Cuz (elaboration) He also examines/investigates to the finest detail God2's innermost being (his inside liver/conscience).</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="pareksa in the sense of teliti"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z">pareksa in the sense of teliti</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="eraunáai ... báthee: like searching out"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">eraunáai ... báthee: like searching out something that is at the bottom of the ocean under deep water NRSV: these things God has revealed to us through the Spirit; for the Spirit searches everything, even the depths of God.<span class="Italic">(10)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="11" />Kotong satu-satu ada pung roh sandiri dalam kotong pung hati. Andia ko kotong manusia pikir deng bekin hal yang beda-beda. Deng sonde ada orang laen yang tau parsís kotong pung dalam hati, cuma kotong pung roh sandiri sa. Bagitu ju deng Tuhan Allah. Sonde ada satu orang ju yang tau Tuhan pung dalam hati. Cuma Dia pung Roh sandiri yang tau batúl.<bt>Each of us-inc have our own spirits in our livers. That is why we humans think and do different things (individuated). And there is no other person who knows precisely our-inc innermost being, only our own spirits. It is the same way with God. There is not one single person who knows God2's innermost being. Only His own Spirit truly/fully knows. [NOTE to daughter translations: Consider collocations and naturalness between /cuma kotong pung roh sandiri sa/ vs. /cuma kotong sandiri sa/. The latter is more natural, the former maintains the higher level parallel with last sentence. Don't force the parallel if it doesn't work.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Check basilect. pnéuma: the part of"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">Check basilect. pnéuma: the part of our own personality with which we relate to God. Not an independent spirit like an obake spirit or a mo`o spirit or a dog spirit, and not a dead person's ghost<span class="Italic">(11) (11) </span>NRSV: For what human being knows what is truly human except the human spirit that is within? So also no one comprehends what is truly God's except the Spirit of God.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="12" />Naa, kotong su tarima ame Tuhan pung Roh, deng Dia yang ator sang kotong. Andia ko kotong sonde iko orang di ini dunya pung pikiran. Tagal Tuhan pung Roh ada dalam kotong pung hati, andia ko kotong bisa kanál samua hal bae yang Dia su bekin kasi kotong.<bt>Naa, we have received God2's Spirit, and He is the one who oversees/regulates/controls us. That is why we do not follow/do according to the thinking of people in this world. Bcause God2's Spirit is in our livers, that is why we can know/recognise all good things which He has done for us.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="pola pikiran = BI"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z">pola pikiran = BI</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="pnéuma: here, could be just the"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">pnéuma: here, could be just the thinking and understanding process of humans generally, human wisdom, the mana`o that originates here in this world eidóomen: know by experience, participate in<span class="Italic">(12) (12) </span>charisthénta: not "spiritual gifts" in the narrow sense of Galatians and Ephesians, but everything God has ever done for us zooee: SK likes "da real kine life dat stay foeva".<span class="Italic">(12) (12) </span>NRSV: Now we have received not the spirit of the world, but the Spirit that is from God, so that we may understand the gifts bestowed on us by God.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="13" />Itu hal dong yang kotong biasa ada ba'omong. Te botong kasi tau hal-hal yang Tuhan pung Roh ada ajar sang botong. Ais botong sonde ajar pake kata-kata yang maso akal iko manusia pung pikiran. Ma botong ajar pake kata-kata dari Tuhan pung Roh, kasi orang yang kanál sang Dia.<bt>It is those things that we-inc often/normally talk about. Cuz (elaboration) we-exc tell/explain the things that God2's Spirit is teaching/has taught us-exc. So then we do not teach using words that make sense according to human's thinking. But we teach using words from God2's Spirit, to/for people who know Him.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Ex given by UNS: &quot;ex. of"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z">Ex given by UNS: "ex. of words that make sense, telling people 'if you don't eat, you'll go hungry'; ex. of words from the Spirit that not everyone might understand, 'if you want to live as God's people, you have to follow His will.'"</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="NRSV: And we speak of these"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">NRSV: And we speak of these things in words not taught by human wisdom but taught by the Spirit, interpreting spiritual things to those who are spiritual.</Message></Annotation><v n="14" />Ma kalo ada orang yang sonde kanál sang Tuhan pung Roh, ais dia dengar botong pung omong, dia sonde mau tarima bae. Te dia pikir bilang, &lt;&lt;Apa tu? Sonde maso di akal!&gt;&gt; Padahal, biar karmana ju, itu orang sonde bisa mangarti itu hal dong, te dia sonde idop ta'ika deng Tuhan pung Roh na.<bt>But if there is a person who does not know God2's Spirit, and then he hears what we are saying, he is not going to receive that well/go along with it. Cuz (elaboration) he is thinking, &lt;&lt;What's that? It doesn't make any sense!&gt;&gt; When in fact (background explanation), no matter what, that person cannot understand those things, cuz (reason/elaboration) he does not live bound/linked to God2's Spirit [+obvious].</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="psychikòs ánthroopos: any naturally, worldly oriented"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">psychikòs ánthroopos: any naturally, worldly oriented person; generic, not a particular individual mouria: foolishness, nonsense, not understandable<span class="Italic">(14) (14) </span>NRSV: Those who are unspiritual do not receive the gifts of God's Spirit, for they are foolishness to them, and they are unable to understand them because they are spiritually discerned.</Message></Annotation><v n="15" />Orang yang idop ta'ika deng Tuhan pung Roh, baru bisa mangarti itu hal dong samua, deng bisa tau mana yang batúl dong. Ma orang laen dong ukur tar ontong sang itu orang.<bt>People who live bound/linked to God2's Spirit, only then can they understand all those things, and know which (of options) are true/right. But other people cannot successfully measure/evaluate that person.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="ukur tar ontong = sonde bisa"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z">ukur tar ontong = sonde bisa ukur (unsuccessful)</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="NRSV: Those who are spiritual discern"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">NRSV: Those who are spiritual discern all things, and they are themselves subject to no one else's scrutiny</Message></Annotation><v n="16" />Mana bisa? Te ada tulis dalam Tulisan Barisi bilang:<bt>How could they? Cuz (elaboration) it is written in the Scriptures, saying:</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">&lt;&lt;Sapa yang bisa mangarti Tuhan Allah pung pikiran?<bt>&lt;&lt;Who is it that is able to understand God's thinking?</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="pikir to resonate with last sentence?"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z">pikir to resonate with last sentence? or change last sentence to reflect dalam hati?</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Ko, sapa yang bisa ator sang Tuhan,<bt>Or, who is it that can oversee/regulate/control God2,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 3" usfm="q3">ko Dia bekin iko itu orang pung nasiat?<bt>so that He does according to that person's advice?</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Sonde ada satu orang ju!&gt;&gt;<bt>There is not even one person!&gt;&gt;</bt><note reference="2:16" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Yesaya 40:13</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Padahal kotong bisa mangarti itu hal dong, tagal Kristus ada tolong ko kotong bisa pikir iko Dia pung pikiran.<bt>However, we-inc can understand those things, because Kristus is helping us so we can think according to His thinking.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="NRSV: “For who has known the"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">NRSV: “For who has known the mind of the Lord so as to instruct him?” But we have the mind of Christ.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Kotong orang parcaya musti karjá satu hati kasi sang Tuhan, deng jang bakanjar kiri-kanan<bt>We-inc believers must work one livered (in harmony, same purpose) for God2, and not be arguing/disputing left-right</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <c n="3" />
      <v n="1" />Sodara sayang dong! Tempo hari waktu beta di sana, bosong sama ke orang yang balóm ta'ika bae-bae deng Tuhan pung Roh. Tagal bosong cuma tau iko bosong pung mau-mau sandiri sa, sama ke manusia biasa. Andia ko beta sonde bisa ba'omong deng bosong, sama ke deng orang dewasa, te bosong ke ana kici sa.<bt>Dear siblings! That (past) time when I was there (remote), you-pl were like people who were not yet bound/linked well/fully with God2's Spirit. Because you only knew how to follow your own desires/passions, as a normal human (not nobility, or no characteristics or power standing out above the rest). That is why I could not speak with you-pl, as with adults/mature/fully developed, cuz (elaboration) you were just like little children.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="beta malas tau = I don't"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z">beta malas tau = I don't care</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="sarkinos: natural, worldly, human Regularize &quot;worldly&quot;."><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">sarkinos: natural, worldly, human Regularize "worldly". Check 1 John 2:16.<span class="Italic">(1) (1) </span>NRSV: And so, brothers and sisters, I could not speak to you as spiritual people, but rather as people of the flesh, as infants in Christ.</Message></Annotation><v n="2" />Beta musti ajar bosong so'al hal ringan sa, te bosong balóm siap tarima hal yang barát, sama ke ana kici yang balóm bisa makan daging. Padahal bosong musti jadi kuat, sama ke orang bésar yang biasa makan daging. Ma sakarang bosong masi sama ke ana mea yang cuma tau minum susu sa.<bt>I had to teach you about lightweight/simple/ insignificant things only, cuz (elaboration) you were not yet ready to receive heavy/complex/significant things, just like small children who are not yet ready to eat meat. Whereas in fact, you should have been strong, like an adult (big person) who often eats meat. But now you are still like infants who only know how to drink milk.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="hal barát = 1) deep things,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z">hal barát = 1) deep things, 2) difficult things</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="brouma; solid food, particularly meat NRSV:"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">brouma; solid food, particularly meat NRSV: I fed you with milk, not solid food, for you were not ready for solid food. Even now you are still not ready,<span class="Italic">(2)</span></Message></Annotation><note reference="3:2" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Ibrani 5:12-13</note><v n="3" />Te bosong masi bapikir sama ke orang yang cuma tau iko dong pung mau-mau sandiri sa. Kalo ada orang yang lebe dari bosong, bosong camburu, deng bakanjar kiri-kanan! Andia ko beta bilang bosong cuma tau iko bosong pung mau-mau sandiri sa. Deng bagitu, bosong sama ke manusia biasa di ini dunya sa.<bt>Cuz (elaboration) you are still thinking like people who only know how to follow their own desires/passions. If there is someone who is more/greater (physical, social, spiritual) than you, you are jealous, and argue/dispute left-right! That is why I said you only know how to follow your own desires/passions. In that way, you are merely like normal humans in this world.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="NRSV: for you are still of"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">NRSV: for you are still of the flesh. For as long as there is jealousy and quarreling among you, are you not of the flesh, and behaving according to human inclinations?</Message></Annotation><v n="4" />Tagal bosong saparu bilang, &lt;&lt;Beta ni, Paulus pung orang!&gt;&gt; Deng ada saparu yang bilang, &lt;&lt;Beta ni, Apolos pung orang!&gt;&gt; Tiap kali bosong omong bagitu, bosong kasi tunju bilang, bosong sama parsís ke manusia biasa yang sonde kanál sang Kristus.<bt>Because, some of you are saying, &lt;&lt;I here, am Paulus' person!&gt;&gt; And there are some who say, &lt;&lt;I here, amd Apolos' person!&gt;&gt; Each time you talk like that, you are showing/demonstrating that you are merely exactly like normal humans who don't know Kristus.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Compare 1:12? NRSV: For when one"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">Compare 1:12? NRSV: For when one says, “I belong to Paul,” and another, “I belong to Apollos,” are you not merely human?<span class="Italic">(4)</span></Message><Message author="Chuck Grimes" created="2015-01-16 03:12:40Z" /></Annotation><note reference="3:4" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">1 Korintus 1:12</note></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Bosong tu, sama ke satu kabón<bt>You are like a garden</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="5" />Padahal Apolos tu, sapa? Deng beta, Paulus ni, sapa? Te botong dua ni, cuma jadi orang suru-suru sa. Botong yang kasi tunju jalan ko bosong bisa parcaya sang Kristus. Apolos kasi jalan tugas iko Bos pung parenta. Deng beta ju bagitu na!<bt>Whereas is fact, that Apolos, who is he? And I, Paulus here, who am I? Cuz (elaboration) the two of us-exc, are only *servants (people who are ordered around). We are the ones who showed the way so you-pl could believe in Kristus. Apolos carried out his work/responsibilities, following/obeying the Bos's orders. And I also did like that [+speaker attitude particle: assertion that can't be denied]!</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="NRSV: What then is Apollos? What"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">NRSV: What then is Apollos? What is Paul? Servants through whom you came to believe, as the Lord assigned to each.</Message></Annotation><v n="6" />Beta yang partama-tama kasi tau sang bosong so'al Kristus. Itu sama ke beta yang tanam bibit. Ais Apolos datang ajar sang bosong. Itu sama ke dia yang siram itu bibit yang beta su tanam. Ma Tuhan Allah tu, Dia yang bekin itu bibit tumbu jadi bésar.<bt>I am the very first one who told you about Kristus. That is like I am the one who planted the seed/s. Then Apolos came and taught you. That is like he is the one who watered those seeds that I had planted. But God [known referent], He is the one who made those seeds grow until they were big.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="NRSV: I planted, Apollos watered, but"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">NRSV: I planted, Apollos watered, but God gave the growth.</Message></Annotation><note reference="3:6" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Utusan dong pung Carita 18:4-11, 24-28</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="7" />Jadi orang yang tanam bibit sonde ada pung arti. Deng yang siram itu bibit ju sonde ada pung arti. Cuma satu hal yang ada pung arti. Andia Tuhan Allah. Tagal Dia yang bekin itu bibit batumbu.<bt>So (consequently), people who plant seeds have no meaning/significance. And those who water those seeds have no significance. Only one thing has meaning/significance. That is God. Because He is the one who makes those seeds grow.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="NRSV: So neither the one who"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">NRSV: So neither the one who plants nor the one who waters is anything, but only God who gives the growth.</Message></Annotation><v n="8" />Orang yang batanam, deng orang yang basiram, dong karjá sama-sama, ke dong ada dalam satu tim. Deng samua orang yang kasi jalan Bos pung karjá, nanti Dia mau balas dong pung cape.<bt>The person who plants, and the person who waters, they work together, like they are on one/same team (loan). And, everyone who carries out the Bos's work, He will repay/reward their tiredness (=efforts).</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="NRSV: The one who plants and"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">NRSV: The one who plants and the one who waters have a common purpose, and each will receive wages according to the labor of each.</Message></Annotation><v n="9a" />Te botong sama-sama jadi Tuhan pung orang karjá. Deng bosong jadi sama ke Tuhan pung kabón yang Dia mau karjá ame.<bt>Cuz (elaboration) we-exc [i.e. who carry out God's work] together are God2's workers. And you-pl are like God2's field/garden which He is working/cultivating.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="NRSV: For we are God's servants,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">NRSV: For we are God's servants, working together; you are God's field,</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Bosong tu, sama ke satu ruma<bt>You are like a house</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="9b" />Bagitu ju, bosong sama ke satu ruma yang Tuhan Allah mau kasi bangun.<bt>In the same way, you are like a house which God wants to/is going to build.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="synergoí: partners, working on the same"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">synergoí: partners, working on the same team -- with God, or with each other working for God NRSV: God's building.<span class="Italic">(9)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="10" />Naa, Tuhan su kasi tunju Dia pung hati bae sang beta. Andia ko beta sama ke kapala tukang. Ais Tuhan tolong sang beta ko beta ajar hal-hal dasar sang bosong dari partama, ko kasi bangun fanderen yang kuat di bosong pung idop. Ais orang laen ju ajar sang bosong, ko dong bangun di atas itu fanderen yang beta su bekin. Ma tiap tukang musti karjá bae-bae ko bangun yang batúl.<bt>Naa, God2 has shown/demonstrated His goodness/grace/kindness/generostiy to me. That is why I am like a master craftsman/construction supervisor. So then God2 helped me so I taught basic/fundamental things from the beginning, to build a strong foundation in your lives. So then other people also teach you, so that they are building on top of that foundation which I have made. But each craftsman/builder must work well/carefully to build correctly/what is right.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="kapala tukang ="><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z">kapala tukang =</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="architéktoon: in Greek times, this person"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">architéktoon: in Greek times, this person not only drew the plans but managed the work. Today it would be a master builder who makes his own house designs themélion: foundation, like rocks or cement that hold the walls up<span class="Italic">(10) (10) </span>NRSV: According to the grace of God given to me, like a skilled master builder I laid a foundation, and someone else is building on it. Each builder must choose with care how to build on it.</Message></Annotation><v n="11" />Fanderen yang kuat su ada. Andia Yesus Kristus. Jadi sonde ada orang yang bisa kasi bangun fanderen laen di bosong pung hati, te Tuhan su taro fanderen yang batúl.<bt>The strong foundation is already there. That is Yesus Kristus. So (consequently), there is nobody (else) who can build a different foundation in your livers, cuz (elaboration/reason) God2 has already put in place/established the true foundation.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="NRSV: For no one can lay"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">NRSV: For no one can lay any foundation other than the one that has been laid; that foundation is Jesus Christ.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="12" />Pasti ada orang yang mau bangun di atas itu fanderen pake bahan macam-macam. Ada yang mau pake bahan mahal ke mas, perak, ko batu mangkilat. Ada yang mau pake bahan biasa ke kayu, rumput, ko alang-alang.<bt>Surely there are people who want to build on that foundation using various kinds of materials. There are those who want to use valuable materials such as gold, silver, or precious/shiny stones. There are those who want to use common material such as wood, grass, or alang-alang (long grass).</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="sekam = husk from padi"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z">sekam = husk from padi</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="NRSV: Now if anyone builds on"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">NRSV: Now if anyone builds on the foundation with gold, silver, precious stones, wood, hay, straw</Message></Annotation><v n="13" />Ma tiap tukang pung karjá nanti kantara, deng samua orang dapa tau dia pung karjá, bae ko sonde. Te nanti kalo dunya kiamat, Tuhan mau uji sang dia, sama ke Dia pake api ko kasi tunju tiap orang pung karjá ada batahan, ko sonde.<bt>But each craftsman/builder's work will become clear/obvious/visible, and everyone will be able to know that work of his, (whether it is) good or not. Cuz (elaboration) later at the end of the world, God2 is going to test him (test character, work), as if He uses fire to show whether each person's work endures/lasts, or not.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="NRSV: the work of each builder"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">NRSV: the work of each builder will become visible, for the Day will disclose it, because it will be revealed with fire, and the fire will test what sort of work each has done.</Message></Annotation><v n="14" />Kalo su uji satu orang pung karjá pake api, deng bahan yang dia pake masi batahan, nanti Tuhan kasi dia pung upa di langit.<bt>If/When a person's work has been tested using fire, and the material he used still endures/lasts, God2 will give his reward in heaven.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="NRSV: If what has been built"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">NRSV: If what has been built on the foundation survives, the builder will receive a reward.</Message></Annotation><v n="15" />Ma kalo su uji orang pung karjá pake api, deng itu bahan yang dia pake ko kasi bangun di atas fanderen jadi tabakar buang, na, Tuhan sonde kasi itu orang upa apa-apa. Ma itu tukang masi dapa salamat, biar sama ke orang yang lari kaluar dari ruma yang tabakar buang, deng dia amper mati.<bt>But if a person's work has been tested using fire, and that material which he used to build on the foundation is burned up, na, God2 will not give that person any reward. But that craftsman will/can still be saved, even though it is like a person who flees from a house that is burning down, and he nearly dies.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="NRSV: If the work is burned"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">NRSV: If the work is burned up, the builder will suffer loss; the builder will be saved, but only as through fire.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Bosong sama ke Tuhan pung ruma sambayang satu<bt>You-pl are like one of God's worship houses</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="16" />Bosong musti mangarti bilang, bosong ju sama ke Tuhan pung ruma sambayang satu, deng Dia pung Roh ada tenga di dalam ju.<bt>You-pl must understand, that you are like one of God's *worship houses, and His Spirit is also living inside.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="oidate: do you-pl know NRSV: Do"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">oidate: do you-pl know NRSV: Do you not know that you are God's temple and that God's Spirit dwells in you?<span class="Italic">(16)</span></Message></Annotation><note reference="3:16" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">1 Korintus 6:19, 2 Korintus 6:16</note><v n="17" />Deng kalo ada orang yang bekin rusak Tuhan pung ruma sambayang, andia Dia pung tampa tenga tu, na, ati-ati ó! Nanti Tuhan ju bekin rusak sang dia! Te Tuhan pung ruma sambayang tu, barisi. Andia ko bosong ju musti barisi.<bt>And if there is a person who ruins/defiles/damages God2's house of worship, that is that place where He is living, na, watch out/careful! God2 will also ruin/defile/damage him! Cuz (elaboration) God2's house of worship is clean/holy/pure. That is why you-pl must also be holy.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="NRSV: If anyone destroys God's temple,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">NRSV: If anyone destroys God's temple, God will destroy that person. For God's temple is holy, and you are that temple.</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Jadi, bosong ju musti barisi, sama"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z">Jadi, bosong ju musti barisi, sama ke Dia pung ruma sambayang.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="18" />Bosong jang tipu diri! Kalo lu anggap diri pintar, deng mangarti samua iko orang dunya sakarang pung mangarti, su jalás lu sonde mangarti satu apa ju. Kalo lu su sadar bilang, lu sonde mangarti apa-apa, baru lu bisa mulai balajar.<bt>You should not deceive yourselves! If you-sg consider yourself to be clever/wise, and understand everything according to the understanding of the people in the world nowadays, it is clear that you don't understand anything. If you are aware that you don't understand anything, only then can you begin to learn.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="en hymíin: anybody from your group"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">en hymíin: anybody from your group NRSV: Do not deceive yourselves. If you think that you are wise in this age, you should become fools so that you may become wise.<span class="Italic">(18)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="19" />Orang dunya sakarang pung pikiran, Tuhan Allah anggap bodo sa. Te dalam Tulisan Barisi ada tulis bilang:<bt>The way people in the world nowadays think, God considers/views that as stupid/ignorant. Cuz (elaboration) in the Scriptures it is written, saying:</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">&lt;&lt;Ada orang yang anggap diri ke pintar,<bt>&lt;&lt;There are people who consider themselves as clever,</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="anggap diri ke pintar"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z">anggap diri ke pintar</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">ma nanti Tuhan pake dong pung akal busuk sandiri,<bt>but God2 will use their own rotten schemes,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 3" usfm="q3">ais hiki bale ko bekin rusak sang dong!&gt;&gt;<bt>and snare them back to ruin/damage them!&gt;&gt;</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="panourgia: crafty, evil cunning, trickery, treachery"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">panourgia: crafty, evil cunning, trickery, treachery NRSV: For the wisdom of this world is foolishness with God. For it is written, “He catches the wise in their craftiness,”<span class="Italic">(19)</span></Message></Annotation><note reference="3:19" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Ayub 5:13</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="20" />Di bagian laen ada tatulis bilang,<bt>In another place it is written saying,</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="bagian"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z">bagian</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">&lt;&lt;Kotong pung Bos su tau apa yang orang pintar dong ada bapikir,<bt>&lt;&lt;Our-inc Bos already knows what it is that the clever people are thinking,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">deng orang yang musti tau mau bekin karmana,<bt>and people who should know what to do,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Dia su tau dong cuma pikir hal-hal yang parcuma sa.&gt;&gt;<bt>He already knows the things they are thinking are futile/pointless/in vain</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="NRSV: and again, “The Lord knows"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">NRSV: and again, “The Lord knows the thoughts of the wise, that they are futile.”</Message></Annotation><note reference="3:20" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Lagu Puji dong 94:11</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="21-22" />Jadi bosong jang angka-angka satu orang bilang, dia hebat. Te Tuhan yang angka orang ko pimpin sang bosong. Samua su jadi bosong pung milik. Jadi bosong pung pamimpin dong, sama ke: beta, bu Apolos, deng bu Pe'u,<bt>So (consequently), you should not lift up/praise/boast about someone saying, he is great/impressive/incredible. Cuz (elaboration) God2 is the one who elevates/appoints people to lead you-pl. Every(thing/body) has already become your property/possession. So (consquently), your leaders, such as: me, older brother Apolos, and older brother Pete,</bt><note reference="3:22" class="Note General Paragraph" usfm="f">Alkitab bahasa Yunani tulis bilang, <span class="Italic">Kefas.</span> Kefas tu, Petrus pung nama laen.<bt>The Yunani language Bible writes saying, <span class="Italic">Kefas</span>. Kefas is Petrus' other name.</bt></note>botong samua jadi bosong pung milik. Deng samua hal di ini dunya ju su jadi bosong pung milik, biar bosong idop ko mati, biar sakarang ko nanti, samua jadi bosong pung milik.<bt>all of us-exc are your possession. And everything in this world has also become your possession, whether you are alive or dead, whether now or later, everything has become your possession. [NOTE: commentarries are all over the place on this. Fee says, "One wonders whether Paul himself had all this in mind when the sentence began....You do not belong to them; they belong to you, as your servants, because “you - and they - are Christ's, and Christ is God's.”" So, don't push your UNS's too hard on this one.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="NRSV: So let no one boast"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">NRSV: So let no one boast about human leaders. For all things are yours, NRSV: whether Paul or Apollos or Cephas or the world or life or death or the present or the future-all belong to you,<span class="Italic">(21)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="23" />Deng bosong jadi Kristus pung milik. Deng Kristus jadi Tuhan Allah pung milik!<bt>And you-pl are/have become Kristus' possession. And Kristus is God's possession!</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="NRSV: and you belong to Christ,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">NRSV: and you belong to Christ, and Christ belongs to God.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Kristus pung utusan yang Dia kirim pi mana-mana<bt>Kristus' emissaries/apostles whom He sent all over the place</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <c n="4" />
      <v n="1" />Jadi bosong musti anggap sang botong bagini: jang angka-angka sang botong, te botong ni, cuma Kristus pung orang suru-suru sa. Deng Tuhan Allah parcaya sang botong ko jaga bae-bae Dia pung hal-hal yang dolu tasambunyi.<bt>[NOTE: higher level cohesion with 3:21-22.] So (consequently), you must view/consider us-exc like this: do not elevate/boast about us-exc, cuz (elaboration) we here, are merely Kristus' servants. And God trusts us to carefully guard/be responsible for His things that were previously hidden.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="mysteeríoon: Paul's job was not to"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">mysteeríoon: Paul's job was not to keep the message about Christ a secret, but to make sure everybody knows it now that the time has come NRSV: Think of us in this way, as servants of Christ and stewards of God's mysteries.<span class="Italic">(1)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="2" />Naa, orang yang jaga dia pung bos pung barang, dia musti jadi orang yang bekin iko apa yang batúl.<bt>Naa, a person who guards his boss's things, he must be a person who does according to what is right/true.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="NRSV: Moreover, it is required of"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">NRSV: Moreover, it is required of stewards that they be found trustworthy.</Message></Annotation><v n="3" />Karmana deng beta? Beta ada karjá iko apa yang batúl, ko sonde? Beta sonde toe bosong ada nilei sang beta karmana. Deng beta ju sonde pusing orang laen dong ada nilei sang beta karmana. Beta ju sonde pusing nilei beta pung diri.<bt>How about me? Do I work according to what is true, or not? I don't care how you evaluate/assess/judge me. And I also don't care2 how other people assess me. I also don't care2 how I assess myself.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="nilai ~ nilei"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z">nilai ~ nilei</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="NRSV: But with me it is"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">NRSV: But with me it is a very small thing that I should be judged by you or by any human court. I do not even judge myself.</Message></Annotation><v n="4" />Te biar beta pung hati bilang beta su bae, balóm tantu dia pung arti beta bae. Yang pantíng tu, Tuhan ada nilei sang beta karmana.<bt>Cuz (elaboration) even if my liver tells me I am good, it is stil not certain that it means I am good. What IS important, is how God2 assesses me.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="NRSV: I am not aware of"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">NRSV: I am not aware of anything against myself, but I am not thereby acquitted. It is the Lord who judges me.</Message></Annotation><v n="5" />Ais bosong jang bekin diri tukang putus parkara ko nilei orang laen dong. Tunggu Bos pung datang kambali. Te Dia yang nanti buka samua hal. Dia yang tarek kaluar hal-hal jahat yang orang sambunyi dalam galáp. Dia mau kasi tunju hal-hal yang orang pikir dalam dong pung hati. Ais Tuhan Allah mau kasi tau hal-hal yang bae, yang orang dong su bekin.<bt>So then you-pl should not be making yourselves out to be judges to assess other people. Wait for the Bos to come back. Cuz (elaboration) He is the one who will open/reveal/unveil everything. He is the one who pulls out the evil things that people have hidden in the dark. He is going to show the things that people think in their livers. So God is going to tell/make known the good things which people have done.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="tarek"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z">tarek</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="NRSV: Therefore do not pronounce judgment"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">NRSV: Therefore do not pronounce judgment before the time, before the Lord comes, who will bring to light the things now hidden in darkness and will disclose the purposes of the heart. Then each one will receive commendation from God.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="6" />Sodara dong! Beta ada ba'omong so'al beta deng bu Apolos, sama ke beta ada kasi conto ko bosong bisa balajar satu hal dari botong, bagini: <span class="Italic">Bekin iko hal-hal yang tatulis dalam Tuhan pung Tulisan Barisi sa. Jang bekin iko yang laen lai.</span> Kalo bosong balajar itu hal, bosong sonde usa bapihak, deng omong bésar tagal ada iko satu orang, deng anggap enteng yang laen.<bt>Siblings! I am talking about myself and older brother Apolos, like I am giving an example so you can learn something from us, like this: <span class="Italic">Just do according to the things that are written in God2's Holy Writings. Don't do according to anything else.</span> If you learn that thing, you don't need to be partisan/favouring one party (over another), and talk big (boast) because (you) are following one person, and belittling/viewing desparaginly another.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="physióusthe: be puffed up in favor"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">physióusthe: be puffed up in favor of one person and against another NRSV: I have applied all this to Apollos and myself for your benefit, brothers and sisters, so that you may learn through us the meaning of the saying, “Nothing beyond what is written,” so that none of you will be puffed up in favor of one against another.<span class="Italic">(6)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="7" />Jadi karmana? Bosong anggap diri laen dari yang laen, ko? Jangan! Te samua yang bosong tarima, bosong dapa dari Tuhan Allah. Jadi kalo bagitu, akurang ko bosong kapala bésar, sama ke bosong yang usaha sandiri?<bt>So (consequently), how is it? You think you're special, huh? (Lit: you consider yourselves different from others, or (what)?) Don't do that! Cuz (elaboration) everything that you have received, you obtained from God. So (consequently), if that is the case, why is it that you are big headed (proud, arrogant), like you yourselves are the ones who accomplished it?</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="se: singular, clear through the verse"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">se: singular, clear through the verse NRSV: For who sees anything different in you? What do you have that you did not receive? And if you received it, why do you boast as if it were not a gift?<span class="Italic">(7)</span></Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Padahal, Tuhan yang kasi. (at end"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z">Padahal, Tuhan yang kasi. (at end to reinforce)</Message></Annotation><v n="8" />Tingka ke samua yang bosong parlú, bosong su dapa. Ke bosong su kaya, na! Bosong bekin diri ke orang bésar, sama ke raja sa, deng botong sonde campor tangan apa-apa. Padahal Tuhan yang kasi samua yang bosong parlú. Ma kalo nanti bosong jadi raja batúl, mangkali botong bisa pegang parenta sama-sama deng bosong, to?<bt>It is as if everything that you need, you have already obtained/gotten. It's like you're already rich [+speaker attitude, obvious, can't be argued with]! You have made yourselves like big/important people, such as kings, and we-exc didn't mix hand (mexendo) in any way. Whereas in fact, God2 is the one who gave everything that you needed. But if later you really do become kings, perhaps we-exc could govern together with you-pl, right? [+facetious] [EXEG:</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="sonde bantu satu ta'i ju ="><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z">sonde bantu satu ta'i ju = (Idiom)</Message><Message author="Chuck Grimes" created="2010-10-29 07:56:16Z">Ex. Summ.</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="NRSV: Already you have all you"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">NRSV: Already you have all you want! Already you have become rich! Quite apart from us you have become kings! Indeed, I wish that you had become kings, so that we might be kings with you!</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="9" />Botong ni, yang Tuhan Allah utus ko pi mana-mana di ini dunya, ko kasi tau orang so'al Kristus. Ma satu-satu kali beta ada pikir ke Tuhan suru botong badiri paling balakang, sama ke orang bui yang ada tunggu dong pung hukuman mati. Ais Dia kasi samua orang di ini dunya, deng Dia pung ana bua di sorga, ko dong manonton ame sang botong.<bt>We-exc here, are the ones whom God has commissioned to go all over this world, to tell people about Kristus. But once in awhile I think God2 has ordered us to stand at the very end (of the line, least importance), like prisoners who are waiting for their punishment of death. So He has made/allowed everyone on this earth, and His *angels (underlings in heaven), for them to view/watch (event/spectacle/TV) us-exc.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="satu-satu kali = ; manonton ="><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z">satu-satu kali = ; manonton =</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="eschátous: last in importance, bottom of"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">eschátous: last in importance, bottom of the barrel. It may also mean the last act in the show; we are going to be executed in front of everybody, and they save that till the very end theatron: "show" is strong enough here<span class="Italic">(9) (9) </span>NRSV: For I think that God has exhibited us apostles as last of all, as though sentenced to death, because we have become a spectacle to the world, to angels and to mortals.</Message></Annotation><v n="10" />Bosong paling hebat su! Te ada orang yang anggap bosong pintar, tagal bosong ta'ika deng Kristus. Ma dong anggap botong ni, paling bodo, tagal botong jadi Kristus pung orang. Mangkali dong kira bosong tu, yang paling kuat su. Ma botong ni, noe-noe sa. Mangkali dong angka tinggi-tinggi sang bosong. Ma dong sonde taro hormat sadiki ju sang botong. Talalu batúl!<bt>You are so great/impressive/incredible [+irony]! Cuz (elaboration) there are people who consider you-pl to be clever, because you are bound/linked to Kristus. But they consider us-exc to be most stupid/ignorant, because we are Kristus' people. Perhaps they think that you must be the strongest. But we are just weaklings. Perhaps they elevate/praise/honour you. But they give no honour2 to us. It's really too much!</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="noe-noe = noe-nauk ="><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z">noe-noe = noe-nauk =</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Check that sarcasm is strong enough."><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">Check that sarcasm is strong enough. NRSV: We are fools for the sake of Christ, but you are wise in Christ. We are weak, but you are strong. You are held in honor, but we in disrepute.<span class="Italic">(10)</span></Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Ada orang yang anggap botong ni,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z">Ada orang yang anggap botong ni, paling bodo, tagal botong jadi Kristus pung orang. Ma dong anggap bosong tu, yang lebe pintar su, tagal bosong ta'ika deng Dia. Dong kira botong ni, noe-noe sa, ma bosong tu, yang paling kuat su. Dong sonde taro hormat sadiki ju sang botong, ma dong angka tinggi-tinggi sang bosong.</Message></Annotation><v n="11" />Sampe sakarang ni ju, botong rasa lapar deng aus. Botong pung pakean puruk mati. Orang maen papoko sang botong. Botong jadi orang tapaleuk yang sonde ada pung ruma.<bt>Until now, we-exc has been hungry and thirsty. Our clothes are worn. People keep beating us. We are wanderers who have no homes.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="orang tapaleuk = wanderer ; tukang"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z">orang tapaleuk = wanderer ; tukang tapaleuk = preman, bum ?? ; aus = haus ; pardiduk (Ambon) = tapaleuk</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="arti: now, present time hwras: hour,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">arti: now, present time hwras: hour, moment<span class="Italic">(11) (11) </span>peinwmen: we are hungry dipswmen: thirsty, suffer from thirst<span class="Italic">(11) (11) </span>gumniteuomen: we are poorly clothed kolaphizw: we are roughly treated, struck with a fist, beaten, physically abused<span class="Italic">(11) (11) </span>astatóumen: we are homeless, vagabond, vagrants (stigmatized) NRSV: To the present hour we are hungry and thirsty, we are poorly clothed and beaten and homeless,<span class="Italic">(11)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="12" />Botong su karjá cape deng tangan sandiri. Kalo orang omong macam-macam so'al botong, botong balas bilang, &lt;&lt;Botong minta ko Tuhan Allah bekin hal-hal yang bae kasi bosong.&gt;&gt; Kalo orang bekin susa sang botong, na, botong pili ko batahan sa.<bt>We have worked hard (tired) with our own hands. If someone says something (negative overtones) about us, we respond saying, &lt;&lt;We-exc ask that God do various good things to you-pl.&gt;&gt; If/when people make trouble for us, na, we just choose to endure/persist/put up with it.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="ergazomenoi: work, be active tais idiais"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">ergazomenoi: work, be active tais idiais xersin: with our own hands<span class="Italic">(12) (12) </span>loidorew: when reviled, abused, when cursed, insulted, slandered eulogew: bless, wih them well<span class="Italic">(12) (12) </span>diwkw: when persecuted, injurious abuse anexometha: endure, bear with, put up with, hold up<span class="Italic">(12) (12) </span>NRSV: and we grow weary from the work of our own hands. When reviled, we bless; when persecuted, we endure;</Message></Annotation><note reference="4:12" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Utusan dong pung Carita 18:3</note><v n="13" />Kalo orang omong bekin busuk botong pung nama bae, botong pili ko balas deng omong manis sa. Biar bagitu ju, ma orang masi anggap sang botong ke ampas, ko, sampa yang dadolek yang pantas ko angka buang sa.<bt>If/when people slanderr our good name, we just choose to respond with sweet/kind words. Even that being the case, nevertheless people still conider/view us as waste/dregs/pulp, or filthy rubbish, which is just worthy of throwing out.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="omong manis different from mulu manis"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z">omong manis different from mulu manis</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="dusphemew: slander, defame parakaloumen: appeal to,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">dusphemew: slander, defame parakaloumen: appeal to, urge, exhort, encourage, conciliate, speak to in a friencly manner, answer kindly<span class="Italic">(13) (13) </span>perikatharma: offscouring, dirt, scum, scapegoats, filth peripsema: dirt, offscouring, sacrifice<span class="Italic">(13) (13) </span>NRSV: when slandered, we speak kindly. We have become like the rubbish of the world, the dregs of all things, to this very day.</Message></Annotation><note reference="4:13" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Ibrani 11:38</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="14" />Beta tulis ini hal dong, bukan mau bekin bosong jadi malu. Ma beta mau togor sang bosong, tagal beta sayang bosong sama ke beta pung ana sandiri. Andia ko beta kasi tau sang bosong, ko kambali iko jalan yang batúl.<bt>I write these things, not to make you ashamed. But I want to warn/admonish/reprimand you, because I love you like my own children. That is why I am telling you, so you can return to the right path.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="entrepwn: to make you ashamed nouthetwn:"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">entrepwn: to make you ashamed nouthetwn: admonish, warn, instruct (not blame)<span class="Italic">(14) (14) </span>NRSV: I am not writing this to make you ashamed, but to admonish you as my beloved children.</Message></Annotation><v n="15" />Biar ada baribu-ribu orang yang bisa kasi tunju jalan sang bosong so'al Kristus, ma cuma ada beta sandiri sa yang jadi bosong pung bapa. Te beta ni, orang partama yang kasi tau sang bosong so'al Yesus Kristus pung Carita Bae. Andia ko bosong jadi parcaya sang Dia. Beta bekin bagitu, tagal beta ta'ika bae-bae deng Dia.<bt>Even if there were thousands of people who could show you the way about Kristus, nevertheless there is only myself who is your father. Cuz (elaboration), I here, was the first person who told you about Yesus Kristus' Good Story. That is why you came to believe in Him. I did that because I am bound/linked well/tightly with Him (=in Christ).</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="ean gar: even if murious: myriad,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">ean gar: even if murious: myriad, countless<span class="Italic">(15) (15) </span>paidagwgous: custodian, guide, slave attendant, guardian, caretaker, tutor NRSV: For though you might have ten thousand guardians in Christ, you do not have many fathers. Indeed, in Christ Jesus I became your father through the gospel.<span class="Italic">(15)</span></Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Te, tagal beta ta'ika deng Yesus"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z">Te, tagal beta ta'ika deng Yesus Kristus, andia ko beta jadi orang partama yang kasi tau sang bosong so'al Dia pung Carita Bae ais bosong parcaya sang Dia. Itu yang bekin beta ke bosong pung bapa.</Message></Annotation><v n="16" />Jadi beta minta ko bosong iko bae-bae beta pung conto.<bt>So (consequently) I ask that you carefully follow my example.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="mimetai: imitator NRSV: I appeal to"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">mimetai: imitator NRSV: I appeal to you, then, be imitators of me.<span class="Italic">(16)</span></Message></Annotation><note reference="4:16" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">1 Korintus 11:1, Filipi 3:17</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="17" />Andia ko beta kirim sang Timotius ko tolong sang bosong. Beta sayang sang dia sama ke beta pung ana sandiri. Beta parcaya sang dia, te dia ju idop ta'ika deng kotong pung Bos. Nanti dia tolong sang bosong ko kasi inga beta pung jalan idop. Beta pung idop bagitu tagal beta ta'ika deng Yesus Kristus, yang Tuhan su kirim datang. Deng itu ju sama ke yang beta ajar kasi orang sarani yang bakumpul di mana-mana.<bt>That is why I sent Timotius to help you. I love him like my own child. I trust him, cuz (elaboration) he also lives bound/linked with our-inc Bos. He will help you to remember my way of life. My life was like that because I was bound with Kristus, whom God2 has sent. And that is also the same as what I taught to the Christians (baptised people) who gather in many places/everywhere/all over the place.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="anamnesei: remind hodos: way, road, way"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">anamnesei: remind hodos: way, road, way of life<span class="Italic">(17) (17) </span>kathws: just as pantaxou: everywhere<span class="Italic">(17) (17) </span>NRSV: For this reason I sent you Timothy, who is my beloved and faithful child in the Lord, to remind you of my ways in Christ Jesus, as I teach them everywhere in every church.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="18" />Ada dari bosong yang pikir bilang, beta sonde jadi datang di situ. Andia ko dong su jadi kapala bésar.<bt>There are those among you who think that, it will not work out for me to come there. That's why they have already become big-headed (proud, arrogant).</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="ephusiwthesan: arrogant, puffed up, conceited, put"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">ephusiwthesan: arrogant, puffed up, conceited, put on airs, bold and boasting, proud, blown up NRSV: But some of you, thinking that I am not coming to you, have become arrogant.<span class="Italic">(18)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="19" />Ma kalo kotong pung Bos mau, sonde lama lai te beta su datang di kota Korintus. Ais nanti beta dapa tau memang, kalo ini orang dong cuma bamulu bésar sa, ko, dong batúl ada pung kuasa!<bt>But if our-inc Bos wants, it won't be long before I have come to the city of Korintus. So then I will know directly/truly, whether these people are only just big-mouthing, or, they really do have power/authority!</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="takheoos: quickly, at once, without delay,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">takheoos: quickly, at once, without delay, soon thelese: according to his will<span class="Italic">(19) (19) </span>gnwsomai: know, find out ou ton logon: not the word<span class="Italic">(19) (19) </span>ten dunamin: power, might, strength, force NRSV: But I will come to you soon, if the Lord wills, and I will find out not the talk of these arrogant people but their power.<span class="Italic">(19)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="20" />Te Tuhan Allah, Raja yang ada pung kuasa. Ais Dia pung orang dong sonde pake mulu baminya ko bangun orang pung parcaya, ma dong pake kuasa yang batúl.<bt>Cuz (elaboration) God is the King who has power/authority. So His people don't use oily mouths to build people's faith, but they use real power/authority.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="mulu baminya"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z">mulu baminya</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="NRSV: For the kingdom of God"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">NRSV: For the kingdom of God depends not on talk but on power.</Message></Annotation><v n="21" />Ais bosong pung mau karmana? Kalo beta datang, na, beta omong karás deng kasi hukum sang bosong? Ko, beta datang kasi tunju sayang deng hati manis?<bt>So then what do you-pl want to do? If I come, na, should I speak harshly and punish you? Or, should I come showing/demonstrating love and sweet liver (gracious/gentle)?</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="hrabdw: rod, discipline, correction prautetos: gentleness,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">hrabdw: rod, discipline, correction prautetos: gentleness, humility, courtesy, considerateness, meekness<span class="Italic">(21) (21) </span>NRSV: What would you prefer? Am I to come to you with a stick, or with love in a spirit of gentleness?</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Ada orang dalam jama'at yang maen parampuan<bt>There are people/person in the congregation who are playing women (fooling around sexually)</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <c n="5" />
      <v n="1" />Beta dengar bilang, ada satu orang dalam bosong pung jama'at yang maen parampuan. Padahal, yang dia bekin tu, lebe jahat dari orang yang sonde kanál sang Tuhan Allah. Te dia maen tidor deng dia pung mama tiri sandiri!<bt>I have heard that, there is someone in your congregation who is playing women. Whereas in fact, what he is doing is more evil than people who don't know God. Cuz (elaboration) he keeps sleeping with his own stepmother! [EXEG: stepmother: see Ex. Summ. CEV, TEV]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="holos akouetai: generally speaking, actually, everywhere"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">holos akouetai: generally speaking, actually, everywhere it is actually reported porneia: fornication, unchastity, every kind of unlawful sexual relations<span class="Italic">(1) (1) </span>LITERALLY: Actually sexual immorality is reported among you, and such sexual immorality as does not even occur among the [heathen / unbelievers], that a man has his father's wife.</Message></Annotation><note reference="5:1" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Carita Ulang so'al Jalan Idop 22:30</note><v n="2" />Ma bosong pung sombong lai, ke bosong pung jama'at ada bae-bae sa! Yang batúl, bosong musti malu deng rasa susa. Orang bagitu tu, bosong musti usir buang sang dia jao-jao!<bt>But you-pl are so arrogant/full of yourselves, as if your congregation is just fine! The right thing, is that you should be ashamed, and troubled/distressed. A person like that, you must evict him far-far (complete separation)! [EXEG: TN; explication required from UNS responses.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="fusiow: be puffed up, proud, arrogant,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">fusiow: be puffed up, proud, arrogant, conceited epentheésate: mourn, express sadness or horror or condemnation, grieve, mourn<span class="Italic">(2) (2) </span>airw: to take away, remove, sweep away LITERALLY: An you [plural] are proud! But rather you should mourn, so that he should be removed from your midst, the one who has done this deed.<span class="Italic">(2)</span></Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="3" />Biar kotong bajao satu deng satu, ma beta pung hati ada tenga di bosong. Jadi beta su putus itu orang jahat pung parkara, sama ke beta ada di situ memang.<bt>Even though we-inc are mutually far from each other, nevertheless my liver is staying/living among you. [NOTE: 1st sentence resonates with a well known proverb] So (consequently), I have already decided that evil person's case, just like I am directly there with you.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="apeimi: be absent, be away pareimi:"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">apeimi: be absent, be away pareimi: be present<span class="Italic">(3) (3) </span>katergasomenon (aorist): commit, achieve, accomplish, do tóoi pneúmati: in my spirit, my thoughts (mana`o)<span class="Italic">(3) (3) </span>LITERALLY: For I indeed, being absent in body but present in spirit, already I have judged, as being present, the one who has done thus.</Message></Annotation><v n="4" />Beta ada pung hak ko putus bagitu, tagal Yesus jadi kotong pung Bos, deng beta ni, Dia pung utusan. Ais bosong musti dudu bakumpul ko putus itu parkara, bawa Bos pung nama. Deng beta pung hati ada sama-sama deng bosong ju.<bt>I have the right to make a decision like that, because Yesus is our-inc Bos, and I here, and His apostle/emissary. So you must sit down together to make a decision on that case, bringing the Bos's name/reputation/authority. And my liver will also be together with you.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="en tw onamati tou kuriou emwn"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">en tw onamati tou kuriou emwn Iesou: on the authority of, as representing, in accordance with sunagw: to gather together, bring together, call together<span class="Italic">(4) (4) </span>dunamis: power, might, strength, force LITERALLY: In the name of our Lord Jesus, coming together, and my spirit with you [plural], by the power of our Lord Jesus,<span class="Italic">(4)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="5" />Ais bosong musti sarakan itu orang pi setan dong pung bos, ko biar lama-lama itu orang angka buang hal-hal jahat yang ada di dia pung hati. Ais nanti kalo kotong pung Bos datang kambali, na, Dia bisa kasi salamat sang itu orang dari dia pung sala-sala.<bt>So then you must turn over/give up that person to the bos of the evil spirits, so that eventually that person will get rid of the evil things which are in his liver. So later, when our-inc Bos comes back, na, He can save that person from his wrongs.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="What would the church actually do"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">What would the church actually do in a case like this? paradidwmi: to give over, hand over, deliver, entrust<span class="Italic">(5) (5) </span>Satanaai: da Devil olethros: [religious] destruction, ruin, death<span class="Italic">(5) (5) </span>sarks: sinful nature, human nature swzw: to save, rescue, preserve, keep from harm<span class="Italic">(5) (5) </span>en te hemera tou kuriou: the day of the Lord, when the Lord come in judgment satanáai: Satan, one name for the Devil<span class="Italic">(5) (5) </span>LITERALLY: To give such a one over to Satan, for the destruction of the sinful nature, in order that the spirit may be saved in the Day of the Lord.</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Ais, bosong musti sarakan itu orang"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z">Ais, bosong musti sarakan itu orang pi di setan dong pung bos, ko biar hal-hal jahat yang ada di dia pung hati kaná usir buang.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="6" />Sonde bae kalo bosong mulu bésar! Jang lupa bilang, kotong campor bibit roti sadiki sa, ko bekin reis roti anteru. Bibit roti tu, sama ke orang pung jahat. Ais, kalo kasi biar dia bekin jahat di bosong pung teng-tenga, nanti orang sarani laen dong ju iko-iko bekin jahat!<bt>It is not good if/when you-pl talk big (arrogant)! Don't forget that, we mix just a little yeast (lit. bread seed) to make the whole bread rise. That yeast, is like that person's evil. So then, if you permit him to do evil in your midst, other Christians will also go along doing evil!</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="kauxema: boast, object of boasting, pride"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">kauxema: boast, object of boasting, pride mikros: small, little bit<span class="Italic">(6) (6) </span>ony take? ony need? LITERALLY: Not good, your boasting. Don't you know that a little bit of yeast [leavens the whole dough / makes all the dough rise]?<span class="Italic">(6)</span></Message></Annotation><note reference="5:6" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Galatia 5:9</note><v n="7" />Usir itu orang jahat dari bosong pung jama'at sama ke dolu orang Yahudi dong angka buang samua ragi dari dong pung ruma ko siap makan pesta Paska. Deng bagitu, baru bosong bisa jadi kambali ke orang yang sonde ada pung jahat dalam hati lai. Bosong musti jadi bagitu. Dolu dong horo domba ana yang sonde ada pung sala ko bekin korban Paska. Dari balakang dong bunu bekin mati Tuhan Allah pung Orang Barisi, ko jadi korban yang bekin barisi kotong pung hati.<bt>Evict that evil person from your congregation just like long ago the Yahudi people (completely) got rid of all the yeast in their houses to prepare to eat the Paska feast. Like that, only then will you-pl be able to again become like a person who has no evil in his liver. You must become like that. Formerly they ritually slaughtered a lamb (sheep offspring) who had done no wrong to make the Paska (Passover, Easter) *sacrifice. Later on they killed God's Holy Person, to be a/the sacrifice which makes our livers clean/holy. [EXEG: CR, Ex. Summ. The figure is taken from the custom of ridding the Jewish household of all leaven in preparation for the Passover (Exodus 12:15f; 13:7) [Ed, ICC, NCBC].]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="ekkathairw: clean out thuw: to slaughter,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">ekkathairw: clean out thuw: to slaughter, kill<span class="Italic">(7) (7) </span>LITERALLY: Clean out the old yeast, in order that you may be a new dough, just as you are, without yeast. For Christ, our Passover lamb, has been slaughtered.</Message></Annotation><note reference="5:7" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Kaluar dari Masir 12:5</note><v n="8" />Dolu orang Yahudi makan pesta Paska pake roti bakál yang sonde pake ragi. Sakarang kotong sama ke itu roti yang sonde pake ragi. Andia ko kotong musti jaga kotong pung diri ko jang bekin hal-hal jahat dong, deng jang bekin orang laen dong saki hati. Kotong musti omong yang batúl tarús. Deng bagitu, orang lia bilang, kotong ada bekin samua-samua iko kotong pung hati bae.<bt>Formerly the Yahudi people ate the Paska feast using trail bread which didn't use yeast2. Now we-inc are like that bread which doesn't use yeast. That is why we must guard ourselves to not do evil things, and not make other people angry/vengeful/upset. We-inc must keep saying what is true. In that way, people will see that we are doing everything according to our goodness/grace/kindness.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="heortazw: to celebrate a [religious] festival"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">heortazw: to celebrate a [religious] festival kakia: depravity, wickedness, vice<span class="Italic">(8) (8) </span>poneria: wickedness, baseness, maliciousness, sinfulness, evil, desire to harm others, ill will, spite eilikrineia: sincerity, purity of motive. = 2 Cor 2:17.<span class="Italic">(8) (8) </span>aletheia: truthfulness, dependability, uprightness LITERALLY: So that we may celebrate the festival, not with old yeast of wicked and malicious yeast, but without yeast, with sincerity and truth.<span class="Italic">(8)</span></Message></Annotation><note reference="5:8" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Kaluar dari Masir 13:7, Carita Ulang so'al Jalan Idop 16:3</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="9" />Dolu beta parná tulis surat bilang, &lt;&lt;Jang bacampor deng orang yang maen serong deng orang yang bukan dong pung laki ko dong pung bini.&gt;&gt;<bt>Formerly I once wrote saying, &lt;&lt;don't mix/get involved with people who play off-track (sexually) with a person who is not their husband or wife.&gt;&gt;</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="sunanameignumi: mix together, mingle with, associate"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">sunanameignumi: mix together, mingle with, associate with pornos: fornicator, one who practises sexual immorality<span class="Italic">(9) (9) </span>LITERALLY: I wrote you a letter not to associate with those who practise sexual immorality</Message></Annotation><v n="10" />Beta sonde ada pung maksud, ko bosong jang bacampor deng <span class="Italic">samua</span> orang di ini dunya yang sonde toe sang Tuhan Allah, ko orang balalas, ko orang putar-balek yang tipu ame orang pung barang, ko tukang songgo dong. Te kalo bagitu, na, bosong musti bekin diri tapisa dari samua orang di ini dunya.<bt>It is/was not my intention, that you shouldn't mix with <span class="Italic">everyone</span> in this world who doesn't care about God, or greedy people, or deceivers who trick people taking their things, or people involved in traditional worship. Cuz (elaboration) if (we did) like that, you would have to separate yourselves from everybody on this earth. [EXEG: Gk harpaks has 2 senses 1) swindler, 2) robber. Note KJV ‘extortioner’, NLT/AGNT/ NASB/NIV ‘swindlers’, CEV ‘who cheats’, TB ‘penipu’. This contrasts with TEV ‘thieves’ and NRSV ‘robbers’. For some odd reason LN only gives the second sense, which even the CEV overrides. BAGD gives both and says the first sense “perhaps better” captures the sense of the word. Now add to that the local Timor worldview, where most readers would say “I'm safe, cuz I'm not a robber.” Whereas as with ‘swindler’ there's more chance of evoking the desired response “Uh-oh. Touché. I'm in trouble.” (Keep in mind this foreshadows the truly good news in 1 Cor. 6: 9ff where these types “cannot inherit the kingdom of heaven, but such WERE some of you…”)]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="*** (2009) note added"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z">*** (2009) note added</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="pleonektes: one who is greedy for"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">pleonektes: one who is greedy for gain, covetous person, money grubber harpaks: swindler, robber, want to seize wealth by force<span class="Italic">(10) (10) </span>eidwlolatres: idolator, idol worshipper ofeilw: to be obligated, to have to do something<span class="Italic">(10) (10) </span>eksepxomai: to come out LITERALLY: Not as all the ones of this world who practise sexual immorality, or greedy persons, or swindlers, or idolators, since then you would have to go out of the world.<span class="Italic">(10)</span></Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Beta sonde ba'omong so'al orang di"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z">Beta sonde ba'omong so'al orang di ini dunya yang sonde toe sang Tuhan Allah, ko orang balalas, ko orang putar-balek yang tipu ame orang pung barang, ko tukang songgo dong. Padahal, bosong musti kaluar/tapisa/ondor dari ini dunya (pung jalan idop), ko jang campor deng orang macam bagitu dong.</Message></Annotation><v n="11" />Ma sakarang, yang beta omong tu, andia: bosong jang campor deng orang yang bilang dia jadi orang sarani, padahal dia ada maen serong ko, dia balalas ko, dia basonggo ko, dia ada omong bekin rusak orang pung nama ko, dia mabok barát ko, dia putar-balek ko mau ame orang pung barang. Kotong jang bacampor deng orang macam bagitu dong. Jang dudu makan deng dong lai!<bt>But now, what I am talking about is this: you should not mix with a person who says he is a Christian, whereas in fact, he is playing off-track (sexually--short for for Gk. porneia; long form above in vs.9), or he is greedy, or he is involved in traditional worship, or he is slandering someone's name, or he is heavily drunk, or he is deceiving to try to take someone else's things. We should not mix with people of that sort (recap for emphasis). Don't sit and eat with them anymore (implies you have no problem with their behaviour)!</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="loidoros: verbally abusive person methusos: drunkard|i(11)"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">loidoros: verbally abusive person methusos: drunkard<span class="Italic">(11) (11) </span>sunesthiw: eat with someone LITERALLY: But now I write to you not to associate with anyone called a brother who practices sexual immorality, or is greedy, or an idolator, or verbally abusive, or a drunkard, or a swindler.<span class="Italic">(11)</span></Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="12" />Bosong ada pung hak ko nilei orang sarani dong pung idop. Ma beta sonde ada pung hak ko putus parkara kasi orang yang sonde parcaya sang Tuhan Allah.<bt>You-pl have the right to assess the life of Christians. But I have no right to make decisions about the cases of people who don't believe in God.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="krinw: to judge, decide, bring before"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">krinw: to judge, decide, bring before a court, condemn LITERALLY: For what business is it for me to judge those outside? Do you not judge those inside?<span class="Italic">(12)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="13" />Te Dia sandiri yang nanti putus parkara kasi orang yang sonde parcaya sang Dia. Ma bosong jang lupa Tuhan pung Tulisan Barisi yang tulis bilang, &lt;&lt;Orang yang subu diri jadi Tuhan pung orang, ma dia maen bekin hal-hal jahat, usir buang sang dia sa!&gt;&gt;<bt>Cuz (elaboration) He himself will judge the cases of people who don't believe in Him. But don't forget that God2's Scriptures which write saying, &lt;&lt;The person who refers to himself as being God2's person, but he keeps doing evil things, just evict him!&gt;&gt;</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="eksairw: to expel, take away LITERALLY:"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">eksairw: to expel, take away LITERALLY: But God will judge those outside. "Expel the evil person from among you!"<span class="Italic">(13)</span></Message></Annotation><note reference="5:13" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Carita Ulang so'al Jalan Idop 13:5, 17:7, 19:19; 22:21,24; 24:7</note></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Orang parcaya jang nae pangadilan deng sodara orang parcaya laen<bt>Believers should not go to court with other fellow believers</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <c n="6" />
      <v n="1" />Kalo satu orang sarani baparkara deng orang sarani laen, akurang ko bosong maju pi pangadilan di muka tukang putus parkara yang sonde kanál deng Tuhan Allah? Karmana bisa bagitu? Lebe bae badiri di muka orang parcaya dong, ko dong yang urus bosong pung parkara!<bt>If one Christian has a dispute with another Christian, why do you-pl go to court before judges who don't know God? How can you do that? It would be better to stand before the believers, so they can handle your dispute!</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="maju = bring (problem to), expose"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z">maju = bring (problem to), expose (tidak malu, barani)</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="tolmaw: dare, presume, bring oneself, have"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">tolmaw: dare, presume, bring oneself, have the audacity pragma: lawsuit, dispute, cause for trial, case<span class="Italic">(1) (1) </span>krinesthai: go to the law, court, judge adikoi: the unrighteous, [unbelievers, pagans]<span class="Italic">(1) (1) </span>hagion: saints, holy ones, ones consecrated to God LITERALLY: A certain one of you having a dispute with another one, how can you do the shocking thing to take your case before the unrighteous, and not before the saints?<span class="Italic">(1)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="2" />Tingka ke bosong sonde tau bilang, orang parcaya dong yang nanti putus parkara kasi samua orang di ini dunya. Jadi, karmana sampe bosong sonde mampu urus hal kici ana dong sandiri?<bt>It's as if you don't know that the believers are the ones who will decide the cases for every person on this earth. So (consequently), how is it that you are unable to handle tiny little matters yourselves?</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="krinw: to judge, decide anaxios: incompetent,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">krinw: to judge, decide anaxios: incompetent, unworthy, not good enough<span class="Italic">(2) (2) </span>elachistos: trivial, very small, unimportant, insignificant kriterion: lawcourt, court<span class="Italic">(2) (2) </span>kósmon: not just the present evil scheme of things on earth, which the word often refers to, but the whole universe, as the next verse says LITERALLY: Or do you not know that the saints will judge the world? And since the world will be judged by you, are you incompetent to judge trivial cases?<span class="Italic">(2)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="3" />Yang batúl, kotong yang nanti putus parkara kasi Tuhan pung ana bua dari sorga dong. Jadi pasti bosong yang musti urus parkara hari-hari dong.<bt>In actual fact, we-inc are the ones who will decide the cases of God2's angels. So (consequently), surely you are the ones who must handle the daily disputes.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="metige: not to speak of, let"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">metige: not to speak of, let alone, how much more biotika: things belonging to daily life, human life, earthly life<span class="Italic">(3) (3) </span>LITERALLY: Do you not know that we will judge angels? How much more things having to do with everyday life.</Message></Annotation><v n="4" />Tamba lai, kalo bosong orang parcaya ada baparkara so'al hal kici ana dong, akurang ko bosong pake tukang putus parkara yang orang sarani sonde hormat sang dong?<bt>Furthermore, if you believers have a dispute about tiny little things, why is it that you use judge whom the Christians don't respect?</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="exoutheneeménos: despised, considered nothing, object of"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">exoutheneeménos: despised, considered nothing, object of contempt, something of no account, amounting to nothing. In this case it could mean the people in the church who were the least esteemed, but in the light of verses before it probably means people who have no standing as Christians because they aren't Christians to begin with kathidzw: appoint, install<span class="Italic">(4) (4) </span>LITERALLY: Therefore if you have disputes about everyday things, why do you appoint as judges those who amount to nothing in the church?</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="5" />Naa, beta mau omong satu hal yang musti bekin bosong malu. Karmana? Sama ke di bosong pung teng-tenga, sonde ada satu orang ju yang cukup pintar ko urus hal kici ana dong, macam ke parkara yang muncul di kotong pung sodara.<bt>Now [+shift], I want to talk about a matter which should make you ashamed. How is that? It's like in your midst, there is not one person who is clever/wise enough to handle (these) tiny little matters, such as the disputes with arise/appear among our-inc siblings. [EXEG: Scholars are divided as to whether this parenthetical statement “I say this to your shame” refers to the preceding or the following statement (see Ex. Summ.). One scholar on Gk discourse (JEG) makes the comment “pròs entropeén hymíin: shame, humiliation. Could refer to what Paul already said, but more likely he is saying that now he wants to say something that will really shame them.”] [NOTE to daughter translations: the ov transition into 5 with “Sakarang” seems too strong/abrupt, so I've softened it to “Naa,…” which signals a slightly softer shift. Many daughter lgs don't have an equivalent, but the MTTs usually have found a regular strategy where “Naa” occurs in the KM.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="*** (2009) notes added, Sakarang changed"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z">*** (2009) notes added, Sakarang changed to Naa</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="pròs entropeén hymíin: shame, humiliation. Could"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">pròs entropeén hymíin: shame, humiliation. Could refer to what Paul already said, but more likely he is saying that now he wants to say something that will really shame them sophos: wise, clever, killful, experienced<span class="Italic">(5) (5) </span>diakrinw: make a decision [not 'to judge'] anà méson: settle a dispute between one brother and another<span class="Italic">(5) (5) </span>LITERALLY: I say this to shame you. So is there among you not one wise person who can make a decision between brothers?</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Di bosong pung teng-tenga, ke sonde"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z">Di bosong pung teng-tenga, ke sonde ada satu orang ju yang pintar ko urus hal kici ana dong, macam ke parkara yang muncul antara kotong pung sodara, ko?</Message></Annotation><v n="6" />Ma orang parcaya satu, hela bawa dia pung sodara orang parcaya pi di muka tukang putus parkara! Padahal itu tukang putus parkara sonde parcaya sang Tuhan!<bt>But one believer is dragging off his sibling believer in front of a judge! Whereas in fact, that judge doesn't believe in God2!</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="apistos: faithless, unbelieving LITERALLY: But brother"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">apistos: faithless, unbelieving LITERALLY: But brother goes to court against brother, and that before unbelievers.<span class="Italic">(6)</span></Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="7" />Ada yang sonde batúl, to? Bosong su kala, kalo bosong satu deng satu maju pi pangadilan. Ada lebe bae, kasi biar lu pung sodara kalo dia bekin sala kasi lu. Deng kalo lu pung sodara orang parcaya ada curi ame lu pung barang, ada lebe bae kasi biar ko dia ame itu barang sa!<bt>There is that which is not right/true/correct, right? You-pl have already lost, if one of you goes to court with another. It would be better, to just let your-sg sibling be if he does wrong to you. And if your sibling believer is stealing your-sg things, it would be better/best to just let him take those things!</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="maju pi pangadilan = take to"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z">maju pi pangadilan = take to court</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="ede men oun: so already therefore"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">ede men oun: so already therefore hwlos: actually<span class="Italic">(7) (7) </span>heétteema: failure, defeat, loss, not living up to your Christian principles, not acting like Christians at all krima: dispute, lawsuit<span class="Italic">(7) (7) </span>ouxi mallon: not rather adikew: do wrong<span class="Italic">(7) (7) </span>aposterew: steal, rob, defraud LITERALLY: So because you have lawsuits among yourselves you are already actually defeated. Why not rather be wronged? Why not rather be robbed?<span class="Italic">(7)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="8" />Ma bosong orang parcaya satu bekin sala kasi dia pung sodara. Deng satu ada curi ame dari satu. Padahal bosong sama-sama orang parcaya!<bt>But one of you believers is doing wrong to his sibling. And one is stealing from another. When in fact, you are both believers!</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="NOTE: Adriana asks that we review"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z">NOTE: Adriana asks that we review vs.7-8, because she feels they are still not yet clear.</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: But you do wrong and"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: But you do wrong and you steal, and that against your brothers!</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="9" />Bosong tingka ke sonde mangarti ini hal dong! Padahal orang yang sonde suka bekin yang batúl, sonde mungkin bisa maso jadi Tuhan Allah pung kelu dong. Jang kasi biar bosong pung diri kaná tipu, ko bosong bekin sala! Orang yang maen serong deng orang yang bukan dong pung laki ko dong pung bini, yang maen songgo, yang barsina, laki-laki yang batidor deng laki-laki,<bt>It is as if you don't understand these matters! Whereas in fact, people who don't like to do what is right, will no way be able to enter becoming God's family. Don't allow yourselves to be deceived, so that you do wrong! People who who play off-track with a person who is not their husband or wife (Gk pornoi), who are involved in traditional worship, who commit adultery (Gk moixoi), men who mutually sleep with men, [NOTE: last two combined in KM; EXEG: combination of Gk /malakoi/ and /arsenokoitai/ together are taken as passive and active members in homosexual intercourse; separately they could be taken as "effeminate" and "male prostitute", but not when the two terms occur together--BADG and a wealth of recent literature support this. Paul seems to be deliberately explicit--clearly the active member is wrong, but don't think those of you who participate passively are free from guilt, no!]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="meme' = banci, effeminate, laki-laki yang"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z">meme' = banci, effeminate, laki-laki yang bagaya parampuan ; *** (2009) fixed order of how we match terms with Gk</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="aikos: unrighteous planaw: lead astray, cause"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">aikos: unrighteous planaw: lead astray, cause to wander, mislead, deceive<span class="Italic">(9) (9) </span>pornos: sexually immoral person, fornicator eidwlolatros: idolators<span class="Italic">(9) (9) </span>moixos: adulterer malakoì ... arsenokóitai: passive and active partners in homosexual acts, presented here negatively as perversions, effeminate, male prostitute<span class="Italic">(9) (9) </span>arsenokoites: male homosexual LITERALLY: Do you not know that the unrighteous will not inherit the kingdom of God? Do not be deceived. Not sexually immoral persons, nor idolators, nor adulterers, nor male prostitutes, nor homosexuals,<span class="Italic">(9)</span></Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Orang yang maen parampuan, yang maen"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z">Orang yang maen parampuan, yang maen songgo, yang maen serong deng orang yang bukan dong pung laki ko bini, laki-laki yang batidor deng laki-laki,</Message></Annotation><v n="10" />orang yang pancuri, yang balalas, yang minum mabo, yang omong bekin busuk orang pung nama, yang putar-balek ko ame orang pung barang dong, te samua orang yang macam ke dong sonde mungkin bisa maso jadi Tuhan pung orang!<bt>people who steal, those who are greedy, those who drink (until) drunk, those who slander other people's names, those who deceive to take other people's things, cuz (elaboration) every person of that sort cannot possibly be able to enter becoming God2's people!</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="kléptai ... hárpages: thief. The first"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">kléptai ... hárpages: thief. The first are more violent, like muggers; the second more slick pleonektes: greedy person, covetous person<span class="Italic">(10) (10) </span>methusos: drunkard loidoros: reviler, abusive person, verbally abusive person<span class="Italic">(10) (10) </span>harpaks: swindler LITERALLY: nor thieves, nor greedy persons, nor drunkards, nor verbally abusive persons, nor swindlers, shall inherit the kingdom of God.<span class="Italic">(10)</span></Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="11" />Padahal, dolu bosong saparu memang bagitu ju! Ma Tuhan Allah su hapus buang bosong pung sala-sala dong ko bekin barisi sang bosong. Deng Dia ju su buka jalan ko bosong bisa babae kambali deng Dia. Dia bekin samua tu, tagal bosong ta'ika deng kotong pung Bos Yesus Kristus, deng tagal bosong ju ta'ika deng Tuhan pung Roh.<bt>Whereas in fact, formerly some of you were really like that also! But God has wiped away your wrongs to make you clean/holy/pure. And He has also opened the way so you could be in a mutually right relationship with Him again. He did all that, because you are bound/linked with our Bos, Yesus Kristus, and because you are also bound/linked with God2's Spirit.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="apeloúsasthe: washed clean from sin --"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">apeloúsasthe: washed clean from sin -- might also be an indirect reference to baptism, but this is not the main thing hagiadzw: to make holy, consecrate, sanctify, dedicate<span class="Italic">(11) (11) </span>dikaiow: treated as righteous, be justified allà ... allà ... allà: not a time sequence, but three aspects of the big change, all brought about by the new relationship with Christ and the Spirit (which is also not presented as a time sequence)<span class="Italic">(11) (11) </span>LITERALLY: And certain ones of you were that. But you were washed, but you were consecrated, but you were treated as righteous by the name of the Lord Jesus Christ and by the Spirit of our God.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Kalo lu jaga bae-bae lu pung badan, itu kasi tunju hormat sang Tuhan<bt>If you take careful care of your body, that shows respect/honour to God2</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="12" />Beta ada pung hak ko bekin samua-samua. Ma samua yang beta mau bekin tu, balóm tantu bae kasi sang beta. Ais, biar beta ada pung hak ko bekin samua-samua, ma beta sonde mau hal yang sonde bae ada pegang kuasa sang beta.<bt>I have the right to do anything/everything. But everything that I want to do, it is not yet sure that it is good for me. So then, even though I have the right to do anything/everything, nevertheless I don't want things that are not good to hold power/authority over me.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="éxestin: is permitted, without saying who"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">éxestin: is permitted, without saying who gives the permission, is proper, is possible sumopherw: to benefit, be an advantage, good for, profitable, gain<span class="Italic">(12) (12) </span>exousiastheésomai: be enslaved by, be put under the authority of, have the right or power over someone or something LITERALLY: All things are permissable for me, but not all things are good for me. All things are permissable for me, but I will not be brought under the control of anything.<span class="Italic">(12)</span></Message></Annotation><note reference="6:12" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">1 Korintus 10:23</note><v n="13" />Conto ke, ada orang bilang, &lt;&lt;Makanan parlú sang parú, deng parú parlú sang makanan.&gt;&gt; Ma inga te nanti Tuhan kasi ancor dua-dua.<bt>For example, someone said, &lt;&lt;Food is needed for the stomach, and the stomach needs/is needed for food.&gt;&gt; But remember [warning], cuz (elaboration) God2 will destroy both of them.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="brwma: food, solid food koilia: stomach|i(13)"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">brwma: food, solid food koilia: stomach<span class="Italic">(13) (13) </span>katargew: abolish, wipe out, do away with, put an end to, destroy swma: body<span class="Italic">(13) (13) </span>porneia: prostitution, unchastity, fornication, every kind of unlawful sexual intercourse LITERALLY: Food is for the stomach, and the stomach for food. But God will destroy both of them. The body is not for sexual immorality, but for the Lord, and the Lord is for the body.<span class="Italic">(13)</span></Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Conto laen lai, kotong jang pake kotong pung badan ko bisa maen serong deng orang yang bukan kotong pung laki ko kotong pung bini. Ma kotong pake kotong pung badan ko kotong bisa karjá kasi sang kotong pung Bos. Deng kotong pung Bos yang milik kotong pung badan ju.<bt>Another example, we should not use our-inc bodies to be able to play off-track with someone who is not our husband or wife. But we (should) use our bodies so we could work for our Bos. And our Bos is the one who owns our bodies. [EXEG: Gk dense play on words “(body) for the Lord, and the Lord for the body”. See Ex.Summ. for complexities. Avoid phrasing that implies he has sexual rights.]</bt><v n="14" />Waktu kotong pung Bos Yesus su mati, Tuhan Allah yang kasi idop kambali sang Dia. Jadi nanti kalo kotong su mati, Dia ju ada pung kuasa ko kasi idop kambali sang kotong.<bt>When our Bos Yesus had died, God brought Him back to life. So (consequently), later when we have died, He also has the power/authority to bring us back to life.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="egeirw: raise [from the dead, from"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">egeirw: raise [from the dead, from sickness] "body" implicit<span class="Italic">(14) (14) </span>LITERALLY: But God raised the Lord and he will raise us up by his power.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="15" />Bosong pung badan jadi Kristus pung milik, sama ke bosong jadi bagian dari Kristus pung badan. Tantu bosong su tau itu hal! Jadi kalo beta pake bagian dari Kristus pung badan, ais pi bacampor deng parampuan nakal pung badan, karmana? Jangan! Te itu sonde pantas!<bt>Your-pl bodies are Kristus' possession, just as if you are a part of Kristus' body. Surely you already know that! So (consequently), if I use a part of Kristus' body, and then go mix/get involved with the body of a prostitute/whore, how is that? Don't do it! Cuz (elaboration) it is not appropriate!</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Metonymy? melos: member, part, limb, body"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">Metonymy? melos: member, part, limb, body part<span class="Italic">(15) (15) </span>ara: so, then, consequently oun: so, therefore, consequently, then<span class="Italic">(15) (15) </span>porne: prostitute me genoito: may it never be! God forbid!<span class="Italic">(15) (15) </span>LITERALLY: Do you not know that your bodies are body parts of Christ? So then shall I make Christ's body parts a prostitute's body parts? May it never be!</Message></Annotation><v n="16" />Tantu bosong su tau, kalo orang maen serong ko tidor bacampor deng parampuan nakal, dong dua su ta'ika jadi satu. Te ada tatulis di Tulisan Barisi bilang, &lt;&lt;Dong dua su ta'ika jadi satu.&gt;&gt;<bt>Surely you already know, that if a person plays off-track to sleep mixing with a prostitute in that way, the two of them are bound/linked together as one. Cuz (elaboration) it is written in the Scriptures saying, &lt;&lt;The two are bound together as one.&gt;&gt;</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="kollaw: join closely together, unite sarks:"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">kollaw: join closely together, unite sarks: flesh, body, human being. Drop the "body" metaphor? [MC]. Needs to be parallel to 17.<span class="Italic">(16) (16) </span>LITERALLY: Or do you not know that the one who is joined to a prostitute becomes one body [with her]. It says, "The two shall become one flesh."</Message></Annotation><note reference="6:16" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Carita Mula-mula 2:24</note><v n="17" />Ma orang yang idop satu hati deng kotong pung Bos, su jadi satu deng Dia, sama ke dong dua ada ta'ika deng satu roh.<bt>But a person who lives one-livered (in accord, harmony) with our-inc Bos, has become united with Him, just like the two of them are bound/linked with the same spirit.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: But the one who is"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: But the one who is joined to the Lord is one spirit [with him].</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="18" />Kalo lu dapa sampát ko maen serong deng orang yang bukan lu pung laki ko lu pung bini, na, lari jao-jao! Orang bekin sala macam-macam yang bekin rusak sang dong sandiri, deng bekin rusak orang laen ju. Ma orang yang suka hohongge, bekin rusak dia pung badan sandiri.<bt>If you-sg have opportunity to play off-track with a person who is not your husband or your wife, na, run far away (complete separation)! People do various sorts of wrong that ruin/defile their own selves, and also ruin/defile other people as well. But a person who is sexually promiscuous, ruins/defiles his own body.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="[unsur &quot;all&quot;? ; bekin rusak &gt;"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z">[unsur "all"? ; bekin rusak &gt; bekin tasala? ]</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="pheugw: flee from, seek safety in"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">pheugw: flee from, seek safety in flight, escape, avoid, shun porneia: sexual immorality of all kinds<span class="Italic">(18) (18) </span>hamartema: sin, ransgression ektos: outside, external, polluting the rest of the world<span class="Italic">(18) (18) </span>porneuw: to practise sexual immorality hamartanw: to sin, transgress, do wrong, miss the mark<span class="Italic">(18) (18) </span>ánthroopos: here Paul is going beyond male and female, and talking about the effects of immorality on any person LITERALLY: Flee from sexual immorality of all kinds. All sin which man may do is outside the body, but the one who practises sexual immorality sins against his own body.<span class="Italic">(18)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="19" />Lu pung badan, sama ke Tuhan pung Roh yang Barisi pung ruma sambayang. Dia pung Roh, yang ada idop di bosong pung hati, te Tuhan Allah sandiri yang kasi Dia pung Roh sang bosong. Andia ko bosong sonde ada pung hak sandiri lai, ko jadi bos kasi bosong satu-satu pung badan sandiri. Ma akurang ko bosong ada idop tingka ke sonde tau ini hal dong?<bt>Your-sg body is like God2's Holy Spirit's house of worship. That Spirit of His, is the one who is living in your-pl livers, cuz (elaboration) God himself is the one who gave His Spirit to you-pl. That is why you do not have the right for just yourselves anymore to be boss over each of your own bodies. But why is it that you are living as if you do not know this matter? [EXEG: NLT]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="ouk oidate: assumes that you really"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">ouk oidate: assumes that you really do know, but you're dodging the issue. naos: temple, shrine, sanctuary<span class="Italic">(19) (19) </span>LITERALLY: Or do you not know that your body is a temple of the Holy Spirit who is in you, which you have from God, and you are not your own?</Message></Annotation><note reference="6:19" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">1 Korintus 3:16, 2 Korintus 6:16</note><v n="20" />Kristus su tabús ame sang bosong pake harga yang mahal. Ais bosong musti idop deng hormat bosong pung badan sandiri, ko kasi tunju bilang, bosong ju hormat sang Tuhan Allah.<bt>Kristus has *redeemed/bought back you at a high cost. So then you must live with respect for your own bodies, to show that you also respect/honour God.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="agoradzoo: to buy, purchase de: indeed,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">agoradzoo: to buy, purchase de: indeed, now, then, therefore<span class="Italic">(20) (20) </span>doksadzoo: praise, honor, magnify, glorify LITERALLY: For you were bought with a price. Therefore glorify God in your bodies.<span class="Italic">(20)</span></Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Ais, bosong musti idop deng kasi"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z">Ais, bosong musti idop deng kasi tunju hormat kasi bosong pung badan sandiri, ko kasi lia sang orang dong, bilang, bosong ju kasi tunju hormat sang Tuhan Allah.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Laki-bini dong<bt>Husbands-wives (doublet)</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <c n="7" />
      <v n="1" />Naa! Sakarang beta mau tulis so'al hal-hal yang bosong tanya dalam bosong pung surat tu bilang, &lt;&lt;Karmana? Ada lebe bae, laki-laki sonde usa kawin, ko?&gt;&gt;<bt>Naa [shift]! Now I want to write about the issues which you asked about in your letter saying, &lt;&lt;How about it? Is it better if a man doesn't marry, or (what)?&gt;&gt;</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="haptw: touch, take hold of, hold,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">haptw: touch, take hold of, hold, cling to; euphemism for sex, or could even be "marry" in this context, like TEV, but taking it as sex in general might be a better bridge from Chapter 6 LITERALLY: But concerning the things you wrote about, good for a man not to touch a woman.<span class="Italic">(1)</span></Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="2" />Bagini: tagal ada banya sampát ko orang bisa jato dalam hubungan seks yang sala, andia ko ada lebe bae satu laki-laki deng dia pung bini sandiri. Bagitu ju, satu parampuan deng dia pung laki sandiri.<bt>It's like this: because there are many oppourtunities where a person can fall (physically, socially, morally, spiritually) in wrong sexual relations, that is why it is better/best if one man has his own wife. In the same way, one woman with her own husband.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="porneia: prostitution, unchastity, fornication, every kind"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">porneia: prostitution, unchastity, fornication, every kind of unlawful sexual intercourse, sexual immorality hekastos: each, every, every single one<span class="Italic">(2) (2) </span>LITERALLY: But because of sexual immorality, let each man have his own wife, and let each woman have her own husband.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="3" />Laki dong! Jang tola lu pung bini pung hak ko tidor bakumpul deng lu. Deng bini dong! Jang tola lu pung laki pung hak ko tidor bakumpul deng lu.<bt>Husbands [vocative]! Do not refuse/reject your-sg wife's right to sleep together with you. And wives [voc]! Don't refuse/reject your-sg husband's right to sleep together with you.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="opheile: obligation, duty, one's due; specifically"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">opheile: obligation, duty, one's due; specifically here, sexual rights. Is this clear? apodidotw: fulfill, give away, pay<span class="Italic">(3) (3) </span>LITERALLY: Let the husband fulfill his duty to his wife, and likewise the wife to the husband.</Message></Annotation><v n="4" />Te bini su kasi dia pung badan ko jadi dia pung laki pung hak milik. Deng laki su kasi dia pung badan ko jadi dia pung bini pung hak milik.<bt>Cuz (elaboration) the wife has given her body to become her husband's ownership rights. And the husband has given his body to become his wife's ownership rights.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="eksousiazw: to have the right or"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">eksousiazw: to have the right or power for something, over someone, be in authority over LITERALLY: The wife does not have the power over her own body, but her husband. And likewise, the husband does not have the power over his own body, but his wife.<span class="Italic">(4)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="5" />Jadi bosong jang maen batola, te bosong dua ada pung hak! Ma kalo bosong mau sambayang to', deng sonde mau pikir hal laen dong, bisa tahan-tahan sadiki ko sonde tidor bakumpul dalam waktu yang pende. Asal laki deng bini ba'omong bae-bae dolo, deng ba'akór bagitu. Deng kalo itu waktu sambayang su abis, lebe bae dong dua capát bakumpul kambali. Kalo sonde bagitu, na, bahaya! Te setan dong pung bos gampang goda orang yang sonde kuat tahan diri.<bt>So (consequently) don't keep refusing (each other), cuz (elaboration) both of you have those rights! But if you-pl are wanting to pray exclusively, and don't want to be thinking about other matters, (you) can restrain/hold back a little to not sleep together for a short time. As long as the husband and wife talk it over carefully/well first, and are in agreement in that way. And when that time of praying is over, it is best for the two of them to get back together quickly. If not, na, that is dangerous! Cuz (elaboration) the boss of the evil spirits can easily tempt people who are not strong in restraining themselves.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="aposterew: steal, rob someone, defraud, deprive"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">aposterew: steal, rob someone, defraud, deprive sumphwnos: harmonious, agreeing, by agreement<span class="Italic">(5) (5) </span>kairon: time, period of time sxolazw: to have time or leisure for, devote self to<span class="Italic">(5) (5) </span>epì tò autò: euphemism for resuming regular sex peirazw: tempt to sin, make trial of, put to the test<span class="Italic">(5) (5) </span>ho Satanaas: da Devil akrasia: lack of self control, self indulgence; can't handle your sex urges<span class="Italic">(5) (5) </span>LITERALLY: Do not deprive each other, unless by agreement for a time, so that you may devote yourselves to prayer, and coming together again, so that Satan may not tempt you because of your lack of self control.</Message></Annotation><v n="6" />Ini hal cuma beta pung usul sa, bukan Tuhan pung atoran.<bt>This matter is just my suggestion, not God2's regulation. [Check what "ini hal" refers to].</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="suggnwme: concession, grant, permission, pardon, indulgence;"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">suggnwme: concession, grant, permission, pardon, indulgence; it sounds like Paul is giving the permission, not God epitage: command, order, injunction<span class="Italic">(6) (6) </span>LITERALLY: But I say this by permission, not by command.</Message></Annotation><v n="7" />Iko beta pung pikir, ada lebe bae orang sonde kawin, sama ke beta. Ma Tuhan Allah kasi tiap orang karunya yang pas deng dia. Ais ada orang yang Dia kasi dong kawin. Deng ada orang laen yang Dia kasi dong sonde kawin.<bt>According to my thinking, it is best if a person doesn't marry, just like me. But God has given each person a *unique.gifting which is fitting for him. So there are people whom He has them marry. And there are other people whom He has them not marry.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="thelw: wish, desire, want houtws: in"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">thelw: wish, desire, want houtws: in this manner, thus, so; not specifically marriage vs. celibacy<span class="Italic">(7) (7) </span>LITERALLY: But I wish all men to be just as I myself. But each one has his own gift from God, one thus, but one thus.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="8" />Beta mau kasi tau laki-laki ko parampuan yang balóm kawin, deng janda dong bilang, ada lebe bae kalo bosong sonde kawin, sama ke beta.<bt>I want to tell/inform the men or women who have not yet married, and the widows that, it is best if you don't marry, just like me.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="agamos: unmarried man or woman. Could"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">agamos: unmarried man or woman. Could be people who never married or who are no longer married. Pairing it up with "widows" could make it refer to men who are widowers or divorced. But "peopo dat not married" keeps the looseness of the Greek without restricting it xera: widow<span class="Italic">(8) (8) </span>mevw: remain, stay LITERALLY: But I say to the unmarried and widows, it is good for them if they remain just as I;<span class="Italic">(8)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="9" />Ma kalo sonde bisa tahan diri, ada lebe bae kawin sa. Lebe bae orang kawin, te kalo sonde, na, dia pung nafsu sandiri bisa makan buang sang dia.<bt>But if (you) are not able to control/restrain yourself, it would be better to just marry. It is better for (that) person to marry, cuz (elaboration) if not, na, his own lust/passion can consume (eat up completely) him/her.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="egkrateuomai: control oneself, abstain, exercise self"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">egkrateuomai: control oneself, abstain, exercise self control gamew: marry<span class="Italic">(9) (9) </span>kreittwn: better, preferable purow: to burn, be inflamed (with sexual desire)<span class="Italic">(9) (9) </span>LITERALLY: But if they cannot control themselves, let them marry, for it is better to marry than to burn.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="10" />Naa, ini bukan dari beta sandiri. Te beta mau kasi tau apa yang kotong pung Bos su parenta sang orang yang su kawin dong bilang, bini sonde bole cere buang dia pung laki.<bt>Naa, this is not from me alone. Cuz (elaboration) I want to make known what our-inc Bos has commanded people who are already married saying, a wife may not divorce her husband.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="parangellw: give orders, command, instruct, direct,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">parangellw: give orders, command, instruct, direct, urge, insist on xwpizw: divide, separate, divorce<span class="Italic">(10) (10) </span>LITERALLY: But to the married I command, but not I but the Lord, let not the wife separate from the husband</Message></Annotation><v n="11" />Ma kalo dia kasi tenga dia pung laki, na, dia jang kawin baru lai. Ada lebe bae, dia bale ko badame deng dia pung laki. Bagitu ju, laki sonde bole cere buang dia pung bini.<bt>But if she abandons her husband, na, she should not remarry again (marry new). It would be best for her to turn back and make relational peace with her husband. In the same way also, a husband may not divorce his wife. [EXEG: CEV undertranslated ‘reconcile’ here.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="cere idop = divorce (spouse still"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z">cere idop = divorce (spouse still alive) vs. cere mati = divorce, then later spouse dies, so can remarry (status sama ke janda)</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="katallassw: be reconciled aphiemi: let go,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">katallassw: be reconciled aphiemi: let go, send away, divorce. SK: "Dass a bad word, 'dump'."<span class="Italic">(11) (11) </span>LITERALLY: --but if she separates, let her remain unmarried or be reconciled to her husband--and let the husband not divorce his wife.</Message></Annotation><note reference="7:10-11" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Mateos 5:32, 19:9, Markus 10:11-12, Lukas 16:18</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="12" />Naa, ini dari beta sandiri, bukan dari kotong pung Bos. Kasi orang laen dong, beta mau omong bagini: kalo ada orang sarani yang dia pung bini sonde parcaya sang Kristus, na, dia jang cere buang dia pung bini, kalo dia pung bini sadia idop tarús deng dia.<bt>Naa, this is from me by myself, not from our Bos. And as for other people, I want to say this: if there is a Christian whose wife does not believe in Kristus, na, he should not divorce his wife, if his wife is prepared to continue living with him.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="loipos: remaining suneudokew: approve of, agree"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">loipos: remaining suneudokew: approve of, agree with, consent to, be willing<span class="Italic">(12) (12) </span>oikew: live, dwell, inhabit LITERALLY: But to the rest I say, not the Lord: if any brother has an unbelieving wife, and she agrees to live with him, let him not divorce her;<span class="Italic">(12)</span></Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Deng kalo orang laen dong, beta"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z">Deng kalo orang laen dong, beta kasi tau bagini (ini beta yang omong, bukan kotong pung Bos): kalo ada sodara orang Kristen yang pung bini sonde parcaya sang Tuhan, itu laki jang usir/cere buang dia pung bini,</Message></Annotation><v n="13" />Bagitu ju, kalo ada bini yang dia pung laki sonde parcaya sang Kristus, na, dia jang cere buang dia pung laki, kalo dia pung laki suka ko dong idop sama-sama tarús.<bt>In the same way also, if there is a wife whose husband doesn't believe in Kristus, na, she should not divorce her husband, if her husband likes for them to continue living together.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: and if any woman has"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: and if any woman has an unbelieving husband, and he agrees to live with her, let her not divorce her husband.</Message></Annotation><v n="14" />Te laki yang sonde parcaya sang Tuhan ju jadi barisi, tagal dia ta'ika deng dia pung bini. Deng bini yang sonde parcaya sang Tuhan ju jadi barisi, tagal dia ta'ika deng dia pung laki. Kalo sonde, na, dong pung ana-ana sonde barisi. Ma deng ini jalan, dong su dapa cap barisi di Tuhan pung muka.<bt>Cuz (elaboration) a husband who doesn't believe in God2 also become clean/pure/holy, because he is bound/linked with his wife. And a wife who doesn't believe in God2 also becomes clean, because she is bound with her husband. If not, na, their children would not be clean/holy. But in this way, they are stamped/declared officially/categorized as (cap) clean before God2.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="hagiazw: make holy, consecrate, sanctify, dedicate,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">hagiazw: make holy, consecrate, sanctify, dedicate, set apart for God epei ara: otherwise, or else, if not<span class="Italic">(14) (14) </span>akathartos: impure, unclean; opposite of heegíastai and hágia hagios: dedicated to God, holy, sacred<span class="Italic">(14) (14) </span>LITERALLY: For the unbelieving husband is consecrated by the wife, and the unbelieving wife is consecrated by the husband; otherwise your children are unclean, but now they are dedicated to God.</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Ma deng ini jalan, dong su"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z">Ma deng ini jalan, dong su tasimpan kasi Tuhan.</Message></Annotation><v n="15" />Ma kalo ada laki ko bini yang sonde parcaya sang Tuhan, yang jalan kasi tenga dia pung pasangan orang parcaya, na, kasi tenga pi sa. Ais laki ko bini yang parcaya dong sonde ta'ika lai bagitu. Te Tuhan ada pange sang bosong ko jadi Dia pung orang, ko bosong bisa idop tanáng deng dame.<bt>But if there is a husband or wife who doesn't believe in God2, who abandons his believing pair/mate, na, just let it be. So/then the husband or wife who believes are no longer bound/linked anymore in that way. Cuz (elaboration) God2 has called you-pl to be His people, so you can live calm (inner peace) and in peace (relational peace).</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="pasangan ="><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z">pasangan =</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="doulow: make a slave, be bound"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">doulow: make a slave, be bound (as a slave), be subject to eirene: peace, harmony<span class="Italic">(15) (15) </span>kalew: call LITERALLY: But if the unbelieving one leaves, let him leave; the brother or the sister has not been bound in such cases; but God has called you/us (TEXT) to peace.<span class="Italic">(15)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="16" />Bini yang parcaya dong! Bosong mungkin bisa kasi salamat sang bosong pung laki. Mungkin sonde. Deng laki yang parcaya dong! Bosong mungkin bisa kasi salamat sang bosong pung bini. Mungkin ju, sonde. Bosong sonde tau parsís.<bt>Wives who believe [vocative]! [NOTE: Gk is singular. KM plural for genre reasons.] It might be that you-pl can save your husbands. It might not. And husbands who believe! It might be that you can save your wives. It also might not. You don't know for sure/precisely.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="ei: may be presenting the positive"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">ei: may be presenting the positive outcome of a "whether", which in Pidgin seems to be best handled in the negative. To load it as "you donno if you goin [save X]" presumes that you won't, so why not split? But if there's a good chance that you will save X, better to stay. soozoo: save, rescue<span class="Italic">(16) (16) </span>LITERALLY: For how do you know, wife, if you will save your husband? Or how do you know, husband, if you will save your wife?</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Bosong tau, ko sonde, kalo bosong"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z">Bosong tau, ko sonde, kalo bosong tu, bisa kasi salamat bosong pung laki? Bisa sa! Bosong sonde tau parsís kalo bosong bisa kasi salamat sang bosong pung laki, ko sonde. Bisa sa! Deng laki dong yang parcaya! Bosong sonde tau parsís kalo bosong bisa kasi salamat sang bosong pung bini, ko sonde. Bisa sa!<span class="Italic">(16)</span></Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Iko bae-bae Tuhan pung Jalan Idop<bt>Follow well God2's Life Way</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="17" />Biar bagitu, ma tiap orang pung dudu-badiri karmana waktu Tuhan Allah pange ame sang bosong jadi Dia pung orang, na, idop tarús bagitu su. Sonde usa oba lai, te Tuhan yang su ator bagitu. Beta ajar ini atoran di samua jama'at.<bt>Even that being the case, nevertheless however each person's situation was when God called you-pl to become His person, na, continue to live that way [+ mild imperative]. There is no need to change it anymore, cuz God2 is the one who arranged it like that. I teach this regulation/instructions in all congregations. [NOTE to daughter translations: vs. 17, 20, 24 should be worded similarly enough that it is clear they are making the same point. Fee characterises it as "change is not to be the rule; rather, one is urged to stay in one's social condition at the time of one's conversion."; NLT]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="ei me: otherwise, except for what"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">ei me: otherwise, except for what I was just talking about hekastos: each, every<span class="Italic">(17) (17) </span>merizw: deal out, assign, apportion peripatew: walk around, go about, conduct oneself<span class="Italic">(17) (17) </span>diatassw: order, direct, command, make a rule LITERALLY: Otherwise each as the Lord assigned him, just as God has called each, thus let him conduct himself; and thus I command in all the churches.<span class="Italic">(17)</span></Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Biar bagitu, ma tiap orang musti"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z">Biar bagitu, ma tiap orang musti kasi jalan tugas iko karunya yang kotong pung Bos su bagi kasi sang dia. Te Tuhan Allah su pange ame kotong jadi Dia pung orang, ko kotong kasi jalan itu tugas. Beta ajar ini atoran di samua jama'at.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="18" />Umpama, kalo bosong parná sunat ko kasi tunju bilang, bosong orang Yahudi, baru dari balakang bosong dengar Tuhan pange sang bosong, na, sonde usa manyangkal itu sunat. Deng orang yang sonde sunat waktu dengar Tuhan pange sang dong jadi Dia pung milik, na, sonde usa sunat ko jadi tanda bilang, dong su jadi Tuhan pung orang.<bt>For example, if you-pl have been circumcised to show/ demonstrate that you are a Yahudi person, and only later you heard God2 calling you, na, (you) don't have to deny/refuse to acknowledge that circumcision. And the person who was not circumcised when (they) heard God2 calling them to become His possession, na, (they) don't need to get circumcised as a sign that they have become God2's people. [EXEG: NLT]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="peritemew: circumcise, cut around epispaomai: conceal"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">peritemew: circumcise, cut around epispaomai: conceal circumcision<span class="Italic">(18) (18) </span>akpobustia: uncircumcised LITERALLY: Was anyone called to circumcision? Let him not conceal it. Has anyone been called to uncircumcision? Let him not be circumcised.<span class="Italic">(18)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="19" />Kalo parná sunat, na, sonde ada pung arti apa-apa. Deng kalo sonde sunat, itu ju sonde ada pung arti apa-apa. Yang ada pung arti, andia: kotong bekin iko Tuhan Allah pung parenta dong.<bt>If (you) have been circumcised, na, that has no meaning. And if (you) have not been circumcised, that also has no meaning. What does have meaning, is: we-inc do according to what God commands.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="teresis: keeping, observance entoln: commandment, order|i(19)"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">teresis: keeping, observance entoln: commandment, order<span class="Italic">(19) (19) </span>LITERALLY: Circumcision is nothing, and uncircumcision is nothing, but the keeping of God's commandments.</Message></Annotation><v n="20" />Waktu Tuhan pili ame sang bosong jadi Dia pung orang, Dia sonde suru bosong sunat ko, sonde sunat. Jadi biar ko bosong tatáp bagitu sa. Sonde parlú oba.<bt>When God2 chose you to become His people, He did not order you to get circumcised or not circumcised. So (consequently), just let you-pl remain constant like that. (You) don't need to change. [EXEG: Different English versions paragraph differently (some after 20, some before 20, and some not at all here). We take vs. 17 as general principle. Vs. 20 reiterates the principle closing out the discussion on circumcision. Vs. 24 reiterates the principle closing out the discussion on slavery. I don't think ES is looking at/addressing this higher level structure. This also meshes nicely with local RL styles of argumentation, whereas literal vague comes across as heavy.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Let each remain in the"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Let each remain in the calling he was in when he was called.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="21" />Beta kasi satu umpama lai. Kalo lu jadi orang pung budak waktu Tuhan pange sang lu, na, biar lu jadi bagitu sa, sonde apa-apa. Ma andekata lu bisa jadi orang bebas, na, jadi bagitu su! Kalo sonde bisa jadi orang bebas ju, sonde apa-apa.<bt>I'll give another example. If you-sg were a person's slave when God2 called you, na, just let you be like that, there is no problem/issue/it's OK. But if perchance you can become a free person, na, then go ahead and do that! If you can't become a free person, that's also OK.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="me soi meletw: never mind, have"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">me soi meletw: never mind, have no care dunamai: can, be able<span class="Italic">(21) (21) </span>eleutheros: free mallon: rather, more<span class="Italic">(21) (21) </span>xraomai: make use of, employ. Can mean either "take the opportunity to get free" or "instead, make good use of your slave status". But the verb is aorist, so it probably doesn't mean to continue your status, but rather to seize the opportunity LITERALLY: Were you called as a slave? Never mind. But if you can be set free, take advantage of it instead.<span class="Italic">(21)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="22" />Te waktu Tuhan pange satu orang budak jadi Dia pung orang, itu budak su jadi ke orang bebas yang karjá kasi dia pung Bos di atas. Deng waktu Tuhan pange satu orang bebas jadi Dia pung orang, itu orang sakarang jadi Kristus pung orang suru-suru.<bt>Cuz (elaboration) when God2 calls a slave to become His person, that slave has already become a free person who works for his Bos above. And when God2 calls a free person to become His person, that person now becomes Kristus' servant.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="apeleutheros: freedman LITERALLY: For the one"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">apeleutheros: freedman LITERALLY: For the one who, being a slave, is called in the Lord, is a freedman of the Lord; likewise the free one who is called is a slave of Christ.<span class="Italic">(22)</span></Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Te orang yang jadi budak waktu"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z">Te orang yang jadi budak waktu Tuhan pange jadi Dia pung orang, dia jadi ke orang bebas yang karjá kasi dia pung Bos di atas. Deng yang jadi orang bebas waktu Tuhan pange jadi Dia pung orang, dia sakarang jadi Kristus pung orang suru-suru.</Message></Annotation><v n="23" />Kristus su bayar putus sang bosong deng harga mahal mati pung! Jadi bosong jang jadi budak kasi orang laen.<bt>Kristus has paid off/paid in full for you-pl with an incredibly high price! So (consequently) you should not become a slave to another/different person.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="time: price, value agorazw: buy, purchase|i(23)"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">time: price, value agorazw: buy, purchase<span class="Italic">(23) (23) </span>LITERALLY: You were bought for a price; do not become a slave of men.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="24" />Sodara sayang dong! Waktu Tuhan Allah pange ame sang bosong jadi Dia pung orang, bosong pung dudu-badiri karmana, na, biar bagitu su. Sonde usa oba lai. Kasi tenga bagitu sa, kasi sang Tuhan.<bt>Dear siblings! When God called you-pl to become His people, whatever your situation was, na, let it just be like that. You don't need to change anymore. Just let it be like that, for God. [NOTE to daughter translations: phrasing similar to vs.17, 20.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: Each one in the situation"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: Each one in the situation he was called, brothers, in this let him remain for God.</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Bosong pung dudu-badiri karmana waktu Tuhan"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z">Bosong pung dudu-badiri karmana waktu Tuhan Allah pange ame sang bosong jadi Dia pung orang, na, biar bagitu su. Sonde usa roba macam-macam. Biar tatáp bagitu sa, kasi sang Tuhan.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">So'al orang yang sonde kawin dong<bt>Regarding people who don't marry</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="25" />Bosong ada tanya sang beta so'al bujang yang sonde parná tidor bacampor dong. Tuhan sonde kasi tau sang beta so'al itu hal. Ma bosong bisa parcaya apa yang beta omong, tagal Tuhan ada kasi tunju Dia pung rasa kasian sang beta. Beta pung pikir bagini:<bt>You-pl are asking me about singles who have never slept together (with someone). God2 has not told me about that matter. But you can trust what I say, because God2 has shown His mercy to me. My thinking is like this:</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="parthenos: virgin (woman), chaste man epitage:"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">parthenos: virgin (woman), chaste man epitage: command, order, injunction<span class="Italic">(25) (25) </span>gnwme: opinion, judgment eleew: have mercy on, pity<span class="Italic">(25) (25) </span>pistos: trustworthy, faithful, dependable, reliable LITERALLY: But concerning the virgins I do not have a command from the Lord, but I give my opinion as one receiving mercy from the Lord to be faithful.<span class="Italic">(25)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="26" />Sakarang kotong dapa sangsara macam-macam. Jadi kalo orang karmana, na, biar bagitu su. Beta pung maksud bagini:<bt>Now we-inc get/experience all sorts of troubles2. So (consequently), however a person is, na, let him/her just be like that. What I mean is this:</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="nomizw: think, believe, consider kalon: pleasant,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">nomizw: think, believe, consider kalon: pleasant, desirable, advantageous<span class="Italic">(26) (26) </span>huparxw: to be, to exist, be present, be available enistemi: impending, imminent[?]; situation right now<span class="Italic">(26) (26) </span>anagke: distress, calamity LITERALLY: Therefore I suppose this is good for the present imminent distress, that it is good for a man to be thus.<span class="Italic">(26)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="27" />Kalo lu ada ta'ika deng lu pung bini, na, jang lapás buang sang dia. Kalo lu sonde ta'ika deng lu pung bini lai, na, sonde usa cari-cari ko kawin deng bini baru.<bt>If you-sg are bound/linked with your wife, na, don't release/get rid of her. If you are not bound with your wife anymore, na, (you) don't need to keep looking to marry a new wife. [EXEG: Gk /luw/ (below in Gk notes) implies this is about remarriage, not just singleness. AGNT, Fee, Ex.Summ. #2.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="dew: bind, tie gunaika: wife|i(27) (27)"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">dew: bind, tie gunaika: wife<span class="Italic">(27) (27) </span>zetew: seek, look for try to obtain, strive for, aim at, desire, wish luw: free, set free, release, unravel (secrets), discharge/release (from contract)<span class="Italic">(27) (27) </span>LITERALLY: Are you bound to a wife? Do not seek to release her. Are you free from a wife? Do not seek a wife.</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Kalo lu ada ta'ika deng lu"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z">Kalo lu ada ta'ika deng lu pung bini, na, jang lapás buang sang dia. Kalo lu sonde ta'ika deng lu pung bini lai, na, sonde usa cari-cari ko kawin deng bini baru.</Message></Annotation><v n="28" />Ma andekata lu jadi kawin, lu sonde bekin sala apa-apa. Deng kalo ada parampuan yang sonde parná tidor bacampor deng laki-laki jadi kawin, dia sonde bekin sala apa-apa ju. Ma inga, te orang yang kawin nanti dapa susa macam-macam di ini dunya. Beta pung maksud ko bosong jang susa bagitu.<bt>But if perchance you happen to marry, you have not done any wrong. And if a woman who has never slept with a man is able to marry, she has not done any wrong. But remember [caution], a person who marries will get/experience all sorts of trouble in this world. My intention is so you-pl don't have those troubles. [NOTE to daughter translations: "troubles" in vs 26 and vs. 28 are different lexemes in the Gk.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="gamew: marry hamartanw: transgress, do wrong,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">gamew: marry hamartanw: transgress, do wrong, sin, offend against religious and moral law of God<span class="Italic">(28) (28) </span>thlipsis: persecution, tribulation, affliction, distress sarks, sarkos: flesh, body, physical, life on earth; Israel Kamakawiwoole's last CD album was N Dis Life.<span class="Italic">(28) (28) </span>exw: to have toioutos: such a kind, such as this<span class="Italic">(28) (28) </span>pheidomai: spare LITERALLY: But if you marry, you do not sin. And if a virgin marries, she does not sin. But such ones will have tribulation in the body, and I am sparing you.<span class="Italic">(28)</span></Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="29" />Sodara sayang dong! Iko beta pung pikir, bagini: waktu su tamba pende, deng hari kiamat su deka-deka. Ais orang yang ada pung bini, jang taro kira sang dia pung bini sa, ma dia ju musti taro kira sang Tuhan.<bt>Dear siblings! According to my thinking, this is how it is: the time is increasingly short, and the end of the world is really close. So for a person who has a wife, he shouldn't just focus on/pay attention to his wife, but he should also focus on God2. [NOTE on vs.29-31: This structure encouraged by Marge Crofts from Baluchi translation in Pakistan, linking to higher level context. See particularly cohesion with vs.32-35]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="phemi: say, affirm kairos: time, point"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">phemi: say, affirm kairos: time, point of time, period of time<span class="Italic">(29) (29) </span>sustellw: draw together, limit, shorten. The end time will come very soon loipon: remaining<span class="Italic">(29) (29) </span>LITERALLY: But I say this, brothers, the remaining time is short, so that the ones who have a wife should be as those who do not have one,</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Ais orang yang ada pung bini,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z">Ais orang yang ada pung bini, ada lebe bae dong karjá hari-hari, sama ke orang yang sonde ada pung bini.</Message></Annotation><v n="30" />Bagitu ju, kalo ada yang manangis, lebe bae dia bakuat ko jang manangis, ko biar dia bisa taro kira sang Tuhan. Kalo ada yang hati babunga, lebe bae dia bekin diri ke sonde bagitu, ko biar dia bisa taro kira sang Tuhan. Kalo ada yang mampu babéli, lebe bae dia idop sama ke orang yang sonde ada pung milik apa-apa, ko biar dia bisa taro kira sang Tuhan.<bt>In the same way also, if there is someone who is crying/mourning, it is best if s/he strengthens himself/pull self together to not cry, so that s/he can focus on God. If there is someone whose liver is flowering (joy), it is best to make himself not like that, so that s/he can focus on God. If there is someone who is able to purchase (consumerism), it is best if s/he live like a person who has no possessions, so that s/he can focus on God.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="babeli = consumerism"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z">babeli = consumerism</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="klaiw: weep, cry xairw: rejoice, be"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">klaiw: weep, cry xairw: rejoice, be glad<span class="Italic">(30) (30) </span>agorazw: buy, purchase katexw: possess<span class="Italic">(30) (30) </span>LITERALLY: and those who cry as not crying, and those who rejoice as not rejoicing, and those who buy as not possessing,</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Bagitu ju, kalo lu ada manangis,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z">Bagitu ju, kalo lu ada manangis, lebe bae bakuat ko jang manangis. Kalo lu hati babunga, lebe bae bekin diri ke sonde bagitu. Kalo lu mampu babeli, lebe bae idop sama ke orang yang sonde ada pung milik apa-apa.</Message></Annotation><v n="31" />Kalo ada yang pake barang dari ini dunya, lebe bae dia bekin diri ke orang yang sonde bagantong di ini dunya pung barang, ko biar dia bisa taro kira sang Tuhan. Tagal ini dunya pung jalan idop nanti ilang buang.<bt>If there is someone who uses things from this world, it is best to make himself like a person who does not depend on this world's things, so that s/he can focus on God. Because this world's way of life will disappear/vanish.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="xpaomai: make use of, employ, make"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">xpaomai: make use of, employ, make the most of, take advantage of kataxraomai: make full use of<span class="Italic">(31) (31) </span>paragw: pass by, pass away sxema: outward appearance, form, shape<span class="Italic">(31) (31) </span>LITERALLY: and those who make use of the world as not making full use of it; for the outward form of this world is passing away.</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Kalo lu pake barang dari ini"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z">Kalo lu pake barang dari ini dunya, bekin diri ke orang yang sonde bagantong di ini dunya pung barang. Tagal ini dunya pung jalan idop nanti ilang buang.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="32" />Beta mau ko bosong jang bapikir-pikir. Te orang yang sonde kawin, dia pung waktu lebe banya ko dia taro kira so'al Tuhan pung mau-mau. Andia ko dia bisa cari jalan ko karjá yang bekin sanáng Tuhan pung hati.<bt>I want for you-pl to not be worrying. Cuz (elaboration) a person who does not marry, his/her time is more, so s/he can focus on/give attention to God2's desires/issues. That is why s/he can look for ways to work which make God2's liver happy.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="thelw: wish, wish to have, desire,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">thelw: wish, wish to have, desire, want amerimnos: free from care<span class="Italic">(32) (32) </span>agamos: unmarried man or woman merimnaw: care for, be concerned about. Legitimate concern, special attention.<span class="Italic">(32) (32) </span>areskw: please, be pleasing. LXX gain someone's approval by giving satisfaction. MM service in the interests of another LITERALLY: But I desire you to be free from care. The unmarried person is concerned about the things of the Lord, how to be pleasing to the Lord;<span class="Italic">(32)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="33-34" />Ma orang yang su kawin ju musti taro kira di ini dunya pung mau-mau. Dia mau taro kira so'al Tuhan pung mau-mau, ma dia ju musti cari jalan ko bekin sanáng dia pung bini. Itu bekin dia pung pikiran jadi tabagi kiri-kanan.<bt>But a person who is already married must also focus on/give attention to the desires/issues of this world. S/he wants to focus on God2's desires/issues, but he must also look for ways to make his wife happy. That is what makes his thinking be divided left-right.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="gamesas: married LITERALLY: But the married"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">gamesas: married LITERALLY: But the married person is concerned about the things of the world, how to be pleasing to his wife.<span class="Italic">(33)</span></Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Ais, dia tahela pi-datang."><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z">Ais, dia tahela pi-datang.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Bagitu ju, parampuan yang sonde ada pung laki lai, deng parampuan yang balóm parná kawin. Dong taro kira so'al Tuhan pung mau-mau, ko dong bisa barisi di hati deng di badan. Ma parampuan yang su kawin, dia pung hati jadi tabagi kiri-kanan. Te dia mau taro kira so'al Tuhan pung mau-mau, ma dia ju musti cari jalan ko bekin sanáng dia pung laki.<bt>It is the same way also, for women who no longer have a husband, and women who have never married. They focus on God2's desires/issues, so they can be clean in liver and in body. But a woman who is married, her liver is divided left-right. Cuz (elaboration) she wants to focus on God2's desires, but she must also look for ways to make her husband happy.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="merizw: divide, separate. Divided interest LITERALLY:"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">merizw: divide, separate. Divided interest LITERALLY: and he is divided. The unmarried woman and the virgin are concerned about the things of the Lord, in order that she may be holy in body and spirit; but the married woman is concerned about the things of the world, how she may be pleasing to her husband.<span class="Italic">(33)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="35" />Beta kasi tau ini hal dong sang bosong, ko bosong dapa dia pung bae. Beta sonde mau ko bosong tahiki. Beta pung suka, bosong bekin yang batúl, deng taro kira di Tuhan pung mau-mau, ko bosong pung pikiran sonde tabagi-bagi.<bt>I am telling these things to you, so you can get the benefit/good. I don't want you to be snared/trapped. My desire is for you to do what is right/true, and focus on God2's desires, so your thinkng is not divided (in different places/directions).</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="sumphoron: beneficial, advantageous, profitable broxon: put"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">sumphoron: beneficial, advantageous, profitable broxon: put or throw a noose on someone (to catch or restrain)<span class="Italic">(35) (35) </span>epibalw: throw over eusxemwn: proper, presentable, good order. Positive image of propriety<span class="Italic">(35) (35) </span>euparedros: constant, sitting beside, attendant, assistant. Wait on someone intently aperispastws: without distraction, with undisturbed mind. Undivided attention, no distraction, not side tracked<span class="Italic">(35) (35) </span>LITERALLY: But I say this for your benefit, not in order to throw a noose around you, but to do right and pay attention to the Lord without distraction.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="36" />Kalo laki-laki ada pung calon bini yang su cukup umur ko dia kawin, na, biar dong kawin sa. Apalai kalo itu laki-laki sonde bisa tahan dia pung diri. Deng bagitu, dong sonde bekin sala apa-apa. Jang sampe dong tunda-tunda tarús, ais dia pung ahir, itu laki-laki bekin hal-hal yang sonde batúl.<bt>If there is a man who has a candidate wife who is old enough to marry, na, just let them marry. Especially if that man is not able to control/restrain himself. They are not doing anything wrong like that. Don't let it get to the point that they keep delaying, and so in the end, that man does things that are not right.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="parthénon: fiancée. Some have taken it"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">parthénon: fiancée. Some have taken it to be a marriageable daughter, but the whole chapter is about husbands and wives. Some have suggested a "spiritual marriage" in which people were soul mates but didn't live together, but there is no evidence for such a custom in Paul's time; that seems to be a later invention, fairly rare. askhemonein: behave disgracefully, dishonorably, indecently. Not fooling around, but holding up the marriage because he thinks it's more spiritual.<span class="Italic">(36) (36) </span>nomizw: think, believe, consider huperakmos: past marriageable age<span class="Italic">(36) (36) </span>opheile: obligation, duty givomai: become, be<span class="Italic">(36) (36) </span>thelw: desire LITERALLY: But if anyone thinks he is not acting properly to his fiancee/virgin, if she is past marriageable age, and thus it ought to be, let him do what he desires; he is not sinning; let them marry.<span class="Italic">(36)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="37" />Ma kalo dia mampu tahan dia pung diri, dia sonde usa paksa kawin capát-capát. Te dia tau dia mau bekin apa. Biar dia batahan lama ju bae.<bt>But if he is able to control/restrain himself, he should not force to marry quickly. Cuz (elaboration) he knows what he wants to do. So even if he endures/lasts/holds out for a long time, that's also good. [EXEG: see NLT, but calon bini in Gk. both verses, so 36: can't control &gt; marry; 37: can control + clear (ministry) vision, so wait. We clearly side on the interpretation that this is about an unmarried man, not about a girls' father. Revolves around interpretations of “not having obligation”, and “he will do well”; Follows HCE; influenced by NRSV &amp; NJB choice of ‘fiancé’; and Tagbanwa BT “not now” (a very Austronesian aspect/mood); “not marry” is taken as “not now, but later”, not “not at all; break off the contract”; this seems to me to resonate better with 33-36.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="histemi: stand hedraios: firm, steadfast|i(37) (37)"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">histemi: stand hedraios: firm, steadfast<span class="Italic">(37) (37) </span>anagken: necessity, compulsion LITERALLY: But the one who stands firm in his heart, not having compulsion, but has power over his own desires, and that one decides in his own heart to keep his own fiancee, he does well;<span class="Italic">(37)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="38" />Jadi laki-laki yang kawin deng dia pung calon bini, itu bae. Deng yang sonde kawin tu, lebe bae lai.<bt>So (consequently), a man who marries his candidate wife, that is good. And those who don't marry, that is even better.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: so that the one who"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: so that the one who marries his own fiancee does well, and the one who does not marry does better.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">So'al mama janda dong<bt>Regarding widow ladies</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="39" />Bini ta'ika sampe mati deng dia pung laki. Ma kalo dia pung laki su mati, na, dia bole kawin baru, asal dia pung laki baru tu, orang yang parcaya sang Kristus ju.<bt>A wife is bound until death to her husband. But if her husband has died, na, she can remarry, as long as her new husband, is also a person who believes in God2.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="hoson: as long koimaw: sleep, fall"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">hoson: as long koimaw: sleep, fall asleep, die<span class="Italic">(39) (39) </span>LITERALLY: A woman is bound as long time as her husband lives; but if the husband dies, she is free to marry whomever she wishes, only in the Lord.</Message></Annotation><v n="40" />Iko beta pung pikir, itu janda jadi lebe ontong kalo dia sonde kawin lai. Beta pikir ini nasiat dari Tuhan pung Roh yang ada di beta.<bt>Following my thinking, that widow is more fortunate/in a better state of affairs if she doesn't marry anymore. I think this advice is from God2's Spirit which is in me.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="makarios: fortunate, happy givwmen: opinion, judgment|i(40)"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">makarios: fortunate, happy givwmen: opinion, judgment<span class="Italic">(40) (40) </span>dokew: think, consider LITERALLY: But she is more fortunate if she remains thus, according to my opinion, and I think I also have the Spirit of God.<span class="Italic">(40)</span></Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">So'al makanan yang orang su pake songgo<bt>Regarding food which people have used in traditional worship</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Carita Ulang so'al Jalan Idop 4:35,39; 6:4)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <c n="8" />
      <v n="1" />Sakarang beta mau omong so'al daging yang orang pake songgo. Kotong samua su tau banya, so'al ini hal dong. Dia pung masala, kalo orang tau banya, dia bisa sombong, te dia pikir dia lebe pintar dari orang laen dong. Lebe bae, kotong basayang deng orang laen sa. Te itu yang bekin samua orang jadi kuat ko bisa batahan lama.<bt>Now I want to talk about meat which people have used in traditional worship. We-inc all already know much about these matters. The problem is, if a person knows alot, s/he can be arrogant, cuz (elaboration) s/he thinks s/he is more clever than other people. It is best for us to just mutually love other people. Cuz (elaboration) that is what make everyone be strong so they are able to persevere/endure for long.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="eidoolothýtoon: sacrificed to an idol --"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">eidoolothýtoon: sacrificed to an idol -- a negative word for Jews and Christians. An animal was killed as part of the ceremony. It does not include offerings from plants such as grain, oil, or wine eidoolothytos: meat offered to an idol<span class="Italic">(1) (1) </span>oida: know gvwsis: knowledge, key to knowledge, embodiment of knowledge<span class="Italic">(1) (1) </span>phusiow: blow up, puff up, make proud, arrogant agape: love, aloha<span class="Italic">(1) (1) </span>oikodomew: build, build up, edify, strengthen, establish, benefit LITERALLY: But concerning the meat offered to idols, we know that we all have knowledge [exegesis: about idols / in general]. Knowledge puffs up, but love builds up.<span class="Italic">(1)</span></Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="2" />Kalo ada orang yang anggap diri su tau, itu kasi tunju bilang, dia pung mangarti balóm langkáp.<bt>If there is a person who considers themself to already know, that shows that his understanding is not yet complete.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="egnookénai: he has attained knowledge already"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">egnookénai: he has attained knowledge already dokew: think, suppose, consider<span class="Italic">(2) (2) </span>givwskw: know, come to know oupw: not yet<span class="Italic">(2) (2) </span>kathws: just as, as dei: it is necessary, must<span class="Italic">(2) (2) </span>LITERALLY: If someone thinks he knows something, he does not know yet as he ought to know;</Message></Annotation><v n="3" />Ma kalo ada orang yang sayang sang Tuhan Allah, Tuhan su kanál sang dia. Itu yang pantíng.<bt>But if there is a person who loves God, God2 already knows him. That is what is important.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="agapaw: love, cherish ginwskw: know, acknowledge|i(3)"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">agapaw: love, cherish ginwskw: know, acknowledge<span class="Italic">(3) (3) </span>houtos: this, this one LITERALLY: but if anyone loves God, this one is known by him.<span class="Italic">(3)</span></Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="4" />Jadi, kalo orang makan daging yang parná pake songgo, kotong samua tau bilang, barang songgo dalam ini dunya, bukan Allah yang batúl. Te kotong tau bilang, &lt;&lt;Cuma ada satu Tuhan Allah yang batúl.&gt;&gt; deng, &lt;&lt;samua barang songgo yang orang sémba sonde ada pung arti apa-apa.&gt;&gt;<bt>So (consequently), if a person eats meat which has been used in traditional worship, we-inc all know that, trad.worship things in this world, are not the true Allah. Cuz (elaboration) we-inc know that, &lt;&lt;There is only one true God (TA).&gt;&gt; and, &lt;&lt;all trad.worship things that people worship have no meaning at all.&gt;&gt; [EXEG: first bit could be from Deut. but not second bit. So not “It is written”, but literal “we know that”. CR, Amarasi 2014]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="brwsis: eating oídamen: we know, used"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">brwsis: eating oídamen: we know, used here as in verse 1 to introduce a statement of something the Corinthians take for granted but isn't quite true<span class="Italic">(4) (4) </span>eidwlon: idol, image, false god kosmos: world<span class="Italic">(4) (4) </span>oudeis: none, no one, nobody, nothing LITERALLY: Therefore concerning the eating of [meat / food] offered to idols we know that an idol is nothing in the world, and that [there is] no God except one.<span class="Italic">(4)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="5" />Ada banya barang di langit deng di bumi yang orang subu bilang, &lt;tuhan&gt; ko &lt;bos&gt;.<bt>There are many things in the sky and on earth which people refer to as &lt;lord2/god2&gt; or &lt;boss&gt;.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="eiper: if indeed, if after all,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">eiper: if indeed, if after all, since legw: say, tell, call<span class="Italic">(5) (5) </span>eite: whether...or hwsper: just as, as<span class="Italic">(5) (5) </span>polus: many LITERALLY: For even if indeed [there are those] called gods, whether in heaven or on earth, just as [there are] many gods and many lords,<span class="Italic">(5)</span></Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">
      <v n="6" />Ma kasi kotong, Tuhan Allah cuma satu sa.<bt>But for us-inc, there is only one God (TA).</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Dia tu, kotong pung Bapa.<bt>He is our Father.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Samua-samua ba'akar di Dia.<bt>Everything is rooted/sourced in Him.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Kotong bekin samua kasi sang Dia.<bt>We do everything for Him.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Deng kotong pung Bos yang hak parenta sang kotong, cuma satu sa.<bt>And our Bos who has the say-so/ordering rights over us-inc, is only one.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Andia, Yesus Kristus.<bt>That is, Yesus Kristus.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Tuhan Allah pake sang Yesus,<bt>God used Yesus,</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Waktu Tuhan Allah bekin samua-samua,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z">Waktu Tuhan Allah bekin samua-samua,</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">waktu Dia bekin samua-samua.<bt>when He made everything. [EXEG: CEV, HCE, Ex. Summ. "It means that Jesus is the agent of creation [Ho, TNTC, TG]. God created all things by means of Jesus Christ [NIC2, TG]."; Fee "Jesus is the one through whom God both created and redeemed."]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Marge objects to the OV of"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z">Marge objects to the OV of these two lines, even though the KM speakers and translators see them as equivalent.</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Yesus tu, yang karjá."><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z">Yesus tu, yang karjá.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Deng kotong ada idop,<bt>And we are living,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">tagal Yesus yang kasi kotong idop.<bt>because Yesus is the one who gave us life.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="LITERALLY: but to us [there is]"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">LITERALLY: but to us [there is] one God the father, from whom [are] all things and we for him, and one Lord Jesus Christ, through whom [are] all things and we through him.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="7" />Ma ada orang yang sonde tau itu hal dong. Dong masi pikir tarús so'al barang songgo dong, sama ke dong parná pikir dolu. Andia ko, tiap kali dong makan daging yang orang parná pake songgo, dong ada pikir bilang, &lt;&lt;Ini makanan su jadi korban ko pake songgo! Kalo beta makan ini barang, beta masi ta'ika deng hal jahat dong!&gt;&gt; Jadi itu bekin rusak dong pung pikiran, sampe dong sonde bisa pikir lurus lai, tagal dong pung hati sonde kuat.<bt>[EXEG: HCE] But there are people who don't know those things. They still keep thinking about those trad.worship things, just like before. That is why, each time they eat meat which people have used for trad.worship, they are thinking, &lt;&lt;This food has been a sacrifice to use for traditional worship! If I eat this stuff, I am still bound/linked with those evil things!&gt;&gt; So (consequently), it ruins/destroys/damages their thinking, to the point that they cannot think straight anymore, because their livers are not strong.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="taro hati = concentrate (on abstract"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z">taro hati = concentrate (on abstract things) ; taro mata = perhatikan, pay attention to (physical things)</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="suvetheia: habit, custom, being accustomed hews:"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">suvetheia: habit, custom, being accustomed hews: until<span class="Italic">(7) (7) </span>arti: now esthiw: eat<span class="Italic">(7) (7) </span>suneidesis: consciousness, awareness, conscience, scrupples asthenes: weak, powerless, morally weak<span class="Italic">(7) (7) </span>molunw: defile, stain, make impure LITERALLY: But the knowledge is not in all; but some by habit of idols until now, eat as meat offered to idols, and their weak conscience is defiled.<span class="Italic">(7)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="8" />Dia pung pasal apa? Makanan sonde bisa bawa kotong pi mangada sang Tuhan Allah, to? Kalo sonde makan, kotong sonde tamba jahat. Deng kalo makan, sonde bekin kotong jadi orang bae, to?<bt>What's the basis of that (lit: what chapter is that)? Food cannot bring us to front up to God, right? If (we) don't eat it, we don't become more evil. And if we eat it, it doesn't make us become good people, right?</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="brwma: food, solid food paristemi: bring"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">brwma: food, solid food paristemi: bring before (for judgement or for closeness); have a better relationship<span class="Italic">(8) (8) </span>phagein (esthiw): eat husterew: be excluded, fail to reach, go without, come short of, lack<span class="Italic">(8) (8) </span>perisseuow: excel, abound LITERALLY: But food will not bring us before God; if we do not eat we are not excluded, if we eat, we do not excel.<span class="Italic">(8)</span></Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="9" />Ma ati-ati, ó! Biar lu ada pung hak ko bekin satu hal, balóm tantu itu hal jadi bae kasi sang lu. Andekata ada satu sodara orang parcaya yang hati sonde kuat, kalo dia dapa lia lu ada bekin itu hal, ais dia ta'antok, na, itu sonde bae!<bt>But be careful, ó! Even if you-sg have the right to do something, it is not yet sure that that matter is good for you. If perchance [+hypothetical] there is a believing sibling whose liver isn't strong, if he happens to see you are doing that matter, and so he stumbles, na, that is not good!</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="blepw: see, look me pws: lest"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">blepw: see, look me pws: lest somehow<span class="Italic">(9) (9) </span>eksousia: power, right, liberty proskomma: stumbling, offense<span class="Italic">(9) (9) </span>LITERALLY: But look, lest somehow your [right / liberty] does not become a stumbling to the weak.</Message></Annotation><v n="10" />Lu sandiri su tau itu hal sonde jadi apa-apa. Ma kalo sodara orang parcaya yang hati sonde kuat, dapa lia lu ada dudu makan di ruma songgo, nanti dia pikir apa? Tantu dia pikir makan barang songgo ju sonde jadi masala kasi sang dia lai, biar dong pake songgo.<bt>You yourself already know that matter has no significance. But if the believing sibling whose liver is not strong, happens to see you are sitting eating in a house of trad.worship, what is s/he going to think? Surely s/he will think that eating thangs of trad.worship are also no longer a problem for him/her, even if they have been used in trad.worship.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="exw: have gnwsis: knowledge|i(10) (10) |reidwleion:"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">exw: have gnwsis: knowledge<span class="Italic">(10) (10) </span>eidwleion: idol's temple katakeimai: recline (to eat)<span class="Italic">(10) (10) </span>suneidesis: consciousness, awarenesss, conscience, scruples asthenes: weak, powerless, morally weak<span class="Italic">(10) (10) </span>oikodomew: build, strengthen eidwlothutos: meat offered to an idol<span class="Italic">(10) (10) </span>esthiw: eat LITERALLY: For if someone sees you, having knowledge, reclining (to eat) in an idol's temple, won't the weak one's conscience be strengthened to eat meat offered to idols?<span class="Italic">(10)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="11" />Lu su mangarti banya hal. Ma kalo lu bekin bagitu, lu bekin rusak orang yang hati sonde kuat. Deng itu orang tu, lu pung sodara orang parcaya. Kristus ju mati kasi sang dia na!<bt>You-sg already understand many things. But if you do that, you ruin/damage/destroy the person whose liver is not strong. And that person, is your believing sibling. Kristus also died for him/her [+speaker attitude particle, obviously--also sense of I've knocked down your arguments/objections]!</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="apollumi: perish, die, be lost (spiritually),"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">apollumi: perish, die, be lost (spiritually), be destroyed apothneskw: die<span class="Italic">(11) (11) </span>LITERALLY: For the weak one is destroyed by your knowledge, the brother for whom Christ died.</Message></Annotation><v n="12" />Lebe bae pikir bagini: kalo lu bekin lu pung sodara yang hati sonde kuat dong bekin satu hal yang dong anggap sala, lu su bekin sala kasi sang dong. Deng lu ju bekin sala kasi sang Kristus.<bt>So it's best to think like this: if you-sg make your sibling whose liver isn't strong do something that they consider wrong, you have done wrong to them. And you have also done wrong to Kristus.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="hamartanw: sin, transgress, do wrong tuptw:"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">hamartanw: sin, transgress, do wrong tuptw: strike, beat, hit<span class="Italic">(12) (12) </span>LITERALLY: But thus as you sin against the brothers and strike their weak conscience, you are sinning against Christ.</Message></Annotation><v n="13" />Jadi, kalo beta makan barang yang bekin beta pung sodara orang parcaya jato dalam sala, lebe bae beta sonde usa makan daging macam bagitu. Biar sampe salamanya ju sonde usa sa. Te beta sonde mau ko dong jato dalam sala.<bt>So (consequently), if I eat something which makes my believing sibling fall into wrong, it is best that I not eat meat like that. Even if it's forever, (I) just don't need to. Cuz (elaboration) I don't want for them to fall into wrong. [EXEG: the ‘forever’ bit is hyperbole. ALT: sampe beta mati.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="dioper: therefore skandalizw: cause to fall,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">dioper: therefore skandalizw: cause to fall, cause to stumble, cause to sin<span class="Italic">(13) (13) </span>kreas: meat LITERALLY: Therefore if food causes my brother to stumble, I will not eat meat for eternity, so that my brother may not stumble.<span class="Italic">(13)</span></Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Waktu Tuhan utus Dia pung orang dong, Dia ju kasi dong hak deng kuasa<bt>When God2 commissions His people, He also gives them rights and power/authority</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <c n="9" />
      <v n="1" />Jang pikir kata, beta sonde ada pung hak ko tulis bagini kasi bosong. Te Tuhan Allah utus sang beta pi jalan kasi tau orang so'al Dia. Beta ju parná lia sang Yesus, kotong pung Bos. Beta ta'ika tarús deng Dia, ais bosong samua ju parcaya sang Dia, tagal beta pung karjá.<bt>[EXEG: Message; MC, HCE, pos-neg] Don't think that I have no right to write this way to you-pl. Cuz (elaboration) God commissioned me to go tell people about Him. I have also seen Yesus, our-inc Bos. I am bound/linked with Him continually, so you all also believe in Him, because of my work. [EXEG: This verse sets off a defense (vs.1-27) against people who try to undermine Paul's claim to apostleship. At a low level “Have I not seen Jesus our Lord?” could be taken as a one-off event in the past, with no connection to the following “Are you not my work in the Lord?” At a high level, a point that runs through the whole section is Paul's continuing fathfulness and endurance, and how that impacted the Corinthians. This is hinted at by NLT “Isn't it because of my hard work that you are in the Lord?”, by CEV “and have led you to have faith in him”, and made explicit by HCE “I stay tight wit da Bos, an all you guys...”]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="*** (2009) note added; last two"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z">*** (2009) note added; last two sentences combined to strengthen the link</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="eleútheros: free to eat and drink"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">eleútheros: free to eat and drink what I like, as in Verse 4? free from the need to work for a living? From Verse 4 on Paul is talking about that, so this is more likely than a meaning tied to what he has finished talking about NRSV: Am I not free? Am I not an apostle? Have I not seen Jesus our Lord? Are you not my work in the Lord?<span class="Italic">(1)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="2" />Biar orang laen dong sonde tarima beta jadi Tuhan pung utusan, ma tantu bosong su tau bilang, Tuhan ada utus sang beta ko kasi tau Dia pung pasán sang bosong. Kalo bosong mau cari lai dia pung bukti, na, lia bosong pung dudu-badiri sa. Te bosong masi ta'ika deng kotong pung Bos!<bt>Even if other people don't accept me as God'2s apostle, nevertheless you-pl surely know that God2 has commissioned me to tell/make known His message to you. If you want to look for further proof, na, just look at your own situation. Cuz (elaboration) you are still bound with our Bos!</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="en kyríooi: my relationship with the"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">en kyríooi: my relationship with the Lord, or you relationship with the Lord -- the Greek can be read either way NRSV: If I am not an apostle to others, at least I am to you; for you are the seal of my apostleship in the Lord.<span class="Italic">(2)</span></Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="3" />Beta mau manyao bale kasi orang yang suka lempar sala sang beta bagini:<bt>I want to respond back to the people who like to accuse me of wrong, in this way:</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="anakrínousin: criticize, examine NRSV: This is"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">anakrínousin: criticize, examine NRSV: This is my defense to those who would examine me.<span class="Italic">(3)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="4" />Bosong ada pikir beta deng Barnabas sonde ada pung hak ko tarima makan-minum dari orang yang botong ajar, ko?<bt>Are you-pl thinking that I and Barnabas have no right to accept food-drink from the people we-exc teach, or (what)? [EXEG: see vs. 6]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="exousían: authority, a right. Looking back,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">exousían: authority, a right. Looking back, it would be the right mentioned in Chapter 8 to be free of dietary restrictions. But looking forward, as the chapter seems to, it would be the right to have food and drink given to them as compensation for their work NRSV: Do we not have the right to our food and drink?<span class="Italic">(4)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="5" />Bosong ada pikir bilang, botong sonde ada pung hak ko kawin deng parampuan Kristen, yang bisa iko sama-sama ko layani di tampa laen, ko? Padahal Tuhan pung utusan laen dong ada bawa dong pung bini. Tuhan pung adi dong ju bagitu. Petrus sandiri ju bekin bagitu!<bt>Are you thinking that we don't have the right to marry a Christian woman, who can accompany us to serve/minister in other places, or (what)? Whereas in fact, God2's other apostles are taking their wives. The Lord's younger siblings also (do) that. Petrus himself is also doing that!</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="NRSV: Do we not have the"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">NRSV: Do we not have the right to be accompanied by a believing wife, as do the other apostles and the brothers of the Lord and Cephas?</Message></Annotation><note reference="9:5" class="Note General Paragraph" usfm="f">Alkitab bahasa Yunani tulis bilang, &lt;Kefas&gt;. Kefas tu, Petrus pung nama laen.<bt>The Yunani language Bible writes saying, &lt;Kefas&gt;. That Kefas, is Petrus' other name.</bt></note><v n="6" />Ko, bosong pikir cuma beta deng Barnabas sandiri sa yang musti karjá cari doi, ko biar botong bisa idop ko ajar orang?<bt>Or, do you think that only I and Barnabas alone must work for money, so we can live to teach people? [EXEG: NLT, CEV]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="*** (2009) revised to get double"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z">*** (2009) revised to get double neg = pos, note added</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="NRSV: Or is it only Barnabas"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">NRSV: Or is it only Barnabas and I who have no right to refrain from working for a living?</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Ko, bosong pikir cuma beta deng"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z">Ko, bosong pikir cuma beta deng Barnabas sandiri sa yang sonde ada pung hak karjá cari doi, ko botong bisa idop ko ajar orang?</Message></Annotation><v n="7" />Bosong pung pikiran tu, dia pung dasar apa? Lia sa tantara dong. Dong sonde usa béli dong pung makanan deng pakean. Lia sa orang yang karjá di kabón anggor. Sonde ada yang larang sang dia bilang, &lt;&lt;Lu sonde bole makan itu bua anggor dong!&gt;&gt; Lia sa gambala dong. Dia ada pung hak ko ame susu dari domba yang dia jaga.<bt>What is the basis for your thinking? Have a look at soldiers. They don't have to buy their food and clothes. Have a look at a person who works in a grape orchard. There is nobody who forbids him saying, &lt;&lt;You-sg are not allowed to eat those grapes!&gt;&gt; Have a look at herders. He has the right to take milk from the sheep he is guarding/watching. [EXEG: focus on workers--if labourers in secular occupations are paid, why not apostles?]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="NRSV: Who at any time pays"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">NRSV: Who at any time pays the expenses for doing military service? Who plants a vineyard and does not eat any of its fruit? Or who tends a flock and does not get any of its milk?</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="8" />Beta sonde omong bagitu iko beta, manusia biasa, pung pikiran sandiri. Te Tuhan Allah pung Atoran dong ju kasi tau hal yang sama.<bt>I am not talking like that according to me, as a normal human's own thinking. Cuz (elaboration) God's Laws also tell about the same matter.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="katà ánthroopon: from a human standpoint,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">katà ánthroopon: from a human standpoint, examples from human experience (not from a special revelation by God), in the everyday way NRSV: Do I say this on human authority? Does not the law also say the same?<span class="Italic">(8)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="9" />Dalam ba'i Musa pung Atoran ada tatulis bilang, &lt;&lt;Waktu sapi ada inja padi ko kasi tapisa buler dari tangke, jang ika mati dia pung mulu ko dia sonde bisa dapa makan.&gt;&gt; Bosong pikir Tuhan mau kasi biar ko cuma sapi sa yang bisa makan, ko?<bt>In Gf Musa's Regulations/Law it is written saying, &lt;&lt;When a cow is stepping on grain to separate the grainheads from the stalks, don't tie closed its mouth so that it cannot eat.&gt;&gt; Do you think that God2 wants to allow it so that only the cows are the ones who can eat, or (what?) [ALT: some RLs can't do the double negative, so ALT: jang ika mati dia pung mulu ko iar dia bisa makan sa.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="padi here = generic for grain"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z">padi here = generic for grain</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="NRSV: For it is written in"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">NRSV: For it is written in the law of Moses, “You shall not muzzle an ox while it is treading out the grain.” Is it for oxen that God is concerned?</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Dalam Tulisan Barisi ada Atoran yang"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z">Dalam Tulisan Barisi ada Atoran yang Tuhan Allah suru ba'i Musa tulis, bilang, [dictation?]</Message></Annotation><note reference="9:9" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Carita Ulang so'al Jalan Idop 25:4, 1 Timotius 5:18</note><v n="10-11" />Sonde! Dia ju ada omong ko taro mata sang botong! Te ada tatulis ju bilang, &lt;&lt;Orang yang bale tana, deng orang yang kasi pisa buler dari tangke, waktu dong ada karjá, dong ju tau bilang, nanti dong dapa dong pung bagian.&gt;&gt; Bagitu ju, ada bae kalo utusan orang Kristen dong bisa tarima dong pung bagian dari dong pung hasil karjá. Te waktu botong ada ajar sang bosong hal-hal dari Tuhan pung Roh, itu sama deng satu orang tani yang batanam. Jadi waktu botong ajar abis, na, itu sonde apa-apa kalo botong tarima makan-minum ko apa-apa ju dari bosong. Te itu memang pantas!<bt>[EXEG: see NLT] No! He is also talking to watch over/attend to us-exc! Cuz (elaboration) it is also written saying, &lt;&lt;The person who turns the soil, and the person who separates the grainhead from the stalk, when they are working, they also know that they will get their share.&gt;&gt; In the same way, it is good if Christian apostles/emissaries can receive their portion from the results/produce of their work. Cuz (elaboration) when we are teaching you-pl things from God2's Spirit, that is the same as a farmer who is planting. So (consequently), when we have finished teaching, na, there is no problem/it is OK if we receive food-drink or other things from you-pl. Cuz that is what is appropriate!</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="metéchein: to get a share of"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">metéchein: to get a share of the crop that will be coming méga: big deal, too much to expect, "is it unfair if we harvest material things?"<span class="Italic">(10) (10) </span>NRSV: Or does he not speak entirely for our sake? It was indeed written for our sake, for whoever plows should plow in hope and whoever threshes should thresh in hope of a share in the crop. NRSV: If we have sown spiritual good among you, is it too much if we reap your material benefits?<span class="Italic">(10)</span></Message></Annotation><note reference="9:11" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Roma 15:27</note><v n="12" />Orang laen yang ajar sang bosong ada pung hak ko tarima makanan deng barang laen dari bosong, to? Ais kalo botong, karmana? Botong pung hak lebe dari dong!<bt>Other people who teach you have the right to receive food and other things from you, right? So than, as for us-exc, how is it? We have more rights than they!</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="NRSV: If others share this rightful"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">NRSV: If others share this rightful claim on you, do not we still more?</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Ma bosong su tau. Botong sonde parná pake botong pung hak ko tuntut bagitu. Botong batahan dalam hal macam-macam, ko jang bekin halangan kasi sang bosong. Te deng bagitu, bosong suka dengar Kristus pung Kabar Bae yang botong carita kasi sang bosong.<bt>But you already know. We-exc have never used our right to claim it like that. We have endured all sorts of things (negative implications), so (we) would not make any barriers/hindrances for you. Cuz (elaboration) in that way, you liked to listen to Kristus' Good News which we told to you.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="NRSV: Nevertheless, we have not made"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">NRSV: Nevertheless, we have not made use of this right, but we endure anything rather than put an obstacle in the way of the gospel of Christ.</Message></Annotation><v n="13" />Pikir coba! Kapala agama dong yang layani di orang Yahudi pung Ruma Sambayang Pusat, dong idop dari persembahan yang orang bawa. Deng orang yang layani di meja korban, dong bisa makan daging dari binatang yang orang bawa.<bt>Have a think! The *priests who serve in the Yahudi people's *Temple (Central House of Worship), they live from the *offerings which people bring. And people who serve at the *altar (sacrifice table), they can eat the meat from the animals which people bring.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="NRSV: Do you not know that"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">NRSV: Do you not know that those who are employed in the temple service get their food from the temple, and those who serve at the altar share in what is sacrificed on the altar?</Message></Annotation><note reference="9:13" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Carita Ulang so'al Jalan Idop 18:1</note><v n="14" />Bagitu ju, Tuhan ada pasán bilang, orang yang pung tugas kasi tau Kristus pung Kabar Bae, dong bisa idop dari dong pung hasil karjá. Itu yang batúl.<bt>In the same way also, God2's has instructed that people whose work/responsibility it is to tell/make known Kristus' Good News, they can live from the produce/results of their work. That is what is right.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="zéen: make a living NRSV: In"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">zéen: make a living NRSV: In the same way, the Lord commanded that those who proclaim the gospel should get their living by the gospel.<span class="Italic">(14)</span></Message></Annotation><note reference="9:14" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Mateos 10:10, Lukas 10:7</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="15" />Biar beta ada pung hak ko idop bagitu, ma beta sonde suka bekin bagitu. Beta sonde tulis ini surat deng maksud ko bosong mulai kasi beta barang. Su lama beta layani sang bosong deng sonde minta apa-apa dari bosong. Jadi lebe bae beta mati, ko biar orang jang pikir beta mulai minta-minta.<bt>Even though I have the right to live like that, nevertheless I don't like to do that. I did not write this letter with the intention that you-pl begin giving me things. For a long time now I have served you without asking for anything from you. So (consequently), it would be better for me to die, than for people to think that I have begun to beg. [EXEG: ‘Boast’ is implicit here, explicit in vs.16. We've gone to the grounds of boasting (Fee, Ex. Summ. NLT, HCE) My feeling is putting boast in explicitly would make very heavy info load and skew the focus off the point he is trying to make here.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="NRSV: But I have made no"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">NRSV: But I have made no use of any of these rights, nor am I writing this so that they may be applied in my case. Indeed, I would rather die than that-no one will deprive me of my ground for boasting!</Message></Annotation><v n="16" />Biar beta kasi tau orang tarús so'al Tuhan pung Kabar Bae, ma itu sonde jadi dasar ko beta bisa omong bésar. Beta musti kasi tau orang so'al Tuhan, te Tuhan yang utus sang beta bagitu. Kalo beta sonde bekin iko beta pung tugas bagitu, na, beta paya tu! Te pasti hukuman jato kaná sang beta.<bt>Even if I continue to tell people about God2's Good News, nevertheless that is not a basis/reason/excuse for me to be able to talk big. I must tell people about God2, cuz (elaboration) God2 is the one who commissioned me to do that. If I don't do according to my work/responsibilities like that, na, I am in real strife/danger! Cuz (elaboration) surely punishment will fall on me. [CHECK: Does speaker attitude come through?]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="ouaì: how terrible -- thinking of"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">ouaì: how terrible -- thinking of future judgment if he messes up. An interjection expressing sorrow NRSV: If I proclaim the gospel, this gives me no ground for boasting, for an obligation is laid on me, and woe to me if I do not proclaim the gospel!<span class="Italic">(16)</span></Message><Message author="Chuck Grimes" created="2015-01-17 01:08:55Z">k</Message></Annotation><v n="17" />Kalo beta bekin ini karjá cuma tagal beta pung suka sandiri, na, barang yang beta dapa tu, sama ke gaji yang orang karjá dong tarima sa. Ma kalo beta bekin ini karjá tagal Tuhan utus sang beta, itu laen. Te Dia ada parcaya sang beta ko jaga Dia pung barang mahal dong.<bt>If I do this work only because of my own liking, na, whatever things I get, are merely like wages which workers receive. But if I do this work because God2 has commissioned me, that is different. Cuz (elaboration) He is trusting me to guard/watch over His valuable things.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="misthos: compensation for work NRSV: For"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">misthos: compensation for work NRSV: For if I do this of my own will, I have a reward; but if not of my own will, I am entrusted with a commission.<span class="Italic">(17)</span></Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Kalo beta bekin ini karjá cuma"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z">Kalo beta bekin ini karjá cuma tagal itu beta pung suka sandiri, na, barang yang beta dapa tu, sama ke orang karjá pung gaji. Ma kalo beta bekin ini karjá tagal Tuhan utus sang beta, itu sama ke Dia parcaya sang beta ko jaga Dia pung barang mahal.</Message></Annotation><v n="18" />Jadi kalo bagitu, beta pung upa apa? Beta sonde parlú tarima gaji! Beta kasi tau Tuhan pung Kabar Bae deng sonde minta apa-apa. Itu yang bekin beta rasa puas. Deng itu rasa puas tu, sama ke beta pung upa. Jadi biar beta ada pung hak macam-macam ke orang yang pung tugas kasi tau itu Kabar Bae, ma beta sandiri sonde mau pake beta pung hak samua.<bt>So (consequently), if that is the case, what is my reward? I don't need to receive wages! I tell God2's Good News an don't ask for anything. That is what makes me feel satisfied. And that feeling of satisfaction, is like my reward. So (consequently), even though I have various rights as a person who has the job/responsibilities to tell that Good News, nevertheless I myself do not want to use all those rights.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="What was his pay? Not clear."><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">What was his pay? Not clear. NRSV: What then is my reward? Just this: that in my proclamation I may make the gospel free of charge, so as not to make full use of my rights in the gospel.<span class="Italic">(18)</span></Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="19" />Beta ni, orang bebas yang karjá iko beta pung suka. Orang sonde ada pung hak ko suru beta karjá ini, ko, karjá itu. Biar bagitu, ma beta bekin diri sama ke budak, ko samua orang ada hak ko suru-suru sang beta. Deng bagitu, beta bisa tolong lebe banya orang ko dong batahan iko sang Tuhan Allah.<bt>I here, am a free person who works according to what I like. People don't have the right to order me to do this, or do that. Even that being the case, nevertheless I make myself like a slave, so that all people have the right to order me around. In that way, I can help more people to endure/persist following God. [EXEG: kerdeésoo: "win people as Christians" fits with Verses 20 &amp; 21. But Verse 22 also brings in Christians who are weak in faith. Could mean "make and keep people as Christians to the end". "close to God" may be a way to cover both]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="eleútheros: free, not a slave. He"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">eleútheros: free, not a slave. He can make his own plans and do his own thing kerdeésoo: "win people as Christians" fits with Verses 20 &amp; 21. But Verse 22 also brings in Christians who are weak in faith. Could mean "make and keep people as Christians to the end". "close to God" may be a way to cover both<span class="Italic">(19) (19) </span>NRSV: For though I am free with respect to all, I have made myself a slave to all, so that I might win more of them.</Message></Annotation><v n="20" />Jadi, kalo beta ada bakumpul deng orang Yahudi, na, beta bekin diri ke orang Yahudi, ko tolong orang Yahudi kanál sang Tuhan. Kalo beta ada bakumpul deng orang yang pegang karás Tuhan pung Atoran, beta bekin iko Tuhan pung Atoran, ko beta ju bisa tolong sang dong ko kanál sang Tuhan, (biar beta su tau bilang, bekin iko itu Atoran sonde bisa bekin beta babae deng Tuhan).<bt>So (consequently), when I am gathered with the Yahudi people, I make myself like a Yahudi person, to help Yahudi people know God2. When I am gathered with people who hold firmly to God2's Law, I do according to God2's Law, so I can also help them to know God2, (even though I already know that doing according to that Law cannot make me be in a reciprocally right relationship with God2).</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="NRSV: To the Jews I became"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">NRSV: To the Jews I became as a Jew, in order to win Jews. To those under the law I became as one under the law (though I myself am not under the law) so that I might win those under the law.</Message></Annotation><v n="21" />Kalo beta ada bakumpul deng orang yang sonde tau Tuhan pung Atoran, beta jadi sama ke dong, ko antar bawa sang dong pi Tuhan. (Beta sonde lapás buang Tuhan pung Atoran yang Dia kasi turun lewat ba'i Musa, ma sakarang beta idop pake Kristus pung Atoran.)<bt>When I am gathered with people who don't know God2's Law, I become like them, to lead them to God2. (I don't release/get rid of God2's Law which He handed down via Gf Musa, but now I live using Kristus' Law.) [EXEG: without reference to Musa, makes it sound like Paul is throwing off God's (higher) law.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="NRSV: To those outside the law"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">NRSV: To those outside the law I became as one outside the law (though I am not free from God's law but am under Christ's law) so that I might win those outside the law.</Message></Annotation><note reference="9:21" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Mateos 22:34-40, Markus 12:28-34, Lukas 10:25-28, 1 Korintus 13:1-8</note><v n="22" />Kasi orang yang pung hati sonde kuat, beta bekin diri sama ke beta pung hati ju sonde kuat, ko beta bisa buju sang dong ko datang di Tuhan Allah. Kasi samua orang, beta bekin diri sama ke dong, ko biar karmana ju, beta bisa tolong kasi salamat orang saparu.<bt>For people whose livers are not strong, I also make myself like a person whose liver isn't strong, so that I can coax/cajole them to come to God. For all people, I make myself like them, so that whatever happens, I can help save some people.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="asthenésin: weak in faith 1 Cor"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">asthenésin: weak in faith 1 Cor 8:10. What kind of people are like them? kerdainoo: profit, win, get them to see things my way<span class="Italic">(22) (22) </span>NRSV: To the weak I became weak, so that I might win the weak. I have become all things to all people, that I might by all means save some.</Message></Annotation><v n="23" />Beta bekin ini hal dong samua, ko biar samua orang bisa parcaya sang Tuhan pung Kabar Bae. Deng bagitu, botong bisa dapa bagian dalam samua hal yang bae, yang Tuhan suka kasi sang botong.<bt>I do all these things, so that all people can believe in God2's Good News. In that way, we can have a share in all good things, which God2 likes to give to us. [HCE; EXEG: "all people" from v22 and context; "I" &gt; "we-excc" shift from implications of "fellow-partaker"]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="NRSV: I do it all for"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">NRSV: I do it all for the sake of the gospel, so that I may share in its blessings.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <fig path="HK-LB\BK00157C.tif" rtfFormat="width:3.5.0cm;textWrapping:around;horizontalPosition:right">Orang Yunani kasi topi juara sang orang yang manáng<bt>The Greeks gave a champion's hat to the person who won</bt></fig>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="24" />Beta kasi umpama dari lomba lari. Banya orang iko lari, ma yang dapa juara satu, cuma satu orang sa. Jadi bosong tiap orang musti lari ukur kuat ko jadi juara kasi sang Tuhan.<bt>I'll give an example from a running competition. Many people participate in running, but the one who gets champion one, is only just one person. So (consequently), each one of you-pl must run with all your strength (lit: measuring strong) to become a/the champion for God2. [EXEG: last sentence changed from 2s to 2p to match the Gk and avoid the idea that Christians are competing with each other to get a reward, and only the one who comes in first gets it—so if others seem to be ahead, just give up. CR, Amarasi 2014] [NOTE to daughter translations: Similarly, you must work with all your strength to.... Kupang is an urban society and has sports vocab. The vernaculars are unlikely to, so the first round of daughter translations are going to need to do some exploratory work to fill out the topic (of comparisons)]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="NRSV: Do you not know that"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">NRSV: Do you not know that in a race the runners all compete, but only one receives the prize? Run in such a way that you may win it.</Message></Annotation><v n="25" />Samua orang yang iko lomba musti disiplín ko cuma bekin iko apa yang dia pung palati kasi tau, to? Dong karjá banting tulang bagitu, ko cuma dapa topi juara yang nanti layu sa. Ma kalo kotong, kotong karjá ko dapa upa yang batahan sampe salamanya.<bt>All people who participate in the competition must be disciplined so that (he) only does according to what his coach/trainer tells him, right? They work their tails off (Lit: work throwing bones down) in that way, so they can get a champion's hat which will wither. But as for us, we work to get a reward which will endure forever. [EXEG: Fee: self-control in focus.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="disiplín = satia bekin iko"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z">disiplín = satia bekin iko</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="engkrateúetai: exercises self-discipline, stays in training"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">engkrateúetai: exercises self-discipline, stays in training NRSV: Athletes exercise self-control in all things; they do it to receive a perishable wreath, but we an imperishable one.<span class="Italic">(25)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="26" />Jadi beta sonde lari sambarang. Ma beta usaha karás ko lari lurus sampe di garis finis. Kalo banding beta deng tukang tinju, na, beta sonde falungku angin, ma beta puku kaná.<bt>So (consequently), I do not run aimlessly/any old way. But I make a hard effort to run straight to the finish line. If you compare me to a boxer, na, I don't fistfight the wind, but I hit connecting.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="NRSV: So I do not run"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">NRSV: So I do not run aimlessly, nor do I box as though beating the air;</Message></Annotation><v n="27" />Beta disiplín tinggi, deng lati karás ko beta bisa batahan. Te sonde bae kalo beta kasi tau orang laen so'al Tuhan Allah, padahal beta sandiri langgar atoran, ais Tuhan kasi aut sang beta dari lomba.<bt>I have high discipline, and train hard so I can endure/persevere/last. Cuz (elaboration) it is not good if I tell other people about God, but in fact I myself have violated the rules, so God2 disqualifies (sports term) me from the competition.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="adókimos: disqualified, defaulted on some rule"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">adókimos: disqualified, defaulted on some rule NRSV: but I punish my body and enslave it, so that after proclaiming to others I myself should not be disqualified.<span class="Italic">(27)</span></Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Ati-ati deng barang songgo dong!<bt>Wathc out for/Be careful with trad.worship things!</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <c n="10" />
      <v n="1" />Sodara sayang dong! Bosong jang lupa buang itu carita dolu-dolu waktu kotong pung nene-moyang ada di tampa sunyi. Tuhan Allah kasi tunju jalan sang dong samua, pake awan yang jalan di dong pung muka. Ais Dia kasi tapisa aer laut, ju antar sang dong lewat di situ sampe dong kaluar di laut pung sablá deng salamat.<bt>[EXEG: NLT] Dear siblings! You-pl must not forget about that story long ago when our-inc ancestors were in the isolated place (wilderness--main feature: no people). God showed the way for all of them, using a cloud that went in front of them. Then He separated the sea water, and led them through there until they came out on the other side of the sea safely. [EXEG: (inclusive-exclusive) “our ancestors”. The thread shows he is assuming quite a bit of familiarity with the story of the Hebrews. So either 1) he is addressing the Jewish portion of his now-believing audience (cf. Acts 18:1-8), or 2) as Ex. Summ. says, it is part of the common Christian heritage. Either interpretation yields ‘inclusive’.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="thalássees: Red Sea, an enclosed arm"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">thalássees: Red Sea, an enclosed arm of the main ocean between Egypt and Sudan on one side, and Sinai and Arabia on the other. Like Pearl Harbor, but much wider and longer inside the land. Imagine they were encircled and trapped by soldiers at Hickam and had to get to Iroquois Point to get away from them. NRSV: I do not want you to be unaware, brothers and sisters, that our ancestors were all under the cloud, and all passed through the sea,<span class="Italic">(1)</span></Message></Annotation><note reference="10:1" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Kaluar dari Masir 13:21-22, 14:22-29</note><v n="2" />Itu awan deng laut tu, jadi satu umpama. Te kotong pung nene-moyang dong parcaya sang ba'i Musa ko pimpin sang dong, ais dong iko itu awan, deng maso dalam laut sama-sama deng dia. Itu sama ke kotong yang parcaya sang Kristus, ju dapa sarani ko kasi tunju bilang, kotong jadi Dia pung orang, deng kotong dengar sang Dia.<bt>[EXEG: HCE] That cloud and that sea are an example/comparison/allegory/parable. Cuz (elaboration) our ancestors trusted in Gf/Ff Musa to lead them, so they followed that cloud, and went into the sea water together with him. That is like we who trust/believe in Kristus, also get *baptised (method neutral), to show that we have become His people, and we listen to/obey Him.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="NRSV: and all were baptized into"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">NRSV: and all were baptized into Moses in the cloud and in the sea,</Message></Annotation><v n="3" />Kotong pung nene-moyang samua makan makanan yang Tuhan pung Roh sadia kasi sang dong.<bt>All our ancestors ate the food that God's Spirit prepared/made available for them. [NOTE on vs.3-4: "the same" omitted (explicit to implicit) for naturalness, and information load. But note it is still implied by the use of /samua/ in this construction.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="NRSV: and all ate the same"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">NRSV: and all ate the same spiritual food,</Message></Annotation><note reference="10:3" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Kaluar dari Masir 16:35</note><v n="4" />Deng dong samua minum aer yang Tuhan pung Roh sadia kasi dong minum. Yang dong minum tu, kaluar dari batu bésar yang Tuhan pung Roh ada kasi tunju sang dong. Dong pi mana sa, na, itu batu su ada. Itu batu tu, andia Kristus.<bt>And they all drank the water that God's Spirit prepared/made available for them to drink. What they drank, came our of a large rock which God's Spirit had shown them. Wherever they went, na, that rock was already there. That rock was Kristus.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="NRSV: and all drank the same"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">NRSV: and all drank the same spiritual drink. For they drank from the spiritual rock that followed them, and the rock was Christ.</Message></Annotation><note reference="10:4" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Kaluar dari Masir 17:6, Daftar Sensus 20:11</note><v n="5" />Ma Tuhan Allah sonde suka deng orang banya pung bekin-bekin. Ais waktu dong jalan kuliling di tampa sunyi yang luas tu, na, ada banya yang mati di situ. Jadi dong kubur dong pung orang di banya tampa.<bt>[EXEG: CEV; HCE] But God did not like the deeds (negatively valued) of many people. So then when they were walking around in that wide lonely place, na, there were many who died there. So (consequently) they buried their people in many places. [EXEG: Gk katestroótheesan is distributive: God killed them, some in one place and some in another, so that everywhere they went they had to bury people in each place]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="*** (2009) banya added in next"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z">*** (2009) banya added in next to last sentence</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="katestroótheesan: God killed them, some in"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">katestroótheesan: God killed them, some in one place and some in another, so that everywhere they went they had to bury people in each place NRSV: Nevertheless, God was not pleased with most of them, and they were struck down in the wilderness.<span class="Italic">(5)</span></Message></Annotation><note reference="10:5" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Daftar Sensus 14:29-30</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="6" />Itu samua jadi ko kasi tunju conto, ko kotong jang kapingin bekin jahat sama ke dong.<bt>All that happened to show an example, so we-inc wouldn't have a desire to do evil like them.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="NRSV: Now these things occurred as"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">NRSV: Now these things occurred as examples for us, so that we might not desire evil as they did.</Message></Annotation><note reference="10:6" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Daftar Sensus 11:4</note><v n="7" />Jang maen songgo, sama ke dong saparu. Di Tuhan pung Tulisan Barisi ada tatulis bilang, &lt;&lt;Ini orang Isra'el dong dudu makan-minum rame-rame di patong sapi ana pung muka. Ais ju dong mulai basonggo.&gt;&gt;<bt>Don't be involved in trad.worship, like some of them were. In Gos2's Scriptures it is written saying, &lt;&lt;These Isra'el people sit eating-drinking fetively in front of the statue of the calf (cow offspring). Then they began to trad.worship.&gt;&gt;</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="NRSV: Do not become idolaters as"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">NRSV: Do not become idolaters as some of them did; as it is written, “The people sat down to eat and drink, and they rose up to play.”</Message></Annotation><note reference="10:7" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Kaluar dari Masir 32:6</note><v n="8" />Kotong jang maen serong deng orang yang bukan kotong pung laki ko kotong pung bini. Te tempo hari, dong hohongge bagitu, ju ada 23.000 orang yang mati dalam satu hari sa.<bt>We-inc must not play off-track (sexually) with a person who is not our husband or our wife. Cuz (elaboration) in those days, they were promiscuous like that, and there were 23,000 people who died in a single day.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="NRSV: We must not indulge in"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">NRSV: We must not indulge in sexual immorality as some of them did, and twenty-three thousand fell in a single day.</Message></Annotation><note reference="10:8" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Daftar Sensus 25:1-18</note><v n="9" />Kotong jang coba-coba bekin jahat macam-macam dolo, ko cari tau, Kristus mau hukum sang kotong, ko sonde. Te orang Isra'el dong saparu mau coba sang Tuhan bagitu, ais Dia kirim datang ular baracon bam-banya yang patok bekin mati sang dong.<bt>We-inc must not keep trying to do various sorts of evil, to find out if Kristus is going to punish us, or not. Cuz (elaboration) some of the people of Isra'el wanted to test God2's mettle like that, so He sent many poisonous snakes which bit (like snake or chicken) them and they died.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="patok = snake strike, ayam (patuk)"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z">patok = snake strike, ayam (patuk)</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="ekpeirázoomen: do an experiment to see"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">ekpeirázoomen: do an experiment to see whether God would perform a miracle, as in Psalm 78.18-19. Try to see how far we can go with God and get away with it, try to see how much we can sin before God punishes us NRSV: We must not put Christ to the test, as some of them did, and were destroyed by serpents.<span class="Italic">(9)</span></Message></Annotation><note reference="10:9" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Daftar Sensus 21:5-6</note><v n="10" />Kotong ju jang mangomek. Te dong saparu maen mangomek tarús, ais ju Tuhan Allah utus Dia pung ana bua dari sorga satu ko bunu bekin mati sang dong.<bt>We-inc must also not complain/grumble. Cuz (elaboration) some of them kept complaining (about everything), so then God sent one of His angels to kill them.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="NRSV: And do not complain as"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">NRSV: And do not complain as some of them did, and were destroyed by the destroyer.</Message></Annotation><note reference="10:10" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Daftar Sensus 16:41-49</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="11" />Itu hal kaná di orang Isra'el dong, ko jadi conto kasi kotong. Dong su tulis samua, ko kotong bisa balajar deng jang bekin iko dong pung sala. Te hari kiamat su deka-deka datang.<bt>Those things happened/occured to the Isra'el people, to be an example for us. They wrote all (those things), so we could learn and not do following their wrongs. Cuz (elaboration) the end of the world is fast approaching (coming very-very near).</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="tà télee tóon aioónoon: we are"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">tà télee tóon aioónoon: we are living in a time close to the end. Not just "da last times stay coming," which has always been true. We're the ones on the verge of eternity. NRSV: These things happened to them to serve as an example, and they were written down to instruct us, on whom the ends of the ages have come.<span class="Italic">(11)</span></Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="12" />Inga-inga, é! Sakarang lu pikir bilang, lu su bisa batahan kuat. Ma lu musti ati-ati, ko lu jang jato.<bt>Remember, é! [caution] Now you-sg are thinking that you can stand/endure/last firmly. But you must be careful, so that you do not fall.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="NRSV: So if you think you"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">NRSV: So if you think you are standing, watch out that you do not fall.</Message></Annotation><v n="13" />Tiap kali lu rasa kapingin bekin jahat, inga te, orang laen su parná rasa coba'an bagitu ju. Ma lu bisa parcaya sang Tuhan ko Dia bekin iko apa yang Dia omong. Te Dia sonde kasi biar lu dapa coba'an lebe dari yang lu bisa tahan. Tiap kali lu dapa coba'an bagitu, na, Dia kasi jalan kaluar sang lu. Dia mau bekin lu kuat batahan, ko lu jang jato.<bt>Each time you feel a desire to do evil, remember that other people have also experienced temptation/ testing/trial like that. But you can trust in God2 for Him to do according to what He has said. Cuz (elaboration) He will not let you experience temptation more/beyond than what you can endure/stand. Each time you get temptation like that, na, He gives/provides a way out for you. He wants to make you strong to endure, so you don't fall. [EXEG: temptation to do wrong, not testing, such as a spouse dying.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="péseei: fall down = be destroyed"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">péseei: fall down = be destroyed NRSV: No testing has overtaken you that is not common to everyone. God is faithful, and he will not let you be tested beyond your strength, but with the testing he will also provide the way out so that you may be able to endure it.<span class="Italic">(13)</span></Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Inga te, samua coba'an yang lu"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z">Inga te, samua coba'an yang lu rasa kapingin bekin jahat tu, sama sa deng orang laen parná rasa ju. Te Dia sonde kasi biar lu dapa coba'an yang takán lu lebe dari yang lu bisa tahan. Inga te, samua coba'an yang lu rasa kapingin bekin jahat tu, sama sa deng orang laen parná rasa ju. Ma lu bisa parcaya sang Tuhan ko Dia bekin iko apa yang Dia omong. Te Dia sonde kasi biar lu dapa coba'an lebe dari yang lu bisa tahan. Tiap kali lu dapa coba'an bagitu, na, Dia kasi jalan kaluar sang lu. Dia mau bekin lu kuat batahan, ko lu jang jato.<span class="Italic">(13)</span></Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="14" />Jadi sodara sayang dong! Kalo orang mau coba paksa sang bosong ko soya sang sosonggo dong, na, lari kaluar dari situ sa! Jang ba'eok lai!<bt>So (consequently) dear siblings! If someone wants to try and force pressure you to bow/worship3 trad.worship things, na, just get out of there! Don't dawdle!</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="NRSV: Therefore, my dear friends, flee"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">NRSV: Therefore, my dear friends, flee from the worship of idols.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="15" />Beta ba'omong kasi bosong yang tau pikir panjang. Biar bosong timbang sandiri ko dapa tau apa yang beta mau omong tu, batúl.<bt>I am speaking to you-pl who know how to think long (wise, think through, examine implications). Go ahead and weigh/evaluate for yourselves so you understand that what I am going to say is true.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="NRSV: I speak as to sensible"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">NRSV: I speak as to sensible people; judge for yourselves what I say.</Message></Annotation><v n="16" />Pikir coba ini hal: kalo kotong bakumpul ko makan di Tuhan pung meja, ais ame itu galás ko minta tarima kasi sang Dia, ais kotong minum dari itu galás, dia pung arti bilang, kotong ada ta'ika deng Kristus. Waktu Dia tumpa Dia pung dara ko mati, itu tingka ke kotong ju iko mati. Kalo kotong bekin pica itu roti, ais kotong makan, dia pung arti sama, andia, kotong ada ta'ika deng Kristus. Jadi waktu Dia mati, itu tingka ke kotong ju iko mati.<bt>Have a think about this: if we-inc gather together to eat at God2's table, then take that glass to give thanks to Him, then we drink from that glass, it means that we are bound/linked with Kristus. When He spilled His blood to die, it is as if we also accompanied/participated in dying. If/when we break that bread, then we eat (it), that means the same thing, that is, we are bound with Kristus. So (consequently), when He died, that is like we also accompanied/participated in dying.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="NRSV: The cup of blessing that"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">NRSV: The cup of blessing that we bless, is it not a sharing in the blood of Christ? The bread that we break, is it not a sharing in the body of Christ?</Message></Annotation><note reference="10:16" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Mateos 26:27-28, Markus 14:22-24, Lukas 22:19-20</note><v n="17" />Kotong samua ame bagian dari satu balok roti. Jadi samua yang ame bagian dari satu roti tu, sama ke kotong ta'ika jadi satu badan, biar kotong banya orang.<bt>All of us-inc take a share/portion in the same loaf of bread. So (consequently), everyone who takes a portion from that bread, is like we are bound/linked together becoming one body, even though we are many people.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="NRSV: Because there is one bread,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">NRSV: Because there is one bread, we who are many are one body, for we all partake of the one bread.</Message></Annotation><v n="18" />Pikir coba bangsa Isra'el dolu-dolu dong. Waktu dong horo binatang di atas meja korban ko sémba sang Tuhan, kapala agama yang horo tu, yang dapa makan dia pung daging. Dia pung arti, dong ta'ika deng Tuhan, deng dong ju ta'ika deng orang yang bawa itu binatang ko bekin korban.<bt>Have a think about the people/race of Isra'el long ago. When they ritually slaughtered animals on the sacrifice table to worship God2, the priest who slit the throat if the one who got to eat its meat. That meant that they were bound/linked with God2, and they were also bound with the person who brought that animal to make a sacrifice. [NOTE to daughter translations: explication to make lexical cohesion to the section that this closes. NLT, HCE]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="NRSV: Consider the people of Israel;"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">NRSV: Consider the people of Israel; are not those who eat the sacrifices partners in the altar?</Message></Annotation><note reference="10:18" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Kapala Agama dong pung Atoran 7:6</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="19-20" />Beta pung maksud karmana? Waktu orang yang sonde kanál sang Tuhan mau kasi persembahan sang dong pung sosonggo, itu sonde ada pung arti apa-apa, ko? Te itu sosonggo tu, cuma patong mati sa! Sonde! Beta pung maksud bagini: waktu orang horo binatang jadi korban kasi dong pung barang sosonggo, dong ada songgo sang roh jahat dong. Ma dong sonde sémba sang Tuhan Allah yang batúl. Jadi beta sonde mau bosong ta'ika deng roh jahat dong bagitu.<bt>What do I mean2? When people who do not know God2 want to give offerings to their trad.worship things, it has no meaning, or (what)? Cuz (elaboration) that trad.worship things is just a dead statue! No! What I mean2 is this: when a person slaughters an animal to be a sacrifice to their trad.worship things, they are trad.worshipping *evil spirits. But they are not worshipping the true God. So (consequently), I don't want you-pl to be bound/linked to evil spirits like that.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="NRSV: What do I imply then?"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">NRSV: What do I imply then? That food sacrificed to idols is anything, or that an idol is anything? No, I imply that what pagans sacrifice, they sacrifice to demons and not to God. I do not want you to be partners with demons.</Message></Annotation><note reference="10:20" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Carita Ulang so'al Jalan Idop 32:17</note><v n="21" />Kalo bosong ta'ika deng Tuhan, ais minum dari itu galás di Tuhan pung meja, na, bosong sonde bole pi bacampor deng roh jahat dong, deng minum dari dong pung galás waktu orang ada songgo sang dong. Te itu dia pung arti bilang, bosong ada ta'ika deng roh jahat dong. Bagitu ju, kalo bosong makan di Tuhan pung meja, bosong sonde bole iko makan di dong pung meja. Te itu dia pung arti bilang, bosong ada ta'ika deng roh jahat dong! Bodo, é!<bt>If you are bound with God2, then drink from that glass at God2's table, na, you may not mix/associate with evil spirits, and drink from their glass when people are trad.worshipping them. Cuz (elaboration) that means that, you are bound/linked to those evil spirits. In the same way also, if you eat at God2's table, you may not participate in eating at their [whose?] table. Cuz (elaboration) that means that you are bound/linked with those evil spirits! Stupid, é!</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="He's not just reporting a situation"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">He's not just reporting a situation he doesn't like; he's rubbing their noses in it and saying they've got to be crazy to act like that. NRSV: You cannot drink the cup of the Lord and the cup of demons. You cannot partake of the table of the Lord and the table of demons.<span class="Italic">(21)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="22" />Bosong ada pikir karmana? Mau bekin kotong pung Bos camburu, ko? Bahaya tu! Mangkali bosong pikir bosong lebe kuat dari Dia, ko?<bt>What are you thinking? Do you want make our-inc Bos jealous, or (what)? That's dangerous! Perhaps you think that you are stronger than He, or (what)? [LEX: parazeelóumen: make God angry, making him resent those who do not give God the total loyalty that they have promised.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="parazeelóumen: make God angry, making him"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">parazeelóumen: make God angry, making him resent those who do not give God the total loyalty that they have promised NRSV: Or are we provoking the Lord to jealousy? Are we stronger than he?<span class="Italic">(22)</span></Message></Annotation><note reference="10:22" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Carita Ulang so'al Jalan Idop 32:21</note></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Bekin samua-samua ko angka tinggi-tinggi Tuhan pung nama<bt>Do everything to *glorify (lift way up high) god2's name</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="23" />Mangkali bosong bilang, &lt;&lt;Beta mau bekin apa sa, bole. Te itu beta pung hak.&gt;&gt; Batúl. Ma inga te sonde samua hal bae kasi sang lu. Deng sonde samua hal bisa tolong bekin kuat lu pung hati.<bt>Perhaps you-pl might say, &lt;&lt;Whatever I want to do, I may do it. Cuz (elaboration) that is my right.&gt;&gt; True, But remember that not everything is good for you. And not everything can help strengthen your liver. [Gk. TEXT: "For me" appears only in late manuscripts or in scribal emendations scribbled on top of old manuscripts. It is here because the Kupang is non-sensical without it, not because it is in later MSS.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="exestin: impersonal, for anybody. &quot;For me&quot;"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">exestin: impersonal, for anybody. "For me" appears only in late manuscripts or in scribal emendations scribbled on top of old manuscripts. NRSV: “All things are lawful,” but not all things are beneficial. “All things are lawful,” but not all things build up.<span class="Italic">(23)</span></Message></Annotation><note reference="10:23" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">1 Korintus 6:12</note><v n="24" />Jang cuma cari ontong kasi lu pung diri sandiri. Ada lebe bae, cari ontong kasi orang laen ju.<bt>Don't just look for benefit/profit for your own self. It is better to also look for benefit for other people.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="NRSV: Do not seek your own"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">NRSV: Do not seek your own advantage, but that of the other.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="25" />Jadi beta usul bagini: kalo béli daging di pasar, na, makan sa. Sonde usa batanya lai, &lt;&lt;Ini daging songgo, ko?&gt;&gt; Ko, pikir bilang, &lt;&lt;Beta bole makan ini daging, ko sonde?&gt;&gt;<bt>So (consequently), I suggest like this: if (you) buy meat in the market, na, just eat it. (You) don't need to be asking around anymore, &lt;&lt;Has this meat been used in trad.worship, or (not)?&gt;&gt; Or, think that, &lt;&lt;May I eat this meat, or not?&gt;&gt;</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="NRSV: Eat whatever is sold in"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">NRSV: Eat whatever is sold in the meat market without raising any question on the ground of conscience,</Message></Annotation><v n="26" />Te di Tuhan pung Tulisan Barisi ada tulis bilang, &lt;&lt;Dunya deng dia pung isi samua, kotong pung Bos pung milik.&gt;&gt;<bt>Cuz (elaboration) in God2's Scriptures it is written saying, &lt;&lt;The world and all its contents, is the possession of our-inc Bos.&gt;&gt;</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="NRSV: for “the earth and its"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">NRSV: for “the earth and its fullness are the Lord's.”</Message></Annotation><note reference="10:26" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Lagu Puji dong 24:1</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="27" />Kalo ada orang yang balóm parcaya sang Tuhan bilang, &lt;&lt;Mari datang makan di ruma!&gt;&gt; Kalo bosong mau pi, na, pi sa, deng makan samua yang dong kasi sang bosong. Sonde usa tanya bilang, &lt;&lt;Beta bole makan ini barang, ko sonde?&gt;&gt;<bt>If a person who does not yet believe in God2, says, &lt;&lt;Come, eat at (my) house!&gt;&gt; If you want to go, na, just go, and eat everything that they give to you-pl. There's no ned to ask, &lt;&lt;May I eat this stuff, or not?&gt;&gt;</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="NRSV: If an unbeliever invites you"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">NRSV: If an unbeliever invites you to a meal and you are disposed to go, eat whatever is set before you without raising any question on the ground of conscience.</Message></Annotation><v n="28" />(Ma kalo ada orang datang bakusu-kusu bilang, &lt;&lt;Jang makan yang ini, te ini daging songgo,&gt;&gt; lebe bae lu sonde usa makan. Lu musti taro kira di itu orang yang datang lapor tu, dia kabaratan, ko sonde.<bt>(But if a person comes up to you and whispers saying, &lt;&lt;Don't eat this here, cuz this is meat used in trad.worship,&gt;&gt; it's better that you-sg not eat. You must pay attention to that person who came to report, whether he objects, or not. [EXEG: From the Gk, the issue is “whose conscience”. Almost all go with “the one who informed you” (Ex.Summ. NLT, CEV). So the issue for Helong is if they take KM /kabaratan/ as 1) have issues with (conscience), or 2) the social act of expressing objection. The first is the intended meaning. Note TB also uses /keberatan/. The problem with the suggestion of saying ‘Pay attention to what he believes to be right’ is this phrasing throws it into the sector of religious beliefs, and not ethical considerations, skewing the focus.] [ALT: ko jang bekin barát sang dia.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="kabaratan ; *** (2009) note added"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z">kabaratan ; *** (2009) note added</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="NRSV: But if someone says to"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">NRSV: But if someone says to you, “This has been offered in sacrifice,” then do not eat it, out of consideration for the one who informed you, and for the sake of conscience</Message></Annotation><v n="29" />Beta pung maksud, pikir bae-bae, iko itu orang pung pikir, bole makan, ko sonde. Jang cuma pikir yang bae iko lu pung diri sandiri.)<bt>What I mean is, think it through carefully, according to that person, is it OK for you to eat, or not. Don't just think what is good for you yourself.) [ALT: iko lu pung pikiran sandiri.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="NRSV: I mean the other's conscience,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">NRSV: I mean the other's conscience, not your own.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Padahal beta bole bekin iko beta pung suka. Ma kalo orang laen pikir itu sonde bae dia bekin satu hal, akurang ko beta ju sonde bebas bekin iko beta pung suka, cuma tagal itu hal sonde bae kasi sang itu orang?<bt>Whereas in fact, I may eat according to my likes. But if another person thinks that it is not good for him to do something, why should I not be free to do according to my likes, just because that thing is not good for that person?</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="NRSV: For why should my liberty"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">NRSV: For why should my liberty be subject to the judgment of someone else's conscience?</Message></Annotation><v n="30" />Kalo beta minta tarima kasi sang Tuhan, ais beta makan, akurang ko orang omong kasi jato sang beta?<bt>If I give thanks to God2, and then I eat, why should people talk making me fall/say bad things about me?</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="NRSV: If I partake with thankfulness,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">NRSV: If I partake with thankfulness, why should I be denounced because of that for which I give thanks?</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="31" />Jadi bosong mau makan ko, minum ko, bekin apa sa, na, bekin samua-samua ko bosong kasi tunju Tuhan Allah pung nama bae.<bt>So (consequently), if you-pl want to eat or, drink or, do whatever, na, do everything so you can show/demonstrate God's good name/reputation. [EXEG: Gk: to the glory of God here]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="NRSV: So, whether you eat or"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">NRSV: So, whether you eat or drink, or whatever you do, do everything for the glory of God.</Message></Annotation><v n="32" />Jang bekin susa sang orang Yahudi, ko, orang bukan Yahudi, ko, Tuhan pung orang parcaya dong.<bt>Don't make trouble for Yahudi people, or non Yahudi people, or God2's believers. [EXEG: Our lex choice is slightly broader/more generic than the literal ‘gloss’ of ‘give no offense’, but well within what is described by LN; CEV, TEV, ICC, NIGTC, TH, HNTC.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="NRSV: Give no offense to Jews"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">NRSV: Give no offense to Jews or to Greeks or to the church of God,</Message></Annotation><v n="33" />Bekin sama ke beta ni. Te beta coba-coba ko bekin sanáng sang dong samua dalam samua hal. Beta sonde cuma coba bekin yang bae kasi sang beta sa. Ma beta coba bekin yang bae kasi sang dong samua, ko dong ju dapa salamat.<bt>Do as I do. Cuz (elaboration) I keep trying to make them happy in everything. I don't just try to do what is good for me. But I try to do what is good for all of them, so they can also be saved.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="NRSV: just as I try to"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">NRSV: just as I try to please everyone in everything I do, not seeking my own advantage, but that of many, so that they may be saved.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <c n="11" />
      <v n="1" />Bosong conto sang beta, deng bekin iko beta pung jalan idop. Te beta conto sang Kristus, deng bekin iko sang Dia.<bt>You-pl example (transitive verb) me, and follow my way of life. Cuz (elaboration) I example Kristus, and follow what He does.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Compare 7:7 NRSV: Be imitators of"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">Compare 7:7 NRSV: Be imitators of me, as I am of Christ.<span class="Italic">(1)</span></Message></Annotation><note reference="11:1" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">1 Korintus 4:16, Filipi 3:17</note></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Kalo bekin ibadat, na, laki-laki deng parampuan musti kasi tunju hormat iko adat pung biasa<bt>If you hold a worship.service, na, males and females must show respect according to the norms of adat</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Parkara so'al orang musti tutu ame"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z">Parkara so'al orang musti tutu ame dong pung kapala waktu dong ada sambayang, ko sonde</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="2" />Beta angka jempol sang bosong, tagal biar karmana ju, bosong inga sang beta tarús. Deng samua hal yang beta su ajar kasi bosong, bosong masi bekin iko. Talalu bae!<bt>[EXEG: See Fee for whole section.] I lift my thumb to you-pl (=well done!), because no matter what, you keep remembering me. And all the things which I taught you, you are still doing. That's sooo good!</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="angka jempol = ; taro hormat"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z">angka jempol = ; taro hormat implies sang ; kasi tunju hormat doesn't have to</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="epainóo: praise, commend, (also Verse 17)"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">epainóo: praise, commend, (also Verse 17) NRSV: I commend you because you remember me in everything and maintain the traditions just as I handed them on to you.<span class="Italic">(2)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="3" />Ma ada satu hal yang beta mau kasi inga sang bosong bagini: jang lupa bosong pung asal dari mana. Tiap laki-laki yang parcaya, ba'akar di Kristus yang jadi dia pung kapala. Parampuan asal dari laki-laki. Deng Kristus datang dari Tuhan Allah.<bt>But there is one thing that I want to remind you of like this: don't forget where your-pl origins/source are. Each man who believes, is rooted in Kristus who is his head. Women originated from men. And Kristus came from God. [EXEG: Gk /kephale/ as source, not authority; see Fee, Nyland, Belzekian, CBE, etc.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="tubu"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z">tubu</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="eidénai: not new teaching, but something"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">eidénai: not new teaching, but something they already had NRSV: But I want you to understand that Christ is the head of every man, and the husband is the head of his wife, and God is the head of Christ.<span class="Italic">(3)</span></Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="itu Orang yang Tuhan Allah su"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z">itu Orang yang Tuhan Allah su tunju memang dari dolu tu, Dia jadi Kapala tiap orang ada pung kapala yang dia dengar. Jadi, bini dengar sang dia pung laki; laki dengar sang Kristus; deng Kristus dengar sang Tuhan Allah.<span class="Italic">(3)</span></Message></Annotation><note reference="11:3" class="Note General Paragraph" usfm="f">Ahli bahasa Yunani dong bilang, <span class="Italic">kefale</span> &lt;&lt;kapala&gt;&gt; pung arti, 1) tubu pung kapala, deng 2) asal, akar (sumber). Ma dalam bahasa Yunani, <span class="Italic">kefale</span> pung arti bukan &lt;&lt;orang yang parenta&gt;&gt;.<bt>Experts in the Yunani language say, <span class="Italic">kefale</span> &lt;&lt;head&gt;&gt; means 1) head of a (physical) body, and 2) origin, root (source). But in the Yunani language <span class="Italic">kefale</span> does not mean &lt;&lt;person who rules&gt;&gt;.</bt></note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="4" />Naa! Laki-laki jang tutu dia pung kapala waktu dia ada sambayang, ko, waktu dia ada kasi tau Tuhan pung pasán. Te itu sama ke dia bekin malu sang Kristus, tagal dia sonde taro hormat iko kotong pung biasa.<bt>Naa! A man should not cover his head when he is praying, or when he is telling/explaining God2's message. Cuz (elaboration) that is like he is bringing shame on Kristus, because he is not placing respect according to our-inc norms.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="propheeteúoon: proclaiming God's message, proclaim the"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">propheeteúoon: proclaiming God's message, proclaim the instructions of God, but not the same as preaching the Gospel katà kephalées échoon: probably a garment hanging down from the head and covering the hair and the upper part of the body<span class="Italic">(4) (4) </span>NRSV: Any man who prays or prophesies with something on his head disgraces his head,</Message></Annotation><v n="5" />Ma parampuan musti tutu dia pung kapala waktu dia ada sambayang, ko, waktu dia kasi tau Tuhan pung pasán. Te kalo sonde, na, itu sama ke dia bekin malu sang dia pung laki, tagal dia sonde taro hormat iko kotong pung biasa. Deng dia ju bekin malu sang dia pung diri sandiri, sama ke kalo parampuan cukur bekin polik dia pung kapala.<bt>But a woman must cover her head when she is praying, or when she is telling God2's message. Cuz (elaboration) if not, na, that is like she is bringing shame on her husband, because she is not placing respect according to our norms. And she is also bringing shame on her own self, just like if/when a woman shaves her head bald.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="kataischýnei teèn kaphaleèn autées: offends the"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">kataischýnei teèn kaphaleèn autées: offends the dignity of her husband gàr: last sentence to expand and emphasize "make her head shame"<span class="Italic">(5) (5) </span>exyreeméneei: in Paul's time, shaving a woman's head was an insult and a shame. It would be done to disgrace her publicly NRSV: but any woman who prays or prophesies with her head unveiled disgraces her head-it is one and the same thing as having her head shaved.<span class="Italic">(5)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="6" />Te kalo ada parampuan yang sonde mau tutu dia pung kapala ko jadi tanda bilang, dia taro hormat sang dia pung laki, na, lebe bae dia gunting bekin pende dia pung rambu. Ma kalo dia rasa dia pung kapala botak tu bekin malu sang dia, lebe bae dia tutu dia pung kapala sa.<bt>Cuz (elaboration) if there is a woman who doesn't want to cover her head as a sign that, she places respect on her husband, na, it would be better if she scissored her hair short. But if she feels her bald head would make her ashamed, it's just better for her to cover her head.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="NRSV: For if a woman will"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">NRSV: For if a woman will not veil herself, then she should cut off her hair; but if it is disgraceful for a woman to have her hair cut off or to be shaved, she should wear a veil.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="7" />Coba pikir bagini: laki-laki sonde parlú tutu ame dia pung kapala, te Tuhan Allah bekin laki-laki iko Dia pung model. Andia ko laki-laki jadi hasil yang kasi tunju Tuhan pung hebat. Deng parampuan ju jadi hasil yang kasi tunju laki-laki pung hebat.<bt>Have a think about this: a man doesn't need to cover up his head, cuz (elaboration) God made man according to His model/pattern/type. That is why man is a product that shows/demonstrates God2's amazing/ incredibleness/ greatness. And a woman is also a product which shows/demonstrates a man's amazing/ incredibleness/ greatness</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="NRSV: For a man ought not"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">NRSV: For a man ought not to have his head veiled, since he is the image and reflection of God; but woman is the reflection of man.</Message></Annotation><note reference="11:7" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Carita Mula-mula 1:26-27</note><v n="8" />Te waktu Tuhan Allah bekin ini dunya, Dia sonde bekin laki-laki dari parampuan. Ma Dia bekin parampuan dari laki-laki.<bt>Cuz (elaboration) when God made this world, He did not make man from woman. But He made woman from man.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="NRSV: Indeed, man was not made"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">NRSV: Indeed, man was not made from woman, but woman from man.</Message></Annotation><v n="9" />Deng Dia sonde bekin laki-laki kasi sang parampuan. Ma Dia bekin parampuan kasi sang laki-laki.<bt>And He did not make man for woman. But He made woman for man.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="NRSV: Neither was man created for"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">NRSV: Neither was man created for the sake of woman, but woman for the sake of man.</Message></Annotation><note reference="11:8-9" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Carita Mula-mula 2:18-19</note><v n="10" />Jadi ada lebe bae parampuan tutu dia pung kapala, ko orang tau bilang, dia ada pake dia pung hak ko sambayang deng kasi tau Tuhan pung pasán, iko yang batúl. Ana bua dari sorga ju tau bagitu.<bt>So (consequently), it is best/better for a woman to cover her head, so people know that she is using her right to pray and tell God2's message, according to what is right. Angels in heaven also know that. [EXEG choice: "as a sign of her authority to pray and prophecy" OR "as a sign that she is under someone's authority"; we take the first. See also CEV, NLT, NRSV take neutral line.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="NRSV: For this reason a woman"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">NRSV: For this reason a woman ought to have a symbol of authority on her head, because of the angels.</Message></Annotation><v n="11" />Ma kalo dong ta'ika deng Tuhan, parampuan deng laki-laki sonde badiri sandiri-sandiri.<bt>But if they are bound/linked with God2, females and males do not stand alone-alone (are not independent of each other).</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="not independent NRSV: Nevertheless, in the"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">not independent NRSV: Nevertheless, in the Lord woman is not independent of man or man independent of woman.<span class="Italic">(11)</span></Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Ma kalo dong ta'ika deng Tuhan,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z">Ma kalo dong ta'ika deng Tuhan, parampuan sonde bekin apa-apa sandiri, deng laki-laki ju sonde bekin apa-apa sandiri.</Message></Annotation><v n="12" />Partama kali, Tuhan Allah bekin parampuan dari laki-laki. Ma ais itu, parampuan yang barana ame laki-laki. Deng Tuhan Allah yang bekin ko samua jadi.<bt>The first time, God made woman from man. But after that, the woman was the one who gave birth to men. And God is the one who made everything happen/ come into being.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="NRSV: For just as woman came"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">NRSV: For just as woman came from man, so man comes through woman; but all things come from God.</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Ma abis itu, tiap laki-laki kaluar"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z">Ma abis itu, tiap laki-laki kaluar dari parampuan.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="13" />Bosong pikir coba! Kalo parampuan sambayang sang Tuhan Allah, deng sonde tutu dia pung kapala, iko bosong, itu bae, ko sonde?<bt>So you should think about it! If a woman prays to God, and does not cover her head, according to you-pl, is that good, or not?</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="NRSV: Judge for yourselves: is it"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">NRSV: Judge for yourselves: is it proper for a woman to pray to God with her head unveiled?</Message></Annotation><v n="14" />Iko bosong pung adat di kota Korintus, kalo laki-laki pung rambu panjang, itu bekin malu sang dia, ko?<bt>According to your adat/customs in the city of Korintus, if a man has long hari, does that bring shame on him, or (what)? [LEX: Gk. phýsis: nature (nowadays we would say "our culture"); see also Fee.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="phýsis: nature (nowadays we would say"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">phýsis: nature (nowadays we would say "our culture") NRSV: Does not nature itself teach you that if a man wears long hair, it is degrading to him,<span class="Italic">(14)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="15" />Ma kalo parampuan pung rambu panjang, dia talalu bagus, to? Tuhan ada kasi dia rambu panjang ko tutu ame dia pung kapala. Itu yang batúl.<bt>But if a woman has long hair, that's really nice, right? God2 has given her long hair to cover her head. That's what is right. [EXEG: Gk: glory here] [NOTE: Last sentence is with reference to v.13-14 idea of natural and proper. This is good Rabbinic logic, but bad Greco-Roman logic.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="NRSV: but if a woman has"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">NRSV: but if a woman has long hair, it is her glory? For her hair is given to her for a covering.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="16" />Ma kalo ada yang mau bakanjar tarús so'al ini hal, inga te, dari botong yang jadi pimpinan, deng dari jama'at-jama'at dong, ini su yang botong pung biasa.<bt>But if there is someone who wants to keep arguing about this matter, remember that from us-exc who are leaders, and from the various congregations, this [decisively] is what is our norm.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="heeméis ... oudè hai ekkleesíai tóu"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">heeméis ... oudè hai ekkleesíai tóu theóu: not us, not the churches of God NRSV: But if anyone is disposed to be contentious-we have no such custom, nor do the churches of God.<span class="Italic">(16)</span></Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Jang macam-macam kalo makan di Tuhan pung meja<bt>Don't mess around when you are eating at God2's table (=communion)</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="17" />Sakarang beta mau omong satu hal lai. Dalam ini hal, beta sonde bisa puji sang bosong. Te waktu bosong ada bakumpul, bosong sonde bekin iko yang batúl, ma bosong tamba lebe kaco lai.<bt>Now I am going to talk about another matter. In this matter, I cannot praise you-pl. Cuz (elaboration) when you are gathered together, you are not doing according to what is right, but you are making things even worse/more chaotic.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="ouk epainóo: no praise, opposite of"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">ouk epainóo: no praise, opposite of Verse 2 NRSV: Now in the following instructions I do not commend you, because when you come together it is not for the better but for the worse.<span class="Italic">(17)</span></Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="18" />Partama, beta ada dengar bilang, waktu bosong bakumpul bekin ibadat, bosong ada tabagi-bagi. Saparu dari yang beta dengar tu, pasti ada yang batúl.<bt>First, I have heard, that when you are gathered to have a worship.service, you are divided/split up. Some of what I have heard, surely has some truth.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="méros: I partly believe it, I"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">méros: I partly believe it, I am sure there is some truth in it NRSV: For, to begin with, when you come together as a church, I hear that there are divisions among you; and to some extent I believe it.<span class="Italic">(18)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="19" />(Memang, tagal bosong pung blok-blok tu, nanti kantara sapa yang batúl-batúl dengar sang kotong pung Bos, deng sapa yang sonde mau dengar sang Dia.)<bt>(Really, because of your-pl factions (blok-blok), it will become evident/visible who really listens to/obeys our Bos, and who doesn't want to obey Him.)</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="blok-blok = factions"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z">blok-blok = factions</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="dokimoi Chap. 3:18?|i(19) (19) |rNRSV: Indeed,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">dokimoi Chap. 3:18?<span class="Italic">(19) (19) </span>NRSV: Indeed, there have to be factions among you, for only so will it become clear who among you are genuine.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="20" />Te waktu bosong orang sarani ada bakumpul ko makan di Tuhan pung meja, bosong musti inga sang Tuhan Yesus. Itu yang batúl. Ma bosong sonde bekin bagitu.<bt>Cuz (elaboration) when you Christians are gathered together to eat at God2's table, you must remember the Lord Yesus. That is what is right. But you are not doing that.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="NRSV: When you come together, it"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">NRSV: When you come together, it is not really to eat the Lord's supper.</Message></Annotation><v n="21" />Dia pung bukti, andia waktu bosong dudu makan, ada yang sonde tunggu orang laen, ada yang makan balalas, deng ada laen lai yang minum mabo. Sampe ada orang laen yang sonde dapa bagian, ko dong jadi lapar.<bt>The proof/evidence, is that when you are sitting and eating, there are those who don't wait for others, there are those who eat greedily, and there are stil others who drink (until) drunk. To the point that there are other people who don't get a share, so they are hungry.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="NRSV: For when the time comes"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">NRSV: For when the time comes to eat, each of you goes ahead with your own supper, and one goes hungry and another becomes drunk.</Message></Annotation><v n="22" />Karmana ni!? Bosong sonde ada pung ruma sandiri ko makan-minum di situ, ko? Ko, bosong pung maksud bekin rusak Tuhan pung jama'at pung nama bae? Ko, bosong mau bekin malu orang malarat dong? Bosong mau beta omong karmana? Mau beta puji sang bosong dalam ini hal, ko? Jang harap!<bt>How can this be!? Don't you have your own houses to eat-drink there, or (what)? Or, is your intention to ruin/damage the good name of God2's congregation/s? Or, are you wanting to shame the poor/destitute people? What do you want me to say? Do you want me to praise you in this matter? Don't hope (=no way)!</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Jang harap = sonde bisa!"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z">Jang harap = sonde bisa!</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="kataischýnete toùs meè échontas: make the"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">kataischýnete toùs meè échontas: make the poor people shame NRSV: What! Do you not have homes to eat and drink in? Or do you show contempt for the church of God and humiliate those who have nothing? What should I say to you? Should I commend you? In this matter I do not commend you!<span class="Italic">(22)</span></Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Roti deng aer anggor jadi tanda ko bekin kotong inga sang Yesus pung mati<bt>That bread and the wine/grape juice, are signs that make us-inc remember Yesus' death</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Mateos 26:26-29; Markus 14:22-25; Lukas 22:14-20)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="23" />Tuhan Yesus sandiri yang kasi tau memang ini hal sang beta, deng beta sarakan lai sang bosong. Bilang, waktu orang dong siap-siap ko mau bunu sang Dia, itu malam Dia angka roti satu balok.<bt>The Lord Yesus himself is the one who told/made known this matter to me directly, and I am handing it over again/further to you. That, when people were preparing to kill Him, that night He picked up a loaf of bread. [NOTE: many commentators feels the wording of this verse is evidence of a very early creed in widespread circulation among Christians predating the writing of the gospels (which were written after most of Paul's letters. So the idea of passing on something he has received with authority needs to be clear.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="parélabon ... parédooka: used among Jewish"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">parélabon ... parédooka: used among Jewish and other teachers when speaking about traditional teaching, emphasizing the personal relationship between the teacher and the ones taught apò (not parà): does this mean that he got this particular teaching indirectly, through church teaching?<span class="Italic">(23) (23) </span>en téei nyktì: night time, probably just a while after sunset, 7 or 8 PM árton: a whole bread, probably not broken yet<span class="Italic">(23) (23) </span>NRSV: For I received from the Lord what I also handed on to you, that the Lord Jesus on the night when he was betrayed took a loaf of bread,</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="deng beta yang kasi tau bale"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z">deng beta yang kasi tau bale sang bosong.</Message></Annotation><v n="24" />Ju Dia sambayang minta tarima kasi sang Tuhan Allah. Ais Dia kasi tau Dia pung ana bua dong bilang, &lt;&lt;Makan ini roti. Te ini Beta pung badan. Nanti dong bekin ancor Beta pung badan kasi sang bosong. Jadi bosong musti makan ini roti ko bosong inga sang Beta.&gt;&gt;<bt>Then He prayed giving thanks to God. Then2 he told His *disciples (underlings) saying, &lt;&lt;Eat this bread. Cuz (elaboration) this is My body. They will destroy/smash My body for you-pl. So (consequently) you must eat this bread so that you remember Me.&gt;&gt; [EXEG: even though “(broken) for you” is a poorly supported textual variant, we can't just go literal “this is My body which is ( ) for you.”]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="anámneesin: memorial, reminder NRSV: and when"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">anámneesin: memorial, reminder NRSV: and when he had given thanks, he broke it and said, “This is my body that is for you. Do this in remembrance of me.”<span class="Italic">(24)</span></Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="25" />Waktu dong su makan abis, Dia ju bekin yang sama deng galás aer anggor bilang, &lt;&lt;Ini aer anggor pung arti, andia: Tuhan Allah mau ika janji baru deng bosong. Deng Beta musti tumpa Beta pung dara sampe Beta mati dolo, baru itu janji bisa jadi. Ais tiap kali bosong minum aer anggor bagini, na, bosong musti inga Beta pung mati.&gt;&gt;<bt>When they had finished eating, He also did the same with a glass of wine/grape juice saying, &lt;&lt;This wine means, that God is going to bind a new promise with you. And I must spill my blood (phrasing implies: for a cause) to the point that I die first, only then will that promise happen/come into effect. So then each time you drink this wine like this, na, you must remember My death.”</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="*** (2009) close quotes at end"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z">*** (2009) close quotes at end of vs.25</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="diatheékee: new relationship with God that"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">diatheékee: new relationship with God that my dying makes possible NRSV: In the same way he took the cup also, after supper, saying, “This cup is the new covenant in my blood. Do this, as often as you drink it, in remembrance of me.”<span class="Italic">(25)</span></Message></Annotation><note reference="11:25" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Kaluar dari Masir 24:6-8, Yeremia 31:31-34</note><v n="26" />Tiap kali bosong bekin ini acara ko makan roti bagini deng minum dari galás bagini, sampe Tuhan datang kambali, itu sama ke bosong ada carita ulang so'al Dia pung mati.<bt>Each time you do this ceremony to eat bread this way and drink from the glass this way, until the Lord comes back, that is like you are retelling about His death. [EXEG: who is speaking here? Jesus (referring to himself in third person as He so often does), or Paul commenting on it? The fact that at least 8 commentators actually address the issue means it's not black and white (even though they all favour Paul, see Ex. Summ.). The shift from 1s in vs.24-25 to 3s in vs.26 also favours Paul. All but one version consulted, and all commentators close the quote at the end of 25. This was queried/challenged by a couple of our MTT teams, so it's likely we're asking for trouble by maintaining the more poorly supported idea of taking the quote through 26, instead of ending it at 25. Revised.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="*** (2009) revised from earlier version,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z">*** (2009) revised from earlier version, note added. <span class="Italic">(26) </span>Perhaps review this, as it was queried/challenged by a couple of teams. Gk has 3s in vs.26. Most translations end quote at vs.25, and return to Paul speaking in vs. 26. Why do we use 1s here??</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="tòn árton tóuton ... tò poteérion:"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">tòn árton tóuton ... tò poteérion: not just any bread and wine, but the bread and wine used in the Christian ceremony NRSV: For as often as you eat this bread and drink the cup, you proclaim the Lord's death until he comes.<span class="Italic">(26)</span></Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Tiap kali bosong bekin ini acara"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z">Tiap kali bosong bekin ini acara ko makan roti bagini deng minum dari galás bagini, sampe Beta datang kambali, itu sama ke bosong ada carita ulang so'al Beta pung mati.&gt;&gt;</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Kalo lu pung hati sonde batúl, na, jang dudu makan di Tuhan pung meja [\s2]<bt>If your liver isn't right, na, don't sit and eat at God2's table</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="27" />Naa! Tagal itu, kalo ada orang yang makan itu roti deng minum dari itu galás ko inga sang kotong pung Bos, ma dia pung hati sonde batúl, nanti Tuhan Allah hukum sang dia. Tagal, itu Tuhan Yesus pung badan deng Dia pung dara. Jadi kalo orang pung hati sonde batúl, na, dia sonde pantas makan deng minum di situ, te itu bekin hina sang Tuhan Yesus sa.<bt>Naa! Because of that, if there is a person who eats that bread and drink from that glass to remember our Bos, but his liver isn't right, God will punish him. Because, that is the Lord Yesus' body and His blood. So (consequently) if a person's liver isn't right, na, it is not appropriate for him/he is not worthy to eat and drink there, cuz (elaboration) that is treating the Lord Yesus with contempt.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="anaxíoos: in a way that dishonors"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">anaxíoos: in a way that dishonors the Lord, in a way that is not appropriate to fit in with the Lord's character NRSV: Whoever, therefore, eats the bread or drinks the cup of the Lord in an unworthy manner will be answerable for the body and blood of the Lord.<span class="Italic">(27)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="28" />Ada lebe bae, tiap orang pareksa dolo dia pung hati sandiri. Ais kalo dia yakin dia pung hati lurus, baru dia bisa makan itu roti, deng minum itu aer anggor.<bt>It is better for each person to first examine his own liver. Then if s/he is sure that his liver is straight/right/honest, only then can s/he eat that bread, and drink that wine.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="NRSV: Examine yourselves, and only then"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">NRSV: Examine yourselves, and only then eat of the bread and drink of the cup.</Message></Annotation><v n="29" />Ma ada orang yang makan deng minum deng hati yang sonde batúl. Te dong pikir bilang, &lt;&lt;Yesus pung mati tu, sonde ada pung arti apa-apa. Yesus pung badan sonde ada arti kasi sang beta.&gt;&gt; Naa, orang bagitu tanggong dong pung risiko sandiri, tagal nanti dong kaná hukum.<bt>But there are people who eat and drink with livers that are not right. Cuz (elaboration) they think that, &lt;&lt;That death of Yesus', has no meaning whatsoever. Yesus' body has no meaning for me.&gt;&gt; Naa, people like that bear/are responsible for their own risk, because they will get punished.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="to sooma: Christ's physical body, symbolized"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">to sooma: Christ's physical body, symbolized by the bread? or Christ's mystical body, the church? The former seems more likely since it's in a eucharistic context; Fee argues for the Church NRSV: For all who eat and drink without discerning the body, eat and drink judgment against themselves.<span class="Italic">(29)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="30" />Andia ko di bosong pung teng-tenga sana, ada yang sonde kuat, ada yang saki-saki, deng ada yang su mati.<bt>That is why among you there (remote), there are those who are not strong, there are those who are sickly, and there are those who have died.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="NRSV: For this reason many of"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">NRSV: For this reason many of you are weak and ill, and some have died.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="31" />Ma kalo kotong pareksa bae-bae kotong pung hati dolo, kotong sonde kaná hukum bagitu.<bt>But if we examine carefully our livers first, we-inc do not will not be punished like that.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="NRSV: But if we judged ourselves,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">NRSV: But if we judged ourselves, we would not be judged.</Message></Annotation><v n="32" />Kalo kotong pung Bos ada kasi hukum sang kotong, Dia bekin bagitu ko ajar sang kotong iko jalan yang batúl. Te Dia sonde mau kotong kaná hukum, deng nanti ancor abis sama-sama deng samua orang di ini dunya.<bt>If our-inc Bos punishes us, He does that to teach us to follow the right path. Cuz (elaboration) He doesn't want us to get punished, and then be destroyed together with everyone (else) on this earth.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="NRSV: But when we are judged"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">NRSV: But when we are judged by the Lord, we are disciplined so that we may not be condemned along with the world.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="33" />Jadi sodara sayang dong! Kalo bosong bakumpul ko makan di Tuhan pung meja, na, satu musti tunggu sang satu.<bt>So (consequently), dear siblings! If/when you are gathered together at God2's table, na, one must wait for the other.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="NRSV: So then, my brothers and"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">NRSV: So then, my brothers and sisters, when you come together to eat, wait for one another.</Message></Annotation><v n="34" />Kalo ada yang lapar talalu, na, lebe bae makan alas di ruma dolo. Ais nanti, kalo bosong bakumpul sama-sama, na, bosong jang kaná hukum.<bt>If there is someone who is excessively hungry, na, it would be better to eat a bit at home first. Then later, if/when you are gathered together, na, you will not get punished.</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">So'al parkara yang laen dong yang bosong ada tanya tu, nanti beta pi sana dolo, baru beta ator.<bt>Regarding other matters/disputes which you have asked about, later when I come there, only then will I handle them.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="NRSV: If you are hungry, eat"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">NRSV: If you are hungry, eat at home, so that when you come together, it will not be for your condemnation. About the other things I will give instructions when I come.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Tuhan pung Roh kasi kuasa sang kotong ko bekin tugas macam-macam<bt>God2's Spirit gives power to us-inc to do various sorts of jobs/responsibilities</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <c n="12" />
      <v n="1" />Sodara sayang dong! Beta mau ko bosong mangarti so'al itu kuasa deng karunya yang Tuhan pung Roh ada kasi sang kotong ko kotong pake.<bt>Dear siblings! I want you to understand about those power/s and unique.gifting/s which God2's Spirit has given us-inc for us to use.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="NRSV: Now concerning spiritual gifts, brothers"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">NRSV: Now concerning spiritual gifts, brothers and sisters, I do not want you to be uninformed.</Message></Annotation><v n="2" />Bosong su tau bilang, waktu bosong balóm jadi Tuhan pung orang dong, bosong maen basonggo barang-barang bisu. Bosong iko buta-buta sang dong.<bt>You-pl already know that when you were not yet God2's people, you used to trad.worship various things that were dumb (unable to speak). You followed/obeyed them blindly.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="NRSV: You know that when you"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">NRSV: You know that when you were pagans, you were enticed and led astray to idols that could not speak.</Message></Annotation><v n="3" />Tagal itu, beta mau ko bosong mangarti bilang, sonde mungkin ada orang yang ta'ika deng Tuhan pung Roh Barisi yang bilang, &lt;&lt;Kutuk sang Yesus tu!&gt;&gt; Deng sonde mungkin ada orang yang sonde ta'ika deng Tuhan pung Roh Barisi bilang, &lt;&lt;Yesus tu, beta pung Bos yang hak parenta sang beta!&gt;&gt;<bt>Because of that, I want for you to understand that, it is not possible for a person who is bound/linked to God2's Holy Spirit to say, &lt;&lt;Curses to Yesus!&gt;&gt; And it is not possible that there is someone who is not bound with God2's Holy Spirit who says, &lt;&lt;Yesus [+known info] is my Bos who has the say-so/ordering rights over me!&gt;&gt; [EXEG: (connector) The Gk uses a connector that is not high frequency, but is described by LN as ‘emphatic’, so the TEV &amp; CEV strategy of using no connector seems a bit of a cop out. The Ex.Summ. sources gloss this one all over the place. CR: “Each part/verse in itself is clear. It is just the connection between 2 &amp; 3. But since something about the situation puzzles everybody, a reasonable understanding is ok too.” If anyone compares with the Gk or the Indonesian TB, they will find we are using the closest parallel connector here.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Kutuk itu Yesus! @@Grammar"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z">Kutuk itu Yesus! @@Grammar</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="NRSV: Therefore I want you to"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">NRSV: Therefore I want you to understand that no one speaking by the Spirit of God ever says “Let Jesus be cursed!” and no one can say “Jesus is Lord” except by the Holy Spirit.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="4" />Tuhan pung Roh ada kasi orang satu-satu deng dia pung karunya, ko dong kasi jalan dong pung tugas laen-laen. Ma samua karunya dong, datang dari satu Roh.<bt>God's Spirit has given each person his/her own unique.gifting, so they carry out each of their different jobs/responsibilities. But all those unique.giftings, come from the same/one Spirit.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="charismatwn: (LN) gift, given graciously, freely"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">charismatwn: (LN) gift, given graciously, freely and generously; (fig: a bribe); a favour bestowed, earthly goods, privelege; (BADG) special gifts of a non-material sort bestowed by the grace of God on individual Christians; the gift of an office, mediated by the laying on of hands; the power to exercise the gift, the power to abstain from s.t.; spiritual gifts in a special sense; the power to fulfill the function; NRSV: Now there are varieties of gifts, but the same Spirit;<span class="Italic">(4)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="5" />Orang dapa karunya macam-macam ko layani orang, ma dong samua cuma dengar dari satu Bos sa.<bt>People get various sorts of unique.giftings to serve people, and all of them only hear/obey from the same/one Bos.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="diakonia: service, ministry, contribution, provision; assistance"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">diakonia: service, ministry, contribution, provision; assistance to do certain duties, (which are often menial) NRSV: and there are varieties of services, but the same Lord;<span class="Italic">(5)</span></Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Ada tugas macam-macam kasi sang Tuhan,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z">Ada tugas macam-macam kasi sang Tuhan, ma samua orang karjá dong cuma ada/dengar satu Bos sa / Bos satu sa.</Message></Annotation><v n="6" />Orang dapa tugas macam-macam ko kasi jalan Tuhan pung karjá, ma cuma Tuhan Allah, yang tolong sang dong ko kasi jalan itu tugas samua.<bt>People get various jobs/responsibilities to carry out God2's work, but only God is the one who helps them to carry out all those jobs.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="energjma: operations, work, function, deed, diversities"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">energjma: operations, work, function, deed, diversities of deeds NRSV: and there are varieties of activities, but it is the same God who activates all of them in everyone.<span class="Italic">(6)</span></Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Tuhan Allah bekin jadi banya macam"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z">Tuhan Allah bekin jadi banya macam hal dalam orang satu-satu pung idop, ma cuma ada satu Tuhan Allah sa yang bekin jadi kasi samua.</Message></Annotation><v n="7" />Tuhan kasi tunju Dia pung Roh di tiap orang pung idop deng cara beda-beda, ma dia pung maksud ko samua dapa ontong sama-sama.<bt>God2 shows/demonstrates His Spirit in each person's life in different ways (distributive), but the purpose is for all to get benefit/advantage together.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="NRSV: To each is given the"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">NRSV: To each is given the manifestation of the Spirit for the common good.</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Tuhan pung Roh ada kantara di"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z">Tuhan pung Roh ada kantara di tiap orang deng jalan/cara yang beda-beda, ma dia pung maksud ko samua dapa ontong sama-sama.</Message></Annotation><v n="8" />Dia kasi Dia pung Roh pung kuasa di Dia pung orang dong. Saparu tarima kuasa ko dong bisa pikir panjang, ais kasi nasiat yang pas. Saparu tarima kuasa ko kasi tau deng taráng, apa yang dong mangarti.<bt>He gives His Spirit's power/authority to His people. Some receive power so they can think long (wise, implications), and so give advice which fits (the situation). Some receive power to tell/explain clearly, what it is they understand.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="NRSV: To one is given through"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">NRSV: To one is given through the Spirit the utterance of wisdom, and to another the utterance of knowledge according to the same Spirit,</Message></Annotation><v n="9" />Saparu lai tarima kuasa ko parcaya kuat sang Tuhan Allah, tagal dong ta'ika bae-bae deng Dia pung Roh. Saparu lai tarima kuasa ko bekin bae orang saki.<bt>Some others receive power to believe strongly in God, because they are bound/linked tightly with His Spirit. Some others receive power to heal sick people.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="NRSV: to another faith by the"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">NRSV: to another faith by the same Spirit, to another gifts of healing by the one Spirit,</Message></Annotation><v n="10" />Saparu lai tarima kuasa ko bekin tanda heran macam-macam yang kasi tunju Tuhan Allah pung hebat. Saparu lai tarima kuasa ko kasi tau Tuhan pung pasán sang Dia pung orang dong. Saparu lai tarima kuasa ko dapa tau roh mana yang ba'akar di Tuhan Allah, deng yang mana yang sonde. Saparu lai tarima kuasa ko bisa omong pake bahasa macam-macam. Saparu lai tarima kuasa ko kasi tau itu bahasa dong pung arti apa.<bt>Some others receive power to do various sorts of *miracles (amazing signs) which show God's greatness/incredibleness. Some others receive power to tell God's message to His people. Some others receive power to be able to know which (of options) spirit is rooted in God, and which are not. Some others receive power so they can speak using various languages. [EXEG: Ex. Summaries, #4, keeps the options open, as in the Gk.] Some others, receive power to tell/explain what those languages/messages/words means.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="génee gloossóon: ecstatic speech -- not"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">génee gloossóon: ecstatic speech -- not normal speech with strange words in it, and probably not natural foreign languages in the ordinary sense, though in Acts 2:4,11 that is what it was. "Spesho kine language"? "language dat nobody can undastan"? NRSV: to another the working of miracles, to another prophecy, to another the discernment of spirits, to another various kinds of tongues, to another the interpretation of tongues.<span class="Italic">(10)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="11" />Ma cuma satu Roh yang bekin ko dong samua bisa bekin itu tugas dong. Dia kasi orang satu-satu ko dong mampu karjá iko Roh pung mau.<bt>But there is only one Spirit who makes it so they/enables them all can do those job/responsibilities (indirect causation). He gives to each person so they are able to work according to the Spirit's will.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="NRSV: All these are activated by"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">NRSV: All these are activated by one and the same Spirit, who allots to each one individually just as the Spirit chooses.</Message></Annotation><note reference="12:4-11" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Roma 12:6-8</note></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Satu badan, deng dia pung bagian macam-macam [\s2]<bt>One body, and its various parts</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="12" />Beta mau banding itu karunya dong deng orang pung badan. Satu badan pung bagian ada macam-macam. Ma itu bagian macam-macam tu, ta'ika jadi satu badan sa.<bt>I want to compare those unique.giftings with a person's body. One body has various parts. But those various parts are linked as just one body. [NOTE: karunya for higher level cohesion with previous section.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="NRSV: For just as the body"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">NRSV: For just as the body is one and has many members, and all the members of the body, though many, are one body, so it is with Christ.</Message></Annotation><note reference="12:12" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Roma 12:4-5</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Itu sama ke Kristus pung orang dong.<bt>That is the same as Kristus' people.</bt><v n="13" />Kotong samua ta'ika deng satu Roh. Andia ko waktu kotong dapa sarani, kotong jadi sama ke satu bangsa. Biar kotong orang Yahudi ko orang bukan Yahudi, orang budak ko orang bebas, Tuhan Allah kasi kotong samua satu Roh sa. Itu sama ke kotong samua minum aer yang bawa idop, dari parigi yang sama.<bt>We-inc are all linked with one Spirit. That is why when we were baptised, we became like one race/people group. Even though we-inc are Yahudi people or non Yahudi people, slave people or free people, God gives us all the one/same Spirit. That is like we all drink water that brings life from the same well. [EXEG: Nyland: The Source]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="NRSV: For in the one Spirit"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">NRSV: For in the one Spirit we were all baptized into one body-Jews or Greeks, slaves or free-and we were all made to drink of one Spirit.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="14" />Memang badan bukan cuma dari satu bagian sa. Te dia jadi dari banya bagian.<bt>It is true that the body is not just from one part. Cuz (elaboration) it happens/comes to be what it is from many parts.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="jadi = sense here of &quot;consists"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z">jadi = sense here of "consists of" &gt; dictionary</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="mélos: part of the body NRSV:"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">mélos: part of the body NRSV: Indeed, the body does not consist of one member but of many.<span class="Italic">(14)</span></Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Memang, badan anteru sonde jadi cuma"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z">Memang, badan anteru sonde jadi cuma dari satu bagian sa. Ma dari banya bagian.</Message></Annotation><v n="15" />Andekata lu pung kaki bilang, &lt;&lt;Beta ni, bukan tangan. Jadi beta sonde jadi bagian dari lu pung badan.&gt;&gt; Biar dia omong bagitu, ma dia masi bagian dari lu pung badan. Batúl, to?<bt>If perchance [+hypothetical] your-sg foot said, &lt;&lt;I here, am not a hand. So (consequently), I am not a part of your body.&gt;&gt; Even if it spoke like that, nevertheless it is still a part of your body. That's correct, right?</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="NRSV: If the foot would say,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">NRSV: If the foot would say, “Because I am not a hand, I do not belong to the body,” that would not make it any less a part of the body.</Message></Annotation><v n="16" />Deng kalo lu pung talinga bilang, &lt;&lt;Beta ni, bukan mata. Jadi beta sonde jadi bagian dari lu pung badan.&gt;&gt; Biar dia omong bagitu, ma dia masi bagian dari lu pung badan.<bt>And if your ear said, &lt;&lt;I here, am not an eye. So (consequently), I am not a part of your body.&gt;&gt; Even if it spoke like that, nevertheless it is still a part of your body.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="NRSV: And if the ear would"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">NRSV: And if the ear would say, “Because I am not an eye, I do not belong to the body,” that would not make it any less a part of the body.</Message></Annotation><v n="17" />Pikir doo! Kalo lu pung badan cuma jadi satu mata sa, karmana ko lu bisa dapa dengar? Deng kalo lu pung badan cuma jadi satu talinga sa, karmana ko lu bisa dapa ciom bau?<bt>Think first! If your body was only one eye, how it is that you would be able to hear? And if your body was only one ear, how is it that you would be able to smell smells [NOTE: object required to disambiguate senses /ciom/ 1) smell, 2) kiss]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="NRSV: If the whole body were"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">NRSV: If the whole body were an eye, where would the hearing be? If the whole body were hearing, where would the sense of smell be?</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="18" />Ma bosong su tau, Tuhan Allah bekin sang kotong jadi sama ke satu badan, deng Dia ator dia pung bagian macam-macam, iko Dia pung model.<bt>But you already know, God makes us become like one body, and He arranges/regulates/controls each of the parts, according to His type/pattern/characteristic. [NOTE to daughter translations: this sense of /model/ in KM may create noise. Keep in mind that the Gk here is ‘as he chose’; try -- iko Dia pung mau OR iko Dia pung putusan.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="NRSV: But as it is, God"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">NRSV: But as it is, God arranged the members in the body, each one of them, as he chose.</Message></Annotation><v n="19" />Kalo kotong pung badan cuma jadi satu macam bagian, dia pung nama su bukan &lt;badan&gt; lai, to?<bt>If our-inc bodies were only one part, it's name is no longer &lt;body&gt;, right?</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="NRSV: If all were a single"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">NRSV: If all were a single member, where would the body be?</Message></Annotation><v n="20" />Ma dia pung batúl, kotong pung badan ada pung bagian macam-macam. Itu yang bekin dia jadi satu badan anteru.<bt>But in truth, our bodies have various parts. That is what makes it be one whole body.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="NRSV: As it is, there are"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">NRSV: As it is, there are many members, yet one body.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="21" />Orang pung mata sonde bisa anggap reme sang itu orang pung tangan bilang, &lt;&lt;Beta sonde parlú sang lu!&gt;&gt; Deng orang pung kapala sonde bisa kasi tau sang itu orang pung kaki bilang, &lt;&lt;Beta sonde butu sang lu!&gt;&gt;<bt>A person's eye cannot view disparagingly/condescendingly that person's hand saying, &lt;&lt;I don't need you-sg!&gt;&gt; And a person's head can't tell that person's foot saying, &lt;&lt;I don't need2 you!&gt;&gt; [NOTE: high level speaker attitude from Fee &amp; Ex. Summ, plus context.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="butu = BI, KM?? reme"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z">butu = BI, KM?? reme</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="NRSV: The eye cannot say to"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">NRSV: The eye cannot say to the hand, “I have no need of you,” nor again the head to the feet, “I have no need of you.”</Message></Annotation><v n="22" />Dia pung batúl, andia, ada badan pung bagian yang kotong anggap sonde kuat deng sonde pantíng, ma kotong masi parlú sang dong.<bt>What is true, is that, there are parts of the body which we-inc consider/view as not strong and not important, but we still need them.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="NRSV: On the contrary, the members"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">NRSV: On the contrary, the members of the body that seem to be weaker are indispensable,</Message></Annotation><v n="23" />Ada bagian yang kotong anggap dong pung guna cuma sadiki sa, ma kotong masi piara bae-bae sang dong. Deng ada bagian yang kotong malu kasi tunju, ais kotong tutu bae-bae sang dong.<bt>There are parts that we consider/view as only having a little use, but we still care for them well. And there are part which we are embarrased to show, so we cover them up carefully.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="NRSV: and those members of the"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">NRSV: and those members of the body that we think less honorable we clothe with greater honor, and our less respectable members are treated with greater respect;</Message></Annotation><v n="24" />Ma kalo bagian yang sonde bekin malu sang kotong, kotong sonde bekin apa-apa sang dong.<bt>But if there is a part which doesn't make us ashamed, we don't do anything to them.</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Ma Tuhan Allah kumpul samua bagian ko bekin jadi satu badan. Ais Dia ator ko bagian yang kotong anggap sonde pantíng, kotong ju piara bae-bae sang dong,<bt>But God has gathered/collected all the parts to make one body. So He has arranged so the parts which we consider not important, we also care for them well,</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="NRSV: whereas our more respectable members"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">NRSV: whereas our more respectable members do not need this. But God has so arranged the body, giving the greater honor to the inferior member,</Message></Annotation><v n="25" />te Dia sonde suka kotong pung badan tabagi-bagi. Dia mau ko samua bagian, satu balia deng satu.<bt>cuz (elaboration) He doesn't like out bodies to be split up/separated (into unconnected parts). He wants for all parts, one to mutually look after the other.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="balia = look after, take care"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z">balia = look after, take care of</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="NRSV: that there may be no"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">NRSV: that there may be no dissension within the body, but the members may have the same care for one another.</Message></Annotation><v n="26" />Te kalo satu bagian dapa susa, na, samua ju rasa. Deng kalo satu ada tarima hormat, na, samua ju iko sanáng.<bt>Cuz (elaboration) if one part gets trouble, na, all (the rest) also feel/experience. And if one is receiving honour/respect, na, all (the rest) also accompany/participate in happiness with it.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="doksazetai: is exalted, not in the"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">doksazetai: is exalted, not in the sense of hype or good press. But what is the exact sense here? NRSV: If one member suffers, all suffer together with it; if one member is honored, all rejoice together with it.<span class="Italic">(26)</span></Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="27" />Bagitu ju deng bosong. Te bosong sama ke Kristus pung badan anteru. Tiap orang parcaya jadi sama ke satu bagian dari Kristus pung badan.<bt>It is the same way also with you. Cuz (elaboration) you-pl are like Kristus' whole body. Each believing person is like one part of Kristus' body.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="NRSV: Now you are the body"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">NRSV: Now you are the body of Christ and individually members of it.</Message></Annotation><v n="28" />Te di orang parcaya dong pung teng-tenga, Tuhan Allah kasi kuasa ko bekin tugas macam-macam.<bt>Cuz (elaboration) in the midst of the believers, God gives power/authority to do various sorts of tasks/responsibilities.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Partama, Dia utus orang saparu pi jalan kasi tau Dia pung pasán.<bt>First, He commissions some people to go tell His message.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Kadua, Dia pake orang saparu jadi Dia pung jubir.<bt>Second, He uses some people as His *prophets (spokespeople).</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Katiga, Dia bekin orang saparu pintar ajar orang so'al Dia.<bt>Third, He makes some people skilled in teaching people about Him.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Tarús, Dia kasi kuasa sang orang saparu ko bisa bekin tanda heran macam-macam ko kasi tunju Dia pung hebat.<bt>Then2, He gives power to some people so they can do various sorts of miracles to show His greatness/incredibleness.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Saparu lai dapa kuasa ko bekin bae orang saki.<bt>Some others get power to heal sick people.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Saparu lai dapa karunya ko tolong orang.<bt>Some others get unique.gifting to help people.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Saparu lai dapa karunya ko bisa urus orang ko dong karjá sama-sama deng bae.<bt>Some others get unique.gifting to be able to manage/organise people so they can work together well.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Deng Dia kasi kuasa sang orang saparu lai, ko dong bisa omong pake bahasa macam-macam.<bt>And He gives power to some other people, so they can speak using various sorts of languages. [LEX: Gk. génee gloossóon: see note on Verse 10]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="génee gloossóon: see note on Verse"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">génee gloossóon: see note on Verse 10 NRSV: And God has appointed in the church first apostles, second prophets, third teachers; then deeds of power, then gifts of healing, forms of assistance, forms of leadership, various kinds of tongues.<span class="Italic">(28)</span></Message></Annotation><note reference="12:28" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Efesus 4:11</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="29" />Naa, bosong pung pikir karmana? Tuhan Allah utus samua orang ko jalan pi kasi tau Dia pung pasán, ko? Sonde. Dia bekin samua orang jadi Dia pung jubir, ko? Sonde. Dia bekin samua orang pintar mangajar, ko? Sonde. Dia kasi kuasa sang samua orang ko bisa bekin tanda heran, ko? Sonde.<bt>Naa, what are you-pl thinking? Does God commission everyone to go tell His message, or (what)? No. Does He make everyone become His spokesperson, or (what)? No. Does He make everyone skilled in teaching, or (what)? No. Does He give pwer to everyone so they can do miracles, or (what)? No.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="NRSV: Are all apostles? Are all"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">NRSV: Are all apostles? Are all prophets? Are all teachers? Do all work miracles?</Message></Annotation><v n="30" />Dia kasi kuasa sang samua orang ko bekin bae orang saki, ko? Sonde. Dia bekin samua orang bisa omong pake bahasa macam-macam, ko? Sonde. Dia bekin samua orang bisa kasi tau itu bahasa dong pung arti, ko? Sonde.<bt>Does He give power to everyone so they can heal the sick, or (what)? No. Does He make everyone able to speak using various languages, or (what)? No. Does He make everyone able to tell the meaning of those languages, or (what)? No.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="NRSV: Do all possess gifts of"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">NRSV: Do all possess gifts of healing? Do all speak in tongues? Do all interpret?</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="31" />Naa! Bosong musti siap sadia ko tarima deng pake karunya yang lebe barguna kasi banya orang dong.<bt>Naa! You-pl must always be prepared to receive and use the unique.giftings which are more useful for many people. [EXEG: Ex. Summ: they can have an earnest desire for them and prepare themselves to receive them; collectively, not individually]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="siap sadia = always be ready,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z">siap sadia = always be ready, be prepared for/be preparing selves for</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="zeelóute: either &quot;go all out&quot; or"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">zeelóute: either "go all out" or "you are doing your best"</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Biar bagitu, ma beta masi mau kasi tunju sang bosong jalan yang paling bae.<bt>Even that being the case, nevertheless I still want to show you-pl a way that is the best.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="NRSV: But strive for the greater"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">NRSV: But strive for the greater gifts. And I will show you a still more excellent way.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Kasi-sayang yang batúl<bt>True love (doublet)</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <c n="13" />
      <v n="1" />Andekata beta bisa ba'omong pake samua macam bahasa, bahasa manusia ko, bahasa dari Tuhan pung ana bua dari sorga ko, ma beta sonde ada pung sayang sadiki ju, dia pung ontong apa? Beta pung omong tu, kosong sa, sama ke gong yang cuma babunyi-babunyi, ko daróm yang babunyi pung-pang pung-pang sa.<bt>If perchance (hypothetical) I could speak using all kinds of languages, (such as) human language or, language from God2's angels or, (whatever), but I don't have even a little love, what good/benefit/advantage is it? What I have to say is just empty, like a gong that just keeps making noise, or a barrel that just sounds pung-pang pung-pang (onomotopoeia).</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="babunyi-babunyi = just making noise ;"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z">babunyi-babunyi = just making noise ; drom ~ daróm ; pung-pang = sound of (really) loud music, like bemo, with a beat, but erratic. ;</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="eàn: several of the &quot;if&quot;s in"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">eàn: several of the "if"s in Verses 1-3 are things that weren't part of Paul's experience, like letting his body be burned up. So it needs to sound very hypothetical -- "supposing this were the case with somebody, even though it really isn't". You can imagine somebody somewhere doing that, and if you should find such a person, he or she would still need to love. It's not just talking about Paul "I" used as generic?<span class="Italic">(1) (1) </span>kalchòs: not a brass wind instrument, but an instrument you strike with something to make a noise. Could be like a gong in a Buddhist temple, or some kind of bell eechóon: making a noise, used for both the ringing of a brass gong and the roar of the surf. The idea may be that after the noise is gone, what do you have left? Nothing<span class="Italic">(1) (1) </span>kýmbalon: cymbal, the kind you hit two of them together, as in a marching band or a drum set NRSV: If I speak in the tongues of mortals and of angels, but do not have love, I am a noisy gong or a clanging cymbal.<span class="Italic">(1)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="2" />Andekata beta ada pung karunya ko kasi tau Tuhan pung pasán sang Dia pung orang, deng beta tau samua rahasia, deng beta mangarti samua hal orang yang pintar dong tau, deng kalo beta pung parcaya sang Tuhan kuat sampe beta bisa kasi pinda gunung dong, ma beta sonde ada pung sayang sadiki ju, dia pung guna apa? Samua yang beta bekin sonde ada pung guna apa-apa.<bt>If perchance I had a unique.gifting to tell God2's message to His people, and I knew all secrets, and I understood everything that knowledgeable people know, and if my faith in God2 is strong to the point that I am able to move mountains, but I don't have even a little love, what use is it? What I do has no use whatsoever. [NOTE to daughter translations: in Kupang /orang pintar/ = dukun, suanggi; /orang yang pintar/ = knowledgeable people; CHECK that your language doesn't have a parallel problem.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="NRSV: And if I have prophetic"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">NRSV: And if I have prophetic powers, and understand all mysteries and all knowledge, and if I have all faith, so as to remove mountains, but do not have love, I am nothing.</Message></Annotation><note reference="13:2" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Mateos 17:20, 21:21, Markus 11:23</note><v n="3" />Kalo beta jual abis beta pung harta, ais bagi kasi dia pung doi samua ko kasi makan orang malarat dong, ko, sarakan beta pung badan jadi korban,<bt>If I sell off my belongings, and then divide up all its money to give food to the poor/destitute people, or hand over/surrender my body as a sacrifice,</bt><note reference="13:3" class="Note General Paragraph" usfm="f">Ada tulisan bahasa Yunani saparu yang tulis tamba bilang, &lt;&lt;sarakan beta pung badan jadi korban bakar&gt;&gt;.<bt>There are some Yunani language writings which write additionally saying, “hand over/surrender my body as a burnt sacrifice,”</bt></note>ma beta sonde ada pung sayang sadiki ju, dia pung guna apa? Beta sonde ada dasar ko angka-angka diri ju. Te itu parcuma sa! Sonde ada ontong.<bt>but I don't have even a little love, what use is it? I have not basis/reason for elevating myself/boasting. Cuz (elaboration) it's pointless/in vain! There is no benefit/advantage.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="psoomísoo: dole out food a little"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">psoomísoo: dole out food a little bit at a time, feed somebody NRSV: If I give away all my possessions, and if I hand over my body so that I may boast, but do not have love, I gain nothing.<span class="Italic">(3)</span></Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">
      <v n="4" />Te sayang tu, manis.<bt>Cuz (elaboration) love is sweet (kind). [DISCOURSE: Reordered so first point is broader]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="chreesteúetai: is good or useful or"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">chreesteúetai: is good or useful or kind</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Sayang tu, sabar.<bt>Love is patient.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="makrothumew: patient, forbearing, slow to anger,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">makrothumew: patient, forbearing, slow to anger, patience of injuries without paying back, opposite of quick-tempered, long-suffering</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Dia sonde tau camburu.<bt>It does not know how to be jealous.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Dia sonde tau angka-angka diri.<bt>It does not know how to elevate itself/boast.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Dia sonde tau sombong.<bt>It does not know how to be arrogant.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="NRSV: Love is patient; love is"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">NRSV: Love is patient; love is kind; love is not envious or boastful or arrogant</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">
      <v n="5" />Dia sonde kasar.<bt>It is not coarse/rude/crude.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="ascheemonéi: get out of line --"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">ascheemonéi: get out of line -- not talking about etiquette, but your whole behavior</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Dia sonde mau manáng sandiri.<bt>It doesn't want/try to win themselves (insist on its own way).</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Dia sonde gampang mara.<bt>It does not get mad easily.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Dia sonde tau simpan hati.<bt>It does not store liver (resentment/hate).</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="logízetai tò kakón: does not keep"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">logízetai tò kakón: does not keep accounts of wrong NRSV: or rude. It does not insist on its own way; it is not irritable or resentful;<span class="Italic">(5)</span></Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">
      <v n="6" />Dia sanáng deng apa yang batúl,<bt>It is happy/pleased with what is right,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 3" usfm="q3">deng sonde suka hal yang sonde adil.<bt>and doesn't like things that are not just/fair.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="adikíaai: things that are not right,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">adikíaai: things that are not right, evil NRSV: it does not rejoice in wrongdoing, but rejoices in the truth.<span class="Italic">(6)</span></Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">
      <v n="7" />Sayang tu, tahan banting.<bt>Love endures abuse/suffering.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="stegw: bear, endure, quietly suffering afflictions,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">stegw: bear, endure, quietly suffering afflictions, self-control, stand</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Dia parcaya tarús.<bt>It keeps trusting.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="pisteuw: believe, ready to allow for"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">pisteuw: believe, ready to allow for circumstances and see the best in others</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Dia baharap tarús.<bt>It keeps hoping. [NOTE to daughter translations: even in Kupang, /baharap/ usually has to be fleshed out with a direct (e.g. hoping for the best in the other) or indirect object; here it works because of the structure of the context, but probably wouldn't if it was removed from context. Check your language carefully.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="elpidzw: hopes, expects what is our"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">elpidzw: hopes, expects what is our best from our brothers and fellow men, confidence about the future attainment of our goals, refusal to take failure as final, confidence about ultimate triumph by God's grace</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Dia batahan tarús.<bt>It keeps lasting.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="hupomenw: remain, stand one's ground, hold"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">hupomenw: remain, stand one's ground, hold out, endure (in trouble) NRSV: It bears all things, believes all things, hopes all things, endures all things.<span class="Italic">(7)</span></Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">
      <v n="8" />Deng sayang sonde tau barenti.<bt>And love never stops.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="píptei: never ends, in contrast with"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">píptei: never ends, in contrast with the other things in the verse that aren't going to be around very long</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Ma apa yang Tuhan pung jubir dong kasi tau, lama-lama sonde parlú lai. Deng kalo orang omong pake bahasa macam-macam, lama-lama ju sonde parlú lai. Deng kalo apa yang orang pintar dong tau, lama-lama ju sonde ada pung guna lai.<bt>But the things that God2's spokespeople made known, will eventually not be needed anymore. And if a person speaks using various kinds of languages, eventually they won't be needed anymore either. And as for the things that knowledgable people know, eventually they will have no more use.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="glóossai: probably the ecstatic speech of"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">glóossai: probably the ecstatic speech of 12:28 and 30, not the ordinary languages of 13:1 katargeetheésetai: be done for, no need, or maybe even that it will be put out of business because we will know so much more, like Einstein came up with a better explanation of the law of gravity than Newton was able to figure out<span class="Italic">(8) (8) </span>NRSV: Love never ends. But as for prophecies, they will come to an end; as for tongues, they will cease; as for knowledge, it will come to an end.</Message></Annotation><v n="9" />Sakarang kotong cuma mangarti sadiki sa. Kalo kotong jadi Tuhan pung jubir, kotong cuma kasi tau hal yang balóm langkáp.<bt>Now we only understand a little. If we are God2's spokespeople, we only make known things which are not yet complete.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="NRSV: For we know only in"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">NRSV: For we know only in part, and we prophesy only in part;</Message></Annotation><v n="10" />Ma sampe dia pung waktu, nanti samua jadi langkáp. Itu waktu, hal-hal yang sonde langkáp, ju sonde ada pung guna lai.<bt>But when it comes to the right/appropriate time, everything will become complete. At that time, things that are not complete, will also not have use anymore. [NOTE: needs to make sense in conjunction w/vs.11ff]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Different views: 1. heaven, (however not"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z">Different views: 1. heaven, (however not mentioned in 1 Cor to now) 2. canon complete, 3. when Christians are mature in their faith. 4. when these people are practising all the gifts with love</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="katargeetheésetai: be done for, no need,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">katargeetheésetai: be done for, no need, or maybe even that it will be put out of business because we will know so much more, like Einstein came up with a better explanation of the law of gravity than Newton was able to figure out (same word as in Verse 8) NRSV: but when the complete comes, the partial will come to an end.<span class="Italic">(10)</span></Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="11" />Conto bagini: waktu beta masi kici ana, beta ba'omong sama ke ana kici dong biasa ba'omong. Beta ju pikir sama ke ana kici biasa bapikir. Ma sakarang beta su jadi bésar. Andia ko beta sonde batingka sama ke ana kici lai.<bt>An example is like this: when I was still a small child, I spoke like small children normally speak. I also thought like small children normally think. But now I am big/grown. That is why I don't behave like a small child anymore.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="batingka = 1) berkelakuan, (bertindak), kelakuan"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z">batingka = 1) berkelakuan, (bertindak), kelakuan 2) sama ke, seperti ;</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="NRSV: When I was a child,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">NRSV: When I was a child, I spoke like a child, I thought like a child, I reasoned like a child; when I became an adult, I put an end to childish ways.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="12" />Conto laen lai: sakarang kotong bisa dapa lia sadiki, ma balóm jalás, sama ke lia pake carmín yang rusak. Ma lama-lama nanti samua jadi jalás. Kotong dapa lia sama ke ada pas di muka idong. Sakarang beta cuma mangarti sadiki sa. Ma lama-lama nanti beta bisa mangarti samua, sama ke yang Tuhan Allah mangarti samua-samua so'al beta pung diri.<bt>Another example: now we-inc are able to see a little, but (things are) not clear, just like looking using a broken mirror. But eventually everything will become clear. We will be able to see just like it is right in front of our nose. Now I only understand a little. But eventually I will be able to understand everything, just like God understands everything about my being.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="peot"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z">peot</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="ainigma: 1) indistinct visual image, 2)"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">ainigma: 1) indistinct visual image, 2) difficult or impossible to understand, puzzling NRSV: For now we see in a mirror, dimly, but then we will see face to face. Now I know only in part; then I will know fully, even as I have been fully known.<span class="Italic">(12)</span></Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="13" />Jadi sakarang ada tiga hal yang kotong musti bekin, yang batahan tarús. Andia:<bt>So (consequently), there are three things which we must do, which keep lasting. They are:</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">kotong musti parcaya tarús sang Tuhan;<bt>we-inc must keep believing in God2;</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">kotong musti baharap tarús bilang, nanti Dia ator samua jadi bae;<bt>we must keep hoping that, He will arrange everything to (eventually) come out good/well; (indirect causation) [NOTE to daughter translations: we UNSed this stopping at /baharap tarús/; UNS's said "hope we get things /barang/"; problem is in Kupang and most lgs in Timor/Maluku, /baharap/ or its equivalent normally needs a direct object (believe what) or indirect object (believe in who); this explication is similar to HCE but adds God in an agentive role. Don't overtranslate this well-known passage if the lg or UNS responses don't require it.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="kotong musti baharap tarús, bilang, nanti"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z">kotong musti baharap tarús, bilang, nanti Dia ator samua jadi bae;</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">deng kotong musti basayang tarús.<bt>and we must keep loving (each other).</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Dari tiga hal ni, yang paling pantíng, andia, <span class="Italic">sayang.</span> Te sayang yang paling bae dari samua.<bt>From these three things here, the most important one is <span class="Italic">love</span>. Cuz (elaboration) love is the best of all.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="NRSV: And now faith, hope, and"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">NRSV: And now faith, hope, and love abide, these three; and the greatest of these is love.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Tuhan pung Roh kasi tugas laen-laen sang Dia pung orang dong<bt>God2's Spirit gives various different job/responsibilities to His people</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <c n="14" />
      <v n="1" />Usaha ko basayang dalam samua hal. Te sonde ada hal laen yang lebe pantíng lai. Deng cari jalan ju ko Tuhan pung Roh kasi bosong kuasa deng karunya ko bosong bisa bekin hal-hal yang bae. Deng yang bagus, andia, kalo bosong dapa karunya ko kasi tau Tuhan pung pasán.<bt>Make an effort to mutually love in all matters. Cuz (elaboration) there is nothing else which is more important. And also look for ways so God2's Spirit will give you-pl power and unique.gifting so you can do good things. And what is really good, is, if you get unique.gifting to tell God2's message. [EXEG: connector: Gk has overt connector, so “And also” added from CR Amarasi 2014]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="zeeloute NRSV: Pursue love and strive"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">zeeloute NRSV: Pursue love and strive for the spiritual gifts, and especially that you may prophesy.<span class="Italic">(1)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="2" />Te kalo orang ada pung karunya ko omong pake bahasa laen, Tuhan pung Roh ada kasi dia kuasa ko kasi tau hal yang balóm jalás. Ma dia sonde omong deng orang laen, te dia cuma omong deng Tuhan sa. Sonde ada orang yang bakumpul di situ, yang mangarti itu orang pung omong tu.<bt>Cuz (elaboration) if a person has a unique.gifting to speak using other language/s, God2's Spirit has/is giving him power to tell/explain/make known things that are not yet clear. But he doesn't speak with other people, cuz (elaboration) he is only speaking with God2. There is nobody gathered there who understands what that person is saying.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="NRSV: For those who speak in"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">NRSV: For those who speak in a tongue do not speak to other people but to God; for nobody understands them, since they are speaking mysteries in the Spirit.</Message></Annotation><v n="3" />Ma kalo orang ada pung karunya ko kasi tau Tuhan pung pasán tu, dia ada kasi pasán sang samua orang di situ. Dia kasi bangun orang pung parcaya sang Tuhan, kasi kuat dong pung hati, deng hibur orang yang susa dong.<bt>But if a person has a unique.gifting to tell God2's message, he is giving the message to all the people there. He is building people's faith in God2, strengthening their livers (encourage), and comforting those in difficulty/strife.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="paramythían: consolation, comfort. UBS suggests it"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">paramythían: consolation, comfort. UBS suggests it means fostering good spirit among the Christian community, which sounds like cheerleading. But in the papyri it's mainly used for situations where somebody is sad or deprived or lonesome, to make them feel better NRSV: On the other hand, those who prophesy speak to other people for their upbuilding and encouragement and consolation.<span class="Italic">(3)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="4" />Orang yang omong pake bahasa laen, dia kasi kuat dia pung diri sa. Ma orang yang omong kasi tau Tuhan pung pasán, dia kasi kuat samua orang yang ada bakumpul, ko jama'at anteru jadi lebe kuat.<bt>A person who speaks using other languages, he just strengthens himself. But a person who speaks telling/explaining God2's message, he strengthens everyone who is gathered, so the who congregation becomes stronger.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="NRSV: Those who speak in a"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">NRSV: Those who speak in a tongue build up themselves, but those who prophesy build up the church.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="5" />Beta pung suka ko bosong samua bisa omong pake bahasa laen. Ma beta lebe suka ko bosong bisa omong kasi tau Tuhan pung pasán. Te orang yang omong kasi tau Tuhan pung pasán, lebe barguna dari orang yang cuma omong pake bahasa laen. Kalo omong pake bahasa laen, itu ju bae, asal ada orang yang bisa kasi tau itu bahasa pung arti. Deng bagitu, itu pasán bisa bekin lebe kuat samua orang di jama'at, ko dong bisa mangarti.<bt>My liking is for all of you to be able to speak in other languages. But I would like it even better for you to be able to speak telling/explaining God2's message. Cuz (elaboration) the person who is telling God2's message, if more useful that the person who is merely speaking using other languages. I (we) speak using other languages, that is good, as long as there is a person who can tell the meaning of that language/message. In that way, that message can strengthen everyone in the congregation, so they can understand.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="NRSV: Now I would like all"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">NRSV: Now I would like all of you to speak in tongues, but even more to prophesy. One who prophesies is greater than one who speaks in tongues, unless someone interprets, so that the church may be built up.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="6" />Sodara sayang dong! Pikir coba ini hal. Andekata beta datang di bosong, ais beta omong pake bahasa yang bosong sonde mangarti, bosong dapa dia pung ontong apa? Sonde ada, to? Ma kalo beta omong kasi bosong, ada lebe bae kalo beta kasi tau Tuhan pung mau. Lebe bae beta buka hal yang dolu sonde jalás. Lebe bae beta tolong sang bosong ko mangarti hal deng lebe bae lai. Lebe bae beta kasi inga Tuhan pung Kata-kata. Lebe bae beta ajar sang bosong. Itu, baru ada pung guna kasi sang bosong, to?<bt>Dear siblings! Have a think about these things. If perchance [+hypothetical] I come to you, and then I speak using a language that you don't understand, what benefit/advantage do you get? There isn't any, right? But if I speak to you-pl, it is better if I tell/explain God2's will. It is better if I reveal things that were previously not clear. It is better if I help you to understand things even better. It is better if I remind you about God2's Words. It is better if I teach you. Only then is it useful for you, right? [NOTE: verse on effective communication.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="NRSV: Now, brothers and sisters, if"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">NRSV: Now, brothers and sisters, if I come to you speaking in tongues, how will I benefit you unless I speak to you in some revelation or knowledge or prophecy or teaching?</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="7" />Bagitu ju deng alat musik dong. Te dong sonde idop, ma dong ada bekin bunyi macam-macam. Pake suling ko, sasando ko, gitar ko, kalo dia pung not sonde roba, tantu orang sonde bisa tau dia ada maen lagu mana, aa?<bt>It's like that with musical instruments. Cuz (elaboration) they are not alive, but they are making various sorts of noises. Wheter (you) are using a flute or, sasando or, guitar or (whatever), if its note does not change, people will certainly not be able to know which song it is playing, right?</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="NRSV: It is the same way"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">NRSV: It is the same way with lifeless instruments that produce sound, such as the flute or the harp. If they do not give distinct notes, how will anyone know what is being played?</Message></Annotation><v n="8" />Deng kalo tarompet bekin bunyi yang sonde jalás, karmana ko tantara dong bisa tau dia pung sein ko dong siap-siap baparáng? Sonde bisa, to?<bt>And if a trumpet makes a sound that is not clear, how will the solders be able to know the signal/indication so they can get ready to attack/war? They can't, right?</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="ádeelon: indistinct, not clearly hearable NRSV:"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">ádeelon: indistinct, not clearly hearable NRSV: And if the bugle gives an indistinct sound, who will get ready for battle?<span class="Italic">(8)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="9" />Bagitu ju kasi bosong. Kalo bosong omong pake bahasa laen, ko, pake bahasa yang orang sonde bisa mangarti deng jalás, itu sama ke bosong ada omong deng angin sa. Parcuma sa, te orang sonde bisa tangkap lu pung maksud!<bt>It's the same way also with you-pl. I you speak using other languages, or, use a language/words/speech that people cannot understand clearly, that is like you are just speaking with the wind. It's pointless/useless/in vain, cuz people can't catch your intent/purpose/meaning!</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="NRSV: So with yourselves; if in"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">NRSV: So with yourselves; if in a tongue you utter speech that is not intelligible, how will anyone know what is being said? For you will be speaking into the air.</Message></Annotation><v n="10" />Ada talalu banya macam bahasa di ini dunya. Tiap bahasa ada dia pung arti sandiri-sandiri.<bt>There are too many/so many kinds of languages in this world. Each language has its own (individual) meaning.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="aphoonon: without meaning, without the capability"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">aphoonon: without meaning, without the capability of expression (used actively of Balaam's donkey) NRSV: There are doubtless many different kinds of sounds in the world, and nothing is without sound.<span class="Italic">(10)</span></Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Deng sonde ada satu bahasa ju"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z">Deng sonde ada satu bahasa ju yang sonde ada dia pung arti.</Message></Annotation><v n="11" />Ma kalo beta sonde tau orang laen pung bahasa, itu sonde ada pung arti apa-apa kasi sang beta. Beta sonde mangarti sang dong, deng dong ju sonde mangarti sang beta. Botong satu deng satu jadi orang asing.<bt>[EXEG: NLT] But if I don't know another person's/other people's language, it has no meaning whatsoever for me. I don't understand them, and they also don't understand me. We are strangers/foreigners to each other.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="NRSV: If then I do not"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">NRSV: If then I do not know the meaning of a sound, I will be a foreigner to the speaker and the speaker a foreigner to me.</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Ma kasi beta yang sonde tau"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z">Ma kasi beta yang sonde tau dong pung bahasa, dong sonde ada pung arti apa-apa.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="12" />Bagitu ju deng bosong. Bosong mau dapa kuasa deng karunya dari Tuhan. Itu bae. Ma ada lebe bae bosong usaha ko dapa kuasa deng karunya yang bosong bisa pake ko tolong bekin kuat orang parcaya bam-banya dong!<bt>It's the same way also with you-pl. You want to get power and unique.gifting from God2. That is good. But it would be better for you to make an effort to get power and unique.gifting which you can use to help strengthen many believers!</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="NRSV: So with yourselves; since you"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">NRSV: So with yourselves; since you are eager for spiritual gifts, strive to excel in them for building up the church.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="13" />Jadi orang yang omong pake bahasa laen, ada lebe bae kalo dia sambayang minta ko Tuhan ju kasi dia karunya ko bisa kasi tau itu bahasa laen pung arti.<bt>So (consequently), a person who speaks using a different language, it is/would be better if s/he prays asking God2 to also give him unique.gifting so s/he can explain the meaning of that different language.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="NRSV: Therefore, one who speaks in"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">NRSV: Therefore, one who speaks in a tongue should pray for the power to interpret.</Message></Annotation><v n="14" />Kalo beta ada sambayang pake bahasa laen, beta sambayang pake beta pung hati, ma beta sonde mangarti beta omong apa.<bt>If I am praying using a different language, I pray using my liver, but I don't understand what I am saying. [EXEG: NLT]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="CHECK does phrase &quot;using my brain&quot;"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z">CHECK does phrase "using my brain" mean "think harder about something difficult"?? That seems to be what one UNS understood who said "If I pray in my own language I don't have to use my brain, just my liver. But if I try to pray in English I have to use my brain." --which is opposite from what is intended in vs. 14; end of vs.14 in NLT is a good way out. "but I don't understand what I am saying."</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="NRSV: For if I pray in"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">NRSV: For if I pray in a tongue, my spirit prays but my mind is unproductive.</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Kalo beta ada sambayang pake bahasa"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z">Kalo beta ada sambayang pake bahasa laen, beta ada sambayang pake beta pung hati, ma beta sonde sambayang pake beta pung otak.</Message></Annotation><v n="15" />Jadi dia pung bae, beta bekin karmana? Beta pake dua-dua, ma satu-satu deng dia pung waktu. Beta mau sambayang pake beta pung hati. Deng beta ju mau sambayang pake kata-kata yang beta mangarti. Beta mau manyanyi lagu puji sang Tuhan pake beta pung hati. Deng beta ju bisa manyanyi pake kata-kata yang beta mangarti.<bt>So (consequently), it is good that I do what/how? I use both, but each of them in its (own appropriate) time. I want to pray using my liver. And I also want to pray using words that I understand. I want to sings praise songs to God2 using my liver. And I can also sing using words that I understand.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="NRSV: What should I do then?"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">NRSV: What should I do then? I will pray with the spirit, but I will pray with the mind also; I will sing praise with the spirit, but I will sing praise with the mind also.</Message></Annotation><v n="16" />Te kalo lu pake bahasa laen ko angka puji-puji sang Tuhan Allah dari lu pung hati, ais ada orang di situ yang sonde mangarti itu hal dong, karmana dia bisa satu hati deng lu? Waktu lu ada minta tarima kasi sang Tuhan pake bahasa laen, karmana ko dia bisa satuju deng lu bilang, &lt;&lt;Itu batúl tu!&gt;&gt; Sonde bisa, to? Te dia sonde mangarti lu pung bahasa tu.<bt>Cuz if you-sg use a different language to lift praises to God from your liver, and there is a person there who doesn't understand those things, how can s/he be one livered (united, harmony, in accord) with you? When you are giving thanks to God2 using a different language, how is it that s/he can agree with you saying, &lt;&lt;That's right!&gt;&gt; S/he can't, right? Cuz (elaboration) s/he can't understand your language/words/message.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="eulogées: pronounce a blessing, say that"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">eulogées: pronounce a blessing, say that God is good because he makes it possible for us to function as we were intended to function (in the Jewish tradition). Not quite the same as giving thanks idioótou: nonexperts, possible those who do not have the gift of interpreting ecstatic speech. Not just an outsider to the group, but one who isn't into interpreting tongues<span class="Italic">(16) (16) </span>NRSV: Otherwise, if you say a blessing with the spirit, how can anyone in the position of an outsider say the “Amen” to your thanksgiving, since the outsider does not know what you are saying?</Message></Annotation><v n="17" />Bisa sa lu minta tarima kasi sang Tuhan bagitu. Ma itu sonde kasi kuat orang laen pung hati.<bt>It is possible for you to give thanks to God2 like that. But that doesn't strengthen/encourage another/the other person's liver.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="NRSV: For you may give thanks"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">NRSV: For you may give thanks well enough, but the other person is not built up.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="18" />Mangkali bosong sonde tau, ma beta omong pake bahasa laen lebe dari bosong samua. Deng beta minta tarima kasi sang Tuhan, tagal Dia bekin beta bisa omong bagitu.<bt>You-pl probably don't know (this), but (in actual fact...) I speak using other languages more than all of you. And I give thanks to God2, because He makes me able to do that.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="NRSV: I thank God that I"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">NRSV: I thank God that I speak in tongues more than all of you;</Message></Annotation><v n="19" />Ma kalo orang parcaya ada bakumpul, ada lebe bae beta omong pake lima kata yang pende sa, yang dong bisa mangarti, ko beta ajar sang dong, daripada beta omong panjang lalolak pake bahasa laen, deng pake kata barangke-rangke, yang dong sonde mangarti.<bt>But if believers are gathered together, it is best that I speak using just five short words that they can understand, so I teach them, than I talk long1 long2 using a different language, and use massive clusters of words (clusters of grapes, bananas, etc.), that they don't understand.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="kata barangke-rangke = clusters of words"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z">kata barangke-rangke = clusters of words ; yang panjang lololak</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="pente: five words -- a small"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">pente: five words -- a small number NRSV: nevertheless, in church I would rather speak five words with my mind, in order to instruct others also, than ten thousand words in a tongue.<span class="Italic">(19)</span></Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="20" />Sodara sayang dong! Kalo bosong mau coba mangarti hal, bosong musti balajar pikir ke orang dewasa. Jang bapikir sama ke ana kici dong! Ma deng hal jahat, bosong musti ke ana kici, yang sonde tau bekin hal jahat dong, te dong hati barisi.<bt>Dear siblings! If you-pl want to try to understand something, you must learn to think like an adult/mature/fully developed. Don't be thinking like small children! But with (regard to) evil things, you must be like small children, who don't know how to do evil things, cuz (elaboration) their livers are clean. [NOTE on STRUCTURE: undo the complex chiasmus. a b a; one variable not children, infants, adults; another variable thinking, evil, (good), thinking]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="NRSV: Brothers and sisters, do not"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">NRSV: Brothers and sisters, do not be children in your thinking; rather, be infants in evil, but in thinking be adults.</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Sodara sayang dong! Jang bapikir sama"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z">Sodara sayang dong! Jang bapikir sama ke ana kici dong! Kalo bapikir hal jahat, bole sa! Te ana kici dong hati barisi, deng sonde tau bekin hal jahat dong. Ma kalo bosong mau mangarti hal, bosong pung pikir musti ke orang yang su dewasa!</Message></Annotation><v n="21" />Di Tuhan pung Tulisan Barisi, ada tulis bilang:<bt>In God2's Scriptures, it is written saying,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">&lt;&lt;Kotong pung Bos ada omong bilang,<bt>&lt;&lt;Our-inc Bos is speaking saying,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">&lt;Beta mau pake orang yang omong pake bahasa laen dong,<bt>&lt;I am going to use people who speak using other languages,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 3" usfm="q3">ko Beta omong kasi ini bangsa Isra'el.<bt>so I can speak to this Isra'el nation/race/people group.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Ma biar Beta omong karmana ju,<bt>But no matter what I say,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">dong sonde mau dengar sang Beta.&gt;&gt;&gt;<bt>they don't want to listen to Me.&gt;&gt;&gt;</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="NRSV: In the law it is"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">NRSV: In the law it is written, “By people of strange tongues and by the lips of foreigners I will speak to this people; yet even then they will not listen to me,” says the Lord.</Message></Annotation><note reference="14:21" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Yesaya 28:11-12</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="22" />Tagal itu, bosong dapa lia, kalo orang omong pake bahasa laen, itu jadi tanda kasi orang yang <span class="Italic">balóm </span>parcaya sang Tuhan, ko dong dapa lia Dia pung kuasa. Itu sonde tolong orang dong yang <span class="Italic">su </span>parcaya sang Tuhan. Ma kalo orang omong kasi tau Tuhan pung pasán, itu tolong orang yang <span class="Italic">su </span>parcaya sang Dia. Itu sonde tolong orang yang <span class="Italic">balóm </span>parcaya sang Dia.<bt>Because of that, you can see, if a person speaks using a different language, that is a sign to people who <span class="Italic">don't yet</span> believe in God2, so they can see His power/authority. That does not help people who <span class="Italic">already </span>believe in God2. But if people speak telling/explaining God2's message, that helps people who <span class="Italic">already </span>believe in Him. That does not help people who do <span class="Italic">not yet</span> believe in Him.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="NRSV: Tongues, then, are a sign"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">NRSV: Tongues, then, are a sign not for believers but for unbelievers, while prophecy is not for unbelievers but for believers.</Message></Annotation><v n="23" />Andekata bosong samua ada bakumpul, ju bosong samua ada omong pake bahasa laen-laen, ais ada orang yang sonde parcaya, ko, orang yang sonde mangarti ini hal dong, maso di bosong pung teng-tenga, nanti dong pikir karmana? Pasti dong bilang, &lt;&lt;Ini orang di sini dong su gila, é!&gt;&gt;<bt>If perchance [+hypothetical] you-pl are all gathered together, and you are all speaking using various other languages, then there is a person who does not believe, or a person who doesn't understand these matters, come into your midst, what are they going to think? Surely they will say, &lt;&lt;These people here are crazy, é!&gt;&gt;</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="idióotai: probably not unbelievers, but people"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">idióotai: probably not unbelievers, but people who are not experts in dealing with ecstatic speech as in Verse 16; the unbelievers are mentioned separately maínesthe: not mentally unbalanced, but under the power of an evil spirit, religious frenzy, be mad, be out of one's mind, have no control over oneself<span class="Italic">(23) (23) </span>NRSV: If, therefore, the whole church comes together and all speak in tongues, and outsiders or unbelievers enter, will they not say that you are out of your mind?</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="24" />Deng andekata bosong samua ada ba'omong kasi tau Tuhan pung pasán, ju ada orang yang sonde parcaya, ko, orang yang sonde mangarti ini hal dong, maso di bosong pung teng-tenga. Pasti itu orang mau dengar apa yang bosong ada omong. Jadi apa yang bosong omong tu, kasi tunju dia pung sala-sala, sampe dia mau pareksa deng alus-alus dia pung idop sandiri.<bt>And if perchance [+hypothetical] all of you are recip-speaking telling/explaining God2's message, and there is a person who doesn't believe, or a person who doesn't understand these matters, comes into your midst. Surely that person wants to listen to what it is you are talking about. So (consequently), what you are talking about shows him his wrongs, to the point that s/he wants to examine carefully/in fine detail his own life. [EXEG: NLT, CEV, HCE]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="hati tapuku(l) = convicted"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z">hati tapuku(l) = convicted</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="idiootees: a person who has not"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">idiootees: a person who has not been to the approved schools, but just learned things himself. Used of the disciples in Acts. UBS suggests it means "Christians who do not have the gift of understanding and interpreting strange tongues" here in 23-24 and in 16. NRSV: But if all prophesy, an unbeliever or outsider who enters is reproved by all and called to account by all.<span class="Italic">(24)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="25" />Ais hal-hal jahat yang dia sambunyi dalam dia pung hati, nanti jadi tabuka ko samua orang dapa tau. Ais ju itu orang nanti tikam lutut ko sémba sang Tuhan Allah bilang, &lt;&lt;Awii! Su jalás Tuhan Allah ada di bosong pung teng-tenga!&gt;&gt;<bt>And the various evil things that s/he has hidden in his liver, will be unveiled (non-agentive) so everyone comes to know about them/for all to know. And then that person will kneel to worship God saying, &lt;&lt;Awii! [+amazement] It's clear that God is in your midst!&gt;&gt;</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="pesoòn epì prósoopon: a sign of"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">pesoòn epì prósoopon: a sign of unworthiness and humiliation, not ordinary prayer. What people say from God has gotten to him, and he feels very bad about how he has lived, whether he is a Christian or not, and he wants to make things right NRSV: After the secrets of the unbeliever's heart are disclosed, that person will bow down before God and worship him, declaring, “God is really among you.”<span class="Italic">(25)</span></Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Samua hal yang kotong bekin, na, bekin iko dia pung batúl. Jang kaco-kaco<bt>Everything that we-inc do, na, do according to what is right. Don't be chaotic/disorder/badly disorganised</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="26" />Jadi sodara sayang dong! Kalo bosong ada bakumpul, tiap orang ada dia pung karunya. Ada yang manyanyi lagu puji sang Tuhan Allah. Ada yang ajar orang so'al Tuhan. Ada yang buka kasi tau hal dari Tuhan, yang dolu ada tasambunyi. Ada yang omong pake bahasa laen. Deng ada yang bisa kasi tau itu bahasa pung arti. Samua hal tu, dong musti bekin ko kasi kuat orang laen dong pung parcaya.<bt>So (consequently) dear siblings! If you are gathered, each person has his (own) unique.gifting. There are those who sing praise songs to God. There are those who teach people about God2. There are those who unveil/explain things from God2, that were previously hidden. There are those who speak using other languages. And there are those who can explain what that language means. All those things, they must do to strengthen other people's faith.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="NRSV: What should be done then,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">NRSV: What should be done then, my friends? When you come together, each one has a hymn, a lesson, a revelation, a tongue, or an interpretation. Let all things be done for building up.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="27" />Kalo ada yang suka omong pake bahasa laen, itu bae. Ma biar dua ko tiga orang sa, cukup su. Sonde usa bam-banya. Satu omong abis dolo, baru satu omong lai. Deng musti ada orang yang bisa kasi tau dong pung bahasa pung arti.<bt>If there is someone who likes to speak using another language, that is good. But just let there be two or three people, that's (quite) enough. You don't need lots and lots. One person should finish speaking first, only then another one speaks. And there must be someone who can explain what their language/message/words mean.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="NRSV: If anyone speaks in a"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">NRSV: If anyone speaks in a tongue, let there be only two or at most three, and each in turn; and let one interpret.</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Satu dolo, baru dia pung tamán."><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z">Satu dolo, baru dia pung tamán.</Message></Annotation><v n="28" />Andekata kalo sonde ada orang yang bisa kasi tau itu bahasa pung arti, na, sonde usa omong pake bahasa laen di orang banya dong pung muka. Biar ko dong omong bagitu dalam dong pung hati sandiri sa. Dong ju bisa omong deng Tuhan bagitu.<bt>If perchance [+hypothetical] there is nobody who can explain the meaning of that language, na, (you) don't need to speak using other languages in front of other people. Just let them speak that way in their own livers. They can also speak to God2 that way.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="NRSV: But if there is no"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">NRSV: But if there is no one to interpret, let them be silent in church and speak to themselves and to God.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="29" />Kalo bosong ada bakumpul, biar dua ko tiga orang sa yang omong kasi tau Tuhan pung pasán. Yang laen dong musti timbang bae-bae dong pung omong tu.<bt>If you are gathered together, just let two or three people speak telling/explaining God2's message. the others must weigh/evaluate well/carefull what they are saying.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="diakrinétoosan: exercise judgment, discuss to understand"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">diakrinétoosan: exercise judgment, discuss to understand how to apply the message from God to their situation -- not to decide whether the people who spoke were qualified or whether they were really talking for God NRSV: Let two or three prophets speak, and let the others weigh what is said.<span class="Italic">(29)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="30" />Ma andekata Tuhan ada buka kasi mangarti satu hal yang dolu sonde jalás, kasi sang satu orang yang dudu dengar di situ, na, itu orang musti kasi tau itu pasán kasi samua yang ada di situ. Deng orang yang ada omong di muka musti barenti, ko kasi salák sang orang yang baru dengar dari Tuhan tu, ko dia omong.<bt>But if perchance [+hypothetical] God2 has/is revealing the understanding of something that was previously not clear, to one person who is sitting there listening, na, that person must tell/explain that message to everyone who is there. And the person who is speaking in front must stop, to give opportunity to the person who has just (now, recently) heard from God2, so s/he can speak. [EXEG: re: “in front”. neither the MTTs nor the UNSs were picturing the dynamics, or understanding “the first person” without it. RL considerations, irrespective of Brethren practices.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="*** (2009) note added"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z">*** (2009) note added</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="NRSV: If a revelation is made"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">NRSV: If a revelation is made to someone else sitting nearby, let the first person be silent.</Message></Annotation><v n="31" />Dia pung batúl, bosong samua bisa kasi tau Tuhan pung pasán. Ma kasi tenga satu orang omong dolo, ais baru dia pung tamán. Deng bagitu, samua orang bisa dengar, samua bisa balajar, deng samua bisa rasa dong pung hati jadi lebe kuat.<bt>The right/proper thing, would be for all of you to be able to tell/explain God2's message. But let/permit/allow one person to speak first, and only then his friend/companion. In that way, everyone can hear, everyone can learn, and everyone can feel/sense/experience their livers becoming stronger.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="NRSV: For you can all prophesy"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">NRSV: For you can all prophesy one by one, so that all may learn and all be encouraged.</Message></Annotation><v n="32" />Inga te, orang yang omong kasi tau Tuhan pung pasán, ju musti tau ator dia pung diri. Ais satu bisa tunggu satu, te yang laen bisa tahan dia pung diri.<bt>Remember that a person who speaks telling/explaining God2's message, must also know how to manage/control/regulate himself. So then one can wait for another, cuz (elaboration) the other is able to restain/hold out himself. [EXEG: HCE]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="context or procedure? Able to shut"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">context or procedure? Able to shut up. NRSV: And the spirits of prophets are subject to the prophets,<span class="Italic">(32)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="33" />Te sonde ada kaco di Tuhan Allah. Samua ta'ator deng tanáng.<bt>Cuz (elaboration) there is no chaos/disorder/disarray in/at God. Everything is just ordered/managed/control/regulated and calm. [NOTE: compound end part follows CEV to fit context.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="ta'ator"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z">ta'ator</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="NRSV: for God is a God"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">NRSV: for God is a God not of disorder but of peace.</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Te sonde ada kaco di Tuhan"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z">Te sonde ada kaco di Tuhan Allah. Samua ta'ator deng tanáng sa.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Di mana-mana, kalo orang parcaya dong bakumpul, dia pung biasa bagini:<bt>All over the place, if/when believers are gathered together, the norm/custom is like this:</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="NRSV: (As in all the churches"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">NRSV: (As in all the churches of the saints,</Message></Annotation><v n="34" />Parampuan dong musti dudu tanáng. Dong jang mulu banya. Dong musti dengar-dengar sang pimpinan dong. Te Tuhan Allah pung Atoran ju omong bagitu, to?<bt>Women must sit calmly/quietly. They should not be many mouthing (=talkative talking a lot). They must be listening to/obeying the leaders. Cuz (elaboration) God's Law says that, right? [EXEG from (Ex.Sum): not taken as absolute, since that would contradict 11:5, 13, 26, 31, etc.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="mulu besar = cerewet ; mulu"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z">mulu besar = cerewet ; mulu banya = suka ba'omong, banya omong, talkative</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="hypotassésthoosan: let them take a subordinate"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">hypotassésthoosan: let them take a subordinate place, not be in charge, NRSV: women should be silent in the churches. For they are not permitted to speak, but should be subordinate, as the law also says.<span class="Italic">(34)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="35" />Kalo ada yang mau tanya satu hal, na, biar tunggu dia pulang dolo, baru tanya sang dia pung laki sa. Te kalo parampuan dong baribut dalam ruma sambayang, itu bekin malu sa!<bt>If there is one (woman) who wants to ask about something, na, let her wait until she goes home first, only then ask her husband. Cuz (elaboration) if women are noisy/disruptive in a house of worship, that is shameful!</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="NRSV: If there is anything they"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">NRSV: If there is anything they desire to know, let them ask their husbands at home. For it is shameful for a woman to speak in church.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="36" />Bosong pung pikir karmana!? Te Tuhan Allah pung Kata-kata sonde datang dari bosong! Deng Dia pung Kata-kata sonde kasi sang bosong di kota Korintus sandiri sa! Pikir bae-bae dolo!<bt>What are you-pl thinking!? Cuz (elaboration) God's Words did not come from you! And His Words were not just given to you in the city of Korintus alone! Think about this, (guys)! [NOTE: Construction of last sentence carries sense of corrective frustration--you should know better!]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="NRSV: Or did the word of"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">NRSV: Or did the word of God originate with you? Or are you the only ones it has reached?)</Message></Annotation><v n="37" />Kalo ada orang yang anggap diri bisa kasi tau Tuhan pung pasán, ko, pikir dia ada tarima kuasa dari Tuhan pung Roh, na, dia sandiri tau bilang, itu hal yang beta ada tulis kasi bosong tu, bukan atoran dari beta, ma itu parenta dari Yesus, kotong pung Bos.<bt>If there is a person who considers themselves able to tell/explain God2's message, or, thinks s/he has received power/authority from God2's Spirit, na, /she himself knows that, that matter which I am writing to you about, is not a regulation from me, but it is a command from Yesus, our-inc Bos.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="epiginooskétoo: acknowledge, recognize, admit, agree NRSV:"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">epiginooskétoo: acknowledge, recognize, admit, agree NRSV: Anyone who claims to be a prophet, or to have spiritual powers, must acknowledge that what I am writing to you is a command of the Lord.<span class="Italic">(37)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="38" />Kalo ada orang yang sonde mau tarima ini hal dong, na, bosong jang tarima sang dia.<bt>If there is a person who does not want to accept these matters, na, you-pl should not receive/welcome him.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="agnoéitai: not recognized by the church?"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">agnoéitai: not recognized by the church? by God? commentators disagree NRSV: Anyone who does not recognize this is not to be recognized.<span class="Italic">(38)</span></Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="39" />Sodara sayang dong! Pasang kaki ko bosong dapa kuasa ko bisa omong kasi tau Tuhan pung pasán. Deng jang larang orang bilang, dong sonde bole omong pake bahasa yang laen.<bt>Dear siblings! Make an effort/strive (lit: fasten your feet) so you get power to be able to speak telling God2's message/instructions. And don't forbid people saying, they are not allowed to speak using other languages.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="NRSV: So, my friends, be eager"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">NRSV: So, my friends, be eager to prophesy, and do not forbid speaking in tongues;</Message></Annotation><v n="40" />Jadi kalo bosong bakumpul, na, kasi jalan samua deng batúl, iko yang pantas. Satu hal jalan dolo, baru yang laen iko. Kasi jalan samua deng ta'ator. Jang kaco-kaco.<bt>So (consequently), if you are gathered together, na, carry out everything rightly, according to what i s appropriate. One thing goes/happens first, and only then another follows. Carry out everything ordered/managed/control/regulated. Don't be chaotic/disorder/badly disorganised.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="NRSV: but all things should be"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">NRSV: but all things should be done decently and in order.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Kristus su idop kambali dari Dia pung mati<bt>Kristus has come back to life from His death</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <c n="15" />
      <v n="1" />Sodara sayang dong! Beta mau ko bosong inga Tuhan pung Kabar Bae yang beta su kasi tau sang bosong dari dolu. Bosong tarima ame, ju batahan iko tarús sang itu Kabar.<bt>Dear siblings! I want you to remember God2's Good News which I have told you from long ago. You received/accepted it and have persevered in continuing to follow/obey that News.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="parelábete: receive -- more than just"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">parelábete: receive -- more than just listening to Paul preach; more like "took it to heart", "bought into it" NRSV: Now I would remind you, brothers and sisters, of the good news that I proclaimed to you, which you in turn received, in which also you stand,<span class="Italic">(1)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="2" />Te itu Kabar yang bisa kasi salamat sang bosong, asal bosong bapegang kuat tarús sang dia. Ma kalo bosong sonde parcaya tarús sang Tuhan Allah, bosong pung parcaya, parcuma sa.<bt>Cuz (elaboration) that News is what can save you, as long as you keep holding firmly to it. But if you don't keep believing in God, your faith is pointless/useless/in vain. [EXEG: in this context focus is on perseverence, whereas in v.14 it is on the truth of the resurrection. This is talking about having geniune faith (Ex.Summ.), not having believed the wrong thing (as per NLT)]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="*** (2009) note expanded"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z">*** (2009) note expanded</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="eikéei: in vain, useless -- if"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">eikéei: in vain, useless -- if the hoped-for consequences of faith will never happen, that makes faith useless NRSV: through which also you are being saved, if you hold firmly to the message that I proclaimed to you-unless you have come to believe in vain.<span class="Italic">(2)</span></Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="3" />Beta ju su ajar sang bosong hal-hal yang paling pantíng, yang dolu orang su parná ajar sang beta. Andia: Kristus, yang Tuhan Allah su kirim datang tu, su mati ko kasi salamat sang kotong dari kotong pung sala-sala, parsís ke Tuhan pung Tulisan Barisi ada tulis dari dolu.<bt>I have also taught you various matters that are most important, which previously (other) people have taught to me. That is: Kristus, whom God has sent coming, died to save us-inc from our wrongs, exactly like God2's Holy Writings have written from long ago. [EXEG: The Gk “foremost things” is plural, followed by an elaboration of a list that goes on for many verses. So in these RLs, making “that important matter” singular doesn't work in context nor match the Gk. The Gk /gar/ links to returning to elaborate on what he said in vs.1-2a (see Ex. Summ.). Note that both NLT and CEV choose to undertranslate /gar/.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="*** (2009) note added"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z">*** (2009) note added</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="NRSV: For I handed on to"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">NRSV: For I handed on to you as of first importance what I in turn had received: that Christ died for our sins in accordance with the scriptures,</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Hal-hal yang paling pantíng yang orang"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z">Hal-hal yang paling pantíng yang orang ajar sang beta dolu, beta ju ajar sang bosong.</Message></Annotation><note reference="15:3" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Yesaya 53:5-12</note><v n="4" />Ju dong kubur sang Dia. Ais dia pung lusa, Tuhan kasi idop kambali sang Dia, parsís ke Tuhan pung Tulisan Barisi ada tulis memang dari dolu.<bt>Then they buried Him. Then2, the day after next, God2 brought Him back to life, exactly as God2's Holy Writings have written beforehand from long ago.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="NRSV: and that he was buried,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">NRSV: and that he was buried, and that he was raised on the third day in accordance with the scriptures,</Message></Annotation><note reference="15:4" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Lagu Puji dong 16:8-10, Mateos 12:40, Utusan dong pung Carita 2:24-32</note><v n="5" />Ais ju Kristus kasi tunju Dia pung diri sang Petrus.<bt>And/then3 Kristus showed Himself to Petrus.</bt><note reference="15:5" class="Note General Paragraph" usfm="f">Alkitab bahasa Yunani tulis bilang, &lt;&lt;Kefas&gt;&gt;. Kefas tu, Petrus pung nama laen.<bt>The Yunani language Bible writes saying, &lt;&lt;Kefas&gt;&gt;. That Kefas, is Petrus' other name.</bt></note>Dia ju kasi tunju Dia pung diri sang Dia pung ana bua dua blas orang.<bt>He also showed Himself to His 12 *disciples (underlings).</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="oóphthee: he was seen, often used"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">oóphthee: he was seen, often used for a supernatural appearance -- "he showed himself to somebody, appeared (usually when they were not expecting it), he let himself be seen" NRSV: and that he appeared to Cephas, then to the twelve.<span class="Italic">(5)</span></Message></Annotation><note reference="15:5" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Mateos 28:16-17, Markus 16:14, Lukas 24:34, 36, Yohanis 20:19</note><v n="6" />Ais satu kali, Dia ju kasi tunju Dia pung diri sang lebe dari lima ratus orang parcaya. Te samua dapa lia sang Dia na! Dari dong tu, ada banya yang masi idop. Cuma sadiki sa yang su mati.<bt>Then2 one time, He also showed Himself to more than 500 believers. All of them got to see Him [+emphatic]! From those, there are many who are still alive. Only a few have already died.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="NRSV: Then he appeared to more"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">NRSV: Then he appeared to more than five hundred brothers and sisters at one time, most of whom are still alive, though some have died.</Message></Annotation><v n="7" />Ais Dia kasi tunju diri sang bu Yakobis. Ais ju Dia kasi tunju diri sang Dia pung utusan dong samua.<bt>Then2 He showed self to older brother Yakobis. And then He showed self to all His *apostles/emissaries. [NOTE for SU: vs. 3-7 can be read together as a Confession of Fatih.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="NRSV: Then he appeared to James,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">NRSV: Then he appeared to James, then to all the apostles.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="8" />Naa! Beta yang paling kakorek ju dapa lia sang Dia. Te beta sama ke ana bungsu yang lahir paling balakang.<bt>Naa! I am the one at the very end of the line/least value who also got to see Him. cuz (elaboration) I am like the youngest child who was born at the very tail end / after everyone else.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="NRSV: Last of all, as to"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">NRSV: Last of all, as to one untimely born, he appeared also to me.</Message></Annotation><note reference="15:8" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Utusan dong pung Carita 9:3-6</note><v n="9" />Tuhan pung utusan yang laen dong, samua lebe pantíng dari beta. Kalo iko yang batúl, sonde pantas beta jadi Dia pung utusan. Te dolu, beta yang bekin sangsara deng siksa sang Tuhan pung orang dong di mana-mana.<bt>God2's other apostles, all of them are more important than me. If we go according to what is right, it is not appropriate for me to be His apostle. Cuz (elaboration) previously, I am the one who cause torment and abuse/mistreatment to God2's people all over the place.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="NRSV: For I am the least"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">NRSV: For I am the least of the apostles, unfit to be called an apostle, because I persecuted the church of God.</Message></Annotation><note reference="15:9" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Utusan dong pung Carita 8:3</note><v n="10" />Ma Tuhan Allah kasi tunju Dia pung hati bae sang beta. Ais Dia yang bekin sang beta ko jadi sama ke sakarang. Waktu Dia ada bekin hal bae kasi sang beta, Dia sonde buang-buang waktu parcuma. Dia pung ujung, beta yang pasang kaki lebe dari samua! Padahal bukan beta yang karjá, ma Tuhan pung hati bae yang ada karjá di beta pung idop.<bt>But God showed His good liver (goodness/grace/kindness/generosity) to me. So He is the one who made me to be as I am now. When He was doing good things to/for me, He was not just throwing away time pointlessly/in vain. The end result is that I am the one who strives more than everyone! Whereas in fact, it is not I who am working, but God2's good liver which is working in my life.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="NRSV: But by the grace of"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">NRSV: But by the grace of God I am what I am, and his grace toward me has not been in vain. On the contrary, I worked harder than any of them-though it was not I, but the grace of God that is with me.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="11" />Jadi sonde pantíng kalo beta yang ajar, ko, utusan laen dong yang ajar. Te botong samua ada ajar hal yang sama. Botong kasi tau orang so'al Tuhan pung Kabar Bae tarús-tarús. Tagal itu, bosong jadi parcaya sang itu Kabar Bae yang sama.<bt>So (consequently) it is not important if I am the one who teaches, or, a different *apostle who teaches. Cuz (elaboration) all of us-exc are teaching the same thing. We keep telling people about God2's Good News. Because of that, you-pl came to believe in that same Good News.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="NRSV: Whether then it was I"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">NRSV: Whether then it was I or they, so we proclaim and so you have come to believe.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Orang mati, nanti idop kambali<bt>Dead people will come back to life/live again</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="12" />Botong biasa ajar bilang, Kristus, yang Tuhan su kirim datang tu, su idop kambali dari Dia pung mati. Jadi akurang ko bosong saparu bilang, &lt;&lt;Orang mati dong, sonde idop kambali&gt;&gt;? Dia pung dasar apa?<bt>We teach that Kristus, whom God2 sent, came back to life from His death. So (consequently), why is it that some of you are saying, &lt;&lt;Dead people don't come back to life&gt;&gt;? What's the basis of that?</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="NRSV: Now if Christ is proclaimed"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">NRSV: Now if Christ is proclaimed as raised from the dead, how can some of you say there is no resurrection of the dead?</Message></Annotation><v n="13" />Te andekata orang mati sonde idop kambali, dia pung arti bilang, Kristus ju sonde idop kambali!<bt>Cuz (elaboration), if perchance [+hypothetical] dead people don't come back to life, that means that Kristus also didn't come back to life!</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="NRSV: If there is no resurrection"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">NRSV: If there is no resurrection of the dead, then Christ has not been raised;</Message></Annotation><v n="14" />Deng kalo Kristus sonde idop kambali, samua-samua yang botong biasa kasi tau sang orang dong, sonde ada pung guna. Deng bosong pung parcaya sang Dia, parcuma sa!<bt>And if Kristus did not come back to life, everything that we-exc are in the habit of telling people has no use. And your-pl faith in Him, is pointless/useless/in vain!</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="NRSV: and if Christ has not"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">NRSV: and if Christ has not been raised, then our proclamation has been in vain and your faith has been in vain.</Message></Annotation><v n="15-16" />Kalo batúl orang mati sonde idop kambali, botong ju jadi saksi omong kosong so'al Tuhan Allah. Te botong biasa ajar bilang, &lt;&lt;Tuhan Allah yang kasi idop kambali sang Kristus!&gt;&gt; Memang botong kasi tau bagitu. Ma andekata orang mati sonde idop kambali, dia pung arti bilang, Tuhan Allah sonde parná kasi idop kambali sang Kristus.<bt>And if it's true that dead people don't come back to life, we are also false witnesses/lying witnesses about God. Cuz (elaboration) we are in the habit of teaching that, &lt;&lt;God is the one who brought Kristus back to life!&gt;&gt; We really do say that. But if perchance [+hypothetical] it were the case that dead people don't come back to life, that means that God never brought Kristus back to life.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="NRSV: We are even found to"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">NRSV: We are even found to be misrepresenting God, because we testified of God that he raised Christ-whom he did not raise if it is true that the dead are not raised. For if the dead are not raised, then Christ has not been raised.</Message></Annotation><v n="17" />Pikir coba ini hal: kalo Kristus sonde idop kambali, bosong pung parcaya sang Tuhan Allah parcuma sa! Te bosong masi pikol bosong pung sala-sala dong!<bt>Have a think about this: if Kristus did not come back to life, your-pl faith in God is pointless! Cuz (elaboration) you are still shoulder-carrying your wrongs!</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="NRSV: If Christ has not been"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">NRSV: If Christ has not been raised, your faith is futile and you are still in your sins.</Message></Annotation><v n="18" />Bukan itu sandiri sa, te samua orang yang su mati dong, yang dolu ta'ika deng Kristus, kalo Kristus sonde parná idop kambali, dong ju mati deng tapisa buang dari Tuhan Allah.<bt>And that's not all, cuz (elaboration) everyone who has died, who was bound/linked with Kristus, if Kristus never came back to life, they died and are separated off/cut off from God.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="*** KT perish (frm John &amp;"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z">*** KT perish (frm John &amp; 2 Cor; see note as Jn 3:16)</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="apoólonto: opposite of salvation NRSV: Then"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">apoólonto: opposite of salvation NRSV: Then those also who have died in Christ have perished.<span class="Italic">(18)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="19" />Kotong ada basandar sang Kristus bilang, nanti Dia mau bekin yang bae kasi kotong. Ma andekata kotong pung harap bagitu, cuma jadi dalam ini dunya sa, na, itu parcuma sa! Deng kotong jadi orang yang paling kasian dari samua!<bt>We-inc are leaning on/depending on/trusting in Kristus, that He is going to do what is good/best for us. But if perchance our hope like that only happens/is only in effect in this world, na, that is pointless/in vain! And we are people who are most pitiable of all!</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="NRSV: If for this life only"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">NRSV: If for this life only we have hoped in Christ, we are of all people most to be pitied.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Apa yang nanti jadi, tagal Kristus idop kambali?<bt>What is going to happen later, because Kristus came back to life?</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="20" />Padahal sonde bagitu, to? Te yang batúl, andia: Kristus, yang Tuhan Allah su kirim datang tu, su idop kambali dari Dia pung mati! Deng bukan Dia sandiri sa, te nanti orang parcaya yang su mati dong, idop kambali ju. Kristus sama ke hasil partama, yang kasi tunju bilang, orang mati nanti idop kambali iko sang Dia.<bt>Whereas in fact, it's not like that, right? Cuz (elaboration) what is true is this: Kristus, whom God has sent, has already come back to life from His death! And not only He alone, cuz (elaboration) later believers who have already died will also come back to life. Kristus is like the first produce/result (agricultural imagery), which shows that those who die will come back to life following His (lead, example, experience). [EXEG: CEV undertranslated here.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="aparcheè: the first sample of a"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">aparcheè: the first sample of a crop was given to God as an offering kekoimeeménoon: those who have fallen asleep. This was a common Christian way of referring to people who had died<span class="Italic">(20) (20) </span>NRSV: But in fact Christ has been raised from the dead, the first fruits of those who have died.</Message></Annotation><v n="21" />Dolu-dolu, cuma satu orang sa, andia Adam, yang langgar Tuhan pung parenta. Jadi dia pung hukuman, andia mati. Itu hukuman ju jato kaná di kotong manusia samua. Ma sakarang, ada satu orang lai, andia Kristus, yang idop iko Tuhan pung parenta. Jadi, tagal Dia pung bae, orang mati bisa idop kambali!<bt>Long ago, it was only one person, that is Adam, who violated God2's command/s. So (consequently) his punishment was death. That punishment also fell on/effected all of us humans. But now, there is one other person, that is Kristus, who lived according to God2's command/s. So (consequently) because of His goodness, dead people can come back to life! [EXEG: (theology): from notes on Rom 5:12: Everybody since Adam has made the same kind of bad choice Adam made, back at the beginning. They all ended up sinning by just the same process as Adam ended up sinning. Spread throughout the human race -- not genetically, just because we are human and the first real human somehow screwed up our genes, or let loose some kind of moral virus, but because practically speaking, all the rest of us have fallen into the same trap as Adam, of not wanting to do things God's way.] [NOTE: still missing in the logical structure here: "to us who have also violated God's law.", but in next verse]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="See Gk notes on Rom 5:12"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z">See Gk notes on Rom 5:12 re: original sin;</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="NRSV: For since death came through"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">NRSV: For since death came through a human being, the resurrection of the dead has also come through a human being;</Message></Annotation><v n="22" />Samua orang yang langgar Tuhan pung parenta, kaná hukuman mati ju, sama ke Adam. Bagitu ju, samua orang yang ta'ika deng Kristus, nanti Tuhan Allah kasi idop kambali sang dong.<bt>Everyone who violates God2's commands is also effected by a punishment of death, just like Adam. In the same way, everyone who is bound/linked with Kristus, God will bring them back to life.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="en ... en: everybody has a"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">en ... en: everybody has a relationship to Adam ... everybody that has a relationship to Christ NRSV: for as all die in Adam, so all will be made alive in Christ.<span class="Italic">(22)</span></Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="23" />Ma satu-satu deng dia pung waktu. Kristus jadi orang partama yang idop kambali, sama ke hasil partama tadi tu. Deng nanti, kalo Dia su datang kambali di ini dunya, baru Dia pung orang dong ju idop kambali.<bt>But each in his own time. Kristus was the first person to come back to life, like the aforementioned first yield/produce earlier. And later, when He has come back to this world, only then will His people also come back to life.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="NRSV: But each in his own"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">NRSV: But each in his own order: Christ the first fruits, then at his coming those who belong to Christ.</Message></Annotation><v n="24" />Ais itu, baru dunya kiamat. Itu waktu, Kristus jadi Raja yang kasi ancor samua kuasa, samua parenta, deng samua ilmu yang bamusu deng Tuhan. Dia ju jadi Raja yang sarakan kambali Dia pung hak parenta sang Tuhan Allah, Dia pung Bapa.<bt>After that, only then the end of the world. At that time, Kristus will be King who destroys all powers/authroities, all rule/commands, and all science/magic that opposes God2. He will also be the King that turns His right to rule back over to God, His Father. [EXEG: NLT + Ex. Summ.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="NRSV: Then comes the end, when"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">NRSV: Then comes the end, when he hands over the kingdom to God the Father, after he has destroyed every ruler and every authority and power.</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="yang kasi ancor samua kuasa yang"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z">yang kasi ancor samua kuasa yang pegang parenta, yang pegang kuasa, deng yang tuntut dong pung hak.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="25" />Te Dia musti pegang parenta tarús, sampe Tuhan Allah bekin kala samua yang malawan sang Kristus, ko dong ta'alok sang Dia.<bt>Cuz (elaboration) He must hold rule continually, until God conquears all who oppose Kristus, so they surrender/submit to him. [NOTE to daughter translations: some mesolectal speakers don't know /ta'alok/, so use a word for "bow".]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="NRSV: For he must reign until"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">NRSV: For he must reign until he has put all his enemies under his feet.</Message></Annotation><note reference="15:25" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Lagu Puji dong 110:1</note><v n="26" />Ada satu hal lai yang bamusu deng kotong manusia. Andia kotong musti mati. Ma yang tarahir, Tuhan ju mau kasi kala sang mati pung kuasa. Dia bekin bagitu abis, ju sonde ada orang yang mati lai.<bt>There is another matter/thing which is opposing/warring with we-inc humans. That is, we must die. But in the end/ultimately, God2 is also going to conquer (cause to lose) the power/authority of death. After He does that, there will not be anyone who dies anymore. [EXEG: see Ex.Summ. and TH for discussion on complex implications of Gk present tense. This version worked out with consultant assistance from UNS responses, but not yet fully satisfying.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="thánatos: Death, as an abstraction, is"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">thánatos: Death, as an abstraction, is not the same as the Devil NRSV: The last enemy to be destroyed is death.<span class="Italic">(26)</span></Message><Message author="Chuck Grimes" created="2015-01-17 03:34:04Z">[EXEG: See</Message></Annotation><v n="27" />Di Tuhan pung Tulisan Barisi ada tulis bilang, &lt;&lt;Tuhan bekin samua yang kala ko tondo sang itu Orang yang Dia janji mau kirim datang.&gt;&gt; Naa! Waktu tulis bilang, &lt;&lt;samua yang kala ko tondo sang Dia pung Orang&gt;&gt;, su jalás bilang, Tuhan Allah sonde tamaso di situ. Te Tuhan sandiri yang angka sang Dia ko jadi Bos kasi samua.<bt>In God2's Holy Writings it is written saying, &lt;&lt;God2 makes all who lose to bow to that Person whom He promised to send.&gt;&gt; Naa! When (they) wrote saying, &lt;&lt;all who lose to bow to His Person&gt;&gt;, it is clear that God is not included there. Cuz (elaboration) God2 himself is the one who appointed Him to be Bos to all.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="hypò toùs pódas autóu: repeats the"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">hypò toùs pódas autóu: repeats the "under his feet" metaphor from Verse 25, but now in the context of hypétaxen, "given them a lower position", so it's not as violent a picture. It basically refers to who is the boss in a relationship NRSV: For “God has put all things in subjection under his feet.” But when it says, “All things are put in subjection,” it is plain that this does not include the one who put all things in subjection under him.<span class="Italic">(27)</span></Message></Annotation><note reference="15:27" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Lagu Puji dong 8:6</note><v n="28" />Nanti kalo samua dengar batúl sang Tuhan Allah pung Ana, itu Ana nanti sarakan samua kambali sang Dia pung Bapa, yang su angka Dia jadi Bos dari samua. Ais ju Tuhan Allah pegang parenta tarús dalam samua hal, kasi sang samua orang.<bt>Later when all truly listen to /obey God's Offspring, that Offspring will turn everything back over to His Father, who had appointed Him to be Bos of all. So then God will hold rule continually in everything, for everyone.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="NRSV: When all things are subjected"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">NRSV: When all things are subjected to him, then the Son himself will also be subjected to the one who put all things in subjection under him, so that God may be all in all.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Andekata orang mati sonde idop kambali<bt>If it were the case [+hypothetical] that dead people didn't come back to life</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="29" />Ada orang yang mau sarani ko ganti orang mati yang balóm sarani. Ma kalo orang mati sonde idop kambali, akurang ko dong mau sarani kasi sang orang mati?<bt>There are people who want to get *baptised to replace/stand in for dead people who were not yet baptised. But if dead people do not come back to life, why is it that they want to get baptised for dead people?</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Janji kasi orang sarani; janji kasi"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z">Janji kasi orang sarani; janji kasi orang Yahudi; Ika Janji Baru deng Tuhan // Tuhan pung Janji yang Baru (yang Lama) // Carita so'al Tuhan Yesus // Tuhan Yesus pung Carita // Surat-surat so'al Tuhan Yesus // Carita so'al Tuhan Yesus su datang (Carita so'al Tuhan Yesus nanti datang). = BC AD Tuhan pung Janji lewat Tuhan Yesus ; Tuhan pung Janji lewat Ba'i Abraham</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="hypèr: on behalf of, for --"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">hypèr: on behalf of, for -- not clear what it refers to NRSV: Otherwise, what will those people do who receive baptism on behalf of the dead? If the dead are not raised at all, why are people baptized on their behalf?<span class="Italic">(29)</span></Message></Annotation><note reference="15:29" class="Note General Paragraph" usfm="f">Ini ayat sonde jalás. Adat ke &lt;&lt;dapa sarani ko ganti orang mati&gt;&gt; sonde ada di ayat laen di anteru tulisan <span class="Italic">Tuhan Allah pung Janji Baru.</span><bt>This verse isn't clear. A ritual like &lt;&lt;get baptised to replace dead people&gt;&gt; does not exist in any other verse in the writings of <span class="Italic">God's New Promise [=NT].</span></bt></note><v n="30" />Deng akurang ko botong mau ame risiko mati tarús, kalo orang mati sonde idop kambali?<bt>And why is it that we-exc are willing to keep taking/getting a risk of dying, if dead people don't come back to life? [CHECK ame/tarima/tanggong risiko mati]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="pasang diri = go face it"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z">pasang diri = go face it (s.t. dangerous, difficult) ; sorong-sorong diri = put self in harm's way deliberately ; ame risiko mati = risk death ; mati tarús-tarús = die repeatedly, mati tarús = eternal death</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="NRSV: And why are we putting"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">NRSV: And why are we putting ourselves in danger every hour?</Message></Annotation><v n="31" />Te beta maen amper mati tiap hari! Ma sodara sayang dong! Beta sumpa, beta rasa sonde apa-apa andekata beta mati. Te beta bisa angka muka, tagal bosong ta'ika tarús deng kotong pung Bos Yesus Kristus, yang Tuhan Allah su kirim datang.<bt>Cuz (elaboration) I keep nearly dying every day! But dear siblings! [CHECK if vocative placement is awkward. Should it be removed?] I swear an oath, I would not feel anything if [+hypothetical] I were to die. Cuz (elaboration) I can lift my face (legitimate pride), because you-pl continue to be bound/linked with our-inc Box, Yesus Kristus, whom God sent.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="NRSV: I die every day! That"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">NRSV: I die every day! That is as certain, brothers and sisters, as my boasting of you-a boast that I make in Christ Jesus our Lord.</Message></Annotation><v n="32" />Tempo hari, waktu beta masi di kota Efesus, beta maen bacakar deng itu orang dong yang sama ke binatang utan yang jahat. Ma kalo beta cuma bakalai ko beta bisa manáng sandiri, bukan kasi sang Tuhan, itu parcuma sa. Sonde ada pung guna! Te kalo batúl orang mati sonde idop kambali, ada lebe bae kotong iko-iko orang pung omong sa, yang bilang,<bt>At that time (past), when I was still in the city of Efesus, I kept clawing/fighting (vivid) with those people who are like evil wild animals. But it I only fight (common lexeme) so I can win for myself, not for God2, that is pointless/futile/in vain. It has no use! [NOTE to daughter translations: different lexeme for reinforcing the point for KM, but don't force it if other lgs don't need it.] Cuz (elaboration) if it is true that dead people don't come back to life, it would be better for us-inc to just go along with what people are saying, who say,</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="bacakar = claw at each other"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z">bacakar = claw at each other ; bara'u</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="katà ánthroopon: two interpretations -- (1)"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">katà ánthroopon: two interpretations -- (1) with "fight", as somebody who fights with merely human hopes, or (2) with "wild animals" of people who can only be described in human terms as "wild beasts". UBS prefers the first -- but Roman citizens weren't punished with the lions that early Ephésooi: there is no indication that he was writing from Ephesus, but that was the first place he went after he left Corinth, so he may be talking about something that had happened then<span class="Italic">(32)</span></Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">&lt;&lt;Mari ko kotong bapesta rame-rame,<bt>&lt;&lt;Let's-inc party festively,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">deng makan-minum ena-ena sa,<bt>and just eat-drink tasty-tasty (to our heart's desire/pleasures),</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 3" usfm="q3">te beso kotong su mati!&gt;&gt;<bt>cuz (elaboration) tomorrow we'll be dead!&gt;&gt;</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="NRSV: If with merely human hopes"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">NRSV: If with merely human hopes I fought with wild animals at Ephesus, what would I have gained by it? If the dead are not raised, “Let us eat and drink, for tomorrow we die.”</Message></Annotation><note reference="15:32" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Yesaya 22:13</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="33" />Bosong jang kaná tipu ko iko pikir bagitu! Te ada kata-kata yang bilang,<bt>You-pl should not be deceived to go along with that thinking! Cuz (elaboration) there are words/a saying which says,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">&lt;&lt;Kalo lu satu kaki deng orang jahat dong,<bt>&lt;&lt;If you-sg are close friends/buddies (one-footed) with evil people,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">itu bekin lu serong dari jalan idop yang lurus.&gt;&gt;<bt>that will make you-sg stray from the life way that is straight (morally).&gt;&gt;</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="planáasthe: be made to stray away"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">planáasthe: be made to stray away from the right way NRSV: Do not be deceived: “Bad company ruins good morals.”<span class="Italic">(33)</span></Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="34" />Jang bekin jahat lai! Barenti su! Ator lu pung diri! Bekin yang batúl sa! Yang batúl, bosong musti rasa malu, te di bosong pung teng-tenga, masi ada orang yang balóm kanál sang Tuhan Allah.<bt>Don't do evil anymore! Stop it! Control yourself! Just do what is right! The truth is, you-pl should feel ashamed, cuz (elaboration) in your midst there are still people who do not yet know God.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="ekneépsate: come to your right mind,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">ekneépsate: come to your right mind, get control, wake up, as a single action (aorist) meè hamartánete: stop doing the bad things you were doing<span class="Italic">(34) (34) </span>NRSV: Come to a sober and right mind, and sin no more; for some people have no knowledge of God. I say this to your shame.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Kalo kotong idop kambali, nanti kotong pung badan karmana?<bt>If we-inc come back to life, what will our bodies be like?</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="35" />Ada yang tanya, &lt;&lt;Kalo orang mati idop kambali, nanti dia pung cara karmana? Deng dong pung badan jadi karmana?&gt;&gt;<bt>There is someone who asks, &lt;&lt;If dead people come back to life, how will that happen? And how will their bodies be?&gt;&gt;</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="NRSV: But someone will ask, “How"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">NRSV: But someone will ask, “How are the dead raised? With what kind of body do they come?”</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="36" />Bodo, é! Te kalo tanam bibit, itu bibit musti ancor dalam tana dolo, baru dia bisa idop deng banupuk.<bt>That's dumb, é! Cuz (elaboration) if you plant/bury seed, that seed must decay/come to ruin/be destroyed first, only then can it live and sprout/start growing. [NOTE: compare with John 12:23-24 plus discussion there. MC]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="some mesolectal speakers think /banupuk/ is"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z">some mesolectal speakers think /banupuk/ is stok lama &gt; batunas (mesolectal) ; mulai batumbu?</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="NRSV: Fool! What you sow does"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">NRSV: Fool! What you sow does not come to life unless it dies.</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Te kalo tanam bibit, itu bibit"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z">Te kalo tanam bibit, itu bibit musti mati dolo, baru dia bisa idop deng banupuk.</Message></Annotation><v n="37" />Deng bibit yang kotong tanam, dia pung model sonde sama ke barang yang banupuk deng badaon. Dia bibit karíng sa, macam ke gandum ko, padi ko, bibit laen dong.<bt>And the seed that we plant, its model/form/type is not the same as something that sprouts and grows leaves. It's just a dry/bare seed, like wheat or, rice/grain or, other seeds.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="bibit karíng = dry seed, bare"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z">bibit karíng = dry seed, bare seed</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="gymnòn: naked, bare, nothing but the"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">gymnòn: naked, bare, nothing but the seed itself NRSV: And as for what you sow, you do not sow the body that is to be, but a bare seed, perhaps of wheat or of some other grain.<span class="Italic">(37)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="38" />Satu-satu iko dia pung model, iko Tuhan pung mau. Te Dia yang su putus tanaman satu-satu pung model.<bt>Each one according to its type/form/model, following God2's will. Cuz (elaboration) He has determined/decided each plant's type/form.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="NRSV: But God gives it a"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">NRSV: But God gives it a body as he has chosen, and to each kind of seed its own body.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="39" />Binatang deng manusia ju bagitu. Satu-satu deng dia pung model, iko Tuhan pung mau. Ais manusia pung badan, iko manusia pung model. Binatang pung badan dong, satu-satu deng dia pung model. Burung deng dia pung. Ikan deng dia pung. Yang laen lai deng dia pung.<bt>Animals and humans are also like that. Each with its own type/form/model, following/according to God2's will. So then human bodies follow human type/form/model. Animals' bodies each follow its own type/form/model. Birds with theirs. Fish with theirs. The others still with each of theirs. [NOTE: we're taking this as for instances, not as a closed list.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="sàrx: switches from sóoma, but talking"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">sàrx: switches from sóoma, but talking about the same thing kteenóon: mainly domestic animals, but can include other kinds -- basically any kine of animal life that isn't people, or birds, or fish<span class="Italic">(39) (39) </span>NRSV: Not all flesh is alike, but there is one flesh for human beings, another for animals, another for birds, and another for fish.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="40" />Ada barang di langit, deng ada barang di bumi. Yang di langit ada dong pung hebat. Ma itu hebat, laen dari yang ada di bumi. Yang di bumi ju ada dong pung hebat. Ma itu hebat, laen dari yang ada di langit.<bt>There are things in the sky, and there are things on earth. Those in the sky have their own greatness/incredibleness. But their greatness is different from those that are on earth. Those on the earth also have their own greatness. But that greatness is different from those that are in the sky. [NOTE to daughter translations: this here and in following verses is Gk. /doxa/ "glory, beauty, splendour"; KM has to go more generic, but many of the surrounding vernaculars have a more specific term that is closer to the Gk.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="does badan work for sun?"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z">does badan work for sun?</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="soómata: bodies, back to the word"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">soómata: bodies, back to the word in Verse 38 dóxa: beauty, splendor<span class="Italic">(40) (40) </span>NRSV: There are both heavenly bodies and earthly bodies, but the glory of the heavenly is one thing, and that of the earthly is another.</Message></Annotation><v n="41" />Kalo di langit, matahari pung hebat laen; bulan pung hebat laen; deng bintang dong ju pung hebat laen-laen. Satu-satu deng dia pung model. Satu-satu deng dia pung hebat. Jadi samua ada pung hebat, to?<bt>As for in the sky, the sun has its own greatness; the moon has its own different greatness; and the stars also have their own kinds of greatness. Each with its own type/form/model. Each with its own greatness. So (consequently) all have greatness, right?</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="NRSV: There is one glory of"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">NRSV: There is one glory of the sun, and another glory of the moon, and another glory of the stars; indeed, star differs from star in glory.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="42" />Naa! Kalo orang mati idop kambali, itu sama ke bibit tadi tu. Te kalo su kubur orang mati, dia pung mayat jadi rusak buang, to? Ma kalo dia idop kambali, dia su sonde sama ke dolu lai. Te kalo su idop kambali, dia sonde bisa mati lai.<bt>Naa! If dead people come back to life, that is just like that seed mentioned earlier. Cuz (elaboration) if (we) have buried a dead person, his corpse becomes completely decayed, right? But if s/he comes back to life, s/he is not the same as previously anymore. Cuz (elaboration) if (s/he) has already come back to life, s/he cannot die anymore.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="aphtharsía: imperishable, not subject to decay"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">aphtharsía: imperishable, not subject to decay NRSV: So it is with the resurrection of the dead. What is sown is perishable, what is raised is imperishable.<span class="Italic">(42)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="43" />Waktu kotong kubur orang mati, kotong rasa itu mayat kamomos. Ma kalo itu orang su idop kambali, na, dia pung hebat lai! Te dia jadi barisi! Orang mati sonde bisa bekin apa-apa waktu orang kubur sang dia. Ma waktu dia su idop kambali, dia jadi talalu kuat!<bt>When we-inc bury dead people, we feel that corpse is dirty/filthy/defiled. But if that person has come back to life, na, how incredible/amazing it is! Cuz (elaboration) is has become clean/pure/holy! A dead person can't do anything when people bury him. But when s/he comes back to life, s/he is so strong/powerful! [EXEG: Gk: raised in glory here]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="kuat not in dictionary?"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z">kuat not in dictionary?</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="NRSV: It is sown in dishonor,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">NRSV: It is sown in dishonor, it is raised in glory. It is sown in weakness, it is raised in power.</Message></Annotation><v n="44" />Kalo orang masi idop, dia cuma tau pikir deng rasa sa, to? Ma waktu dia mati, ko idop kambali, na, Tuhan pung Roh kasi sang dia idop yang batúl. Deng dia su sonde sama ke dolu lai.<bt>If/when a person is still alive, s/he only knows how to think and feel, right? But when s/he dies, to come back to life, na, God2's Spirit gives him true life. And s/he is then no longer the same as before. [NOTE: reduced redundancy; Because of UNS responses, and under consultant guidance, we focused on “think and feel” keeping lexical ties through 45-46 to make explicit s.t. that local worldviews see as iconic differences between the dead and the living.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="NRSV: It is sown a physical"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">NRSV: It is sown a physical body, it is raised a spiritual body. If there is a physical body, there is also a spiritual body.</Message><Message author="Chuck Grimes" created="2014-02-21 01:14:15Z">UnBe</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Te ada orang di ini dunya"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z">Te ada orang di ini dunya yang cuma tau pikir deng rasa sa. Deng ju ada orang yang idop batúl, ta'ika deng Tuhan pung Roh. Waktu orang mati, dong kubur dia pung badan. Ma waktu Tuhan pung Roh kasi idop sang dia, dia dapa idop yang batúl. [no commentary support]<span class="Italic">(44)</span></Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="45" />Manusia partama yang sama ke kotong, andia Adam. Iko Tuhan pung Tulisan Barisi, ada tulis bilang, &lt;&lt;dia jadi manusia yang idop, yang tau pikir deng rasa.&gt;&gt; Ma manusia yang model ke Adam yang paling di atas tu, andia Kristus. Dia pung Roh yang bisa kasi orang idop yang batúl.<bt>The first human who was like us, was Adam. According to God2's Holy Writings, it is written saying, &lt;&lt;he became a living humans who knew how to think and feel.&gt;&gt; But the human who is a type/form/model like Adam at the very top/peak (a metaphor they use in kinship and social structure), is Kristus. His Spirit is the one who can give people true life. [EXEG: "the last Adam" is common Jewish Messianic reference; last = highest ranking; see Ex. Summ.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="NRSV: Thus it is written, “The"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">NRSV: Thus it is written, “The first man, Adam, became a living being”; the last Adam became a life-giving spirit.</Message></Annotation><note reference="15:45" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Carita Mula-mula 2:7</note><v n="46" />Yang partama tu, andia orang yang cuma tau pikir deng rasa sa, ais dia bisa mati. Ma yang su idop kambali tu, andia orang yang dapa idop yang batúl dari Tuhan pung Roh.<bt>That first one, was a person who only knew how to think and feel, and then/so s/he could die. But the one who has come back to life, is a person who gets/obtains true life from God2's Spirit. [EXEG: HCE]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="NRSV: But it is not the"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">NRSV: But it is not the spiritual that is first, but the physical, and then the spiritual.</Message></Annotation><v n="47" />Manusia model partama di bumi tu, ada bekin dari tana isi. Ma yang model kadua tu, andia Kristus, ada datang dari langit.<bt>The human of the first type/form/model on earth was made/created from dirt. But the one of the second type/form/model, is Kristus, came from the sky/heaven.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="NRSV: The first man was from"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">NRSV: The first man was from the earth, a man of dust; the second man is from heaven.</Message></Annotation><v n="48" />Kotong yang idop di bumi, model sama ke manusia partama, yang Tuhan bekin dari tana isi. Ma orang yang ta'ika deng Tuhan Allah di langit, model sama ke Kristus yang datang dari langit.<bt>We-inc who live on earth, are the same type/form/model as the first human who God2' made from dirt. But a person who is bound/linked to God in heaven, is the same type/form/model as Kristus who came from heaven.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="NRSV: As was the man of"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">NRSV: As was the man of dust, so are those who are of the dust; and as is the man of heaven, so are those who are of heaven.</Message></Annotation><v n="49" />Kotong sakarang model sama ke Adam yang Tuhan bekin dari tana isi. Ma lama-lama kotong ganti model baru, yang sama ke Kristus yang datang dari langit.<bt>We now are the same type/form/model as Adam who God2 made from dirt. But eventually we will exchange for a new type/form/model, which is the same as Kristus who came from heaven.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="NRSV: Just as we have borne"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">NRSV: Just as we have borne the image of the man of dust, we will also bear the image of the man of heaven.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="50" />Sodara sayang dong! Yang beta mau kasi tau sang bosong, bagini: kotong yang jadi manusia model partama, kotong pung badan dari dara deng tulang. Deng bagitu, kotong sonde bisa tarima kotong pung pusaka ko jadi Tuhan Allah pung ana di sorga. Sonde bisa! Te orang model ke itu, nanti dong pung badan rusak buang, ais dong sonde bisa tarima hal yang batahan tarús.<bt>Dear siblings! What I want to tell you is this: we-inc who are/became humans of the first type/form/model, our bodies are from blood and bones. [NOTE: Kupang way of talking about "flesh and blood"] In that way/form, we are not able to receive our inheritance to become God's offspring in heaven2. Just can't do it! Cuz (elaboration) a person of that type/form/model, their bodies will completely decay, so they are not able to receive things that last/endure continually/forever.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="NRSV: What I am saying, brothers"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">NRSV: What I am saying, brothers and sisters, is this: flesh and blood cannot inherit the kingdom of God, nor does the perishable inherit the imperishable.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="51" />Jadi dengar bae-bae! Te beta mau buka kasi bosong satu rahasia. Nanti ada orang parcaya saparu yang sonde mati. Ma kotong samua nanti ganti model baru.<bt>So (consequently), listen carefully! Cuz (elaboration) I am going to reveal a secret to you-pl. There will be some believers who do not die. But all of us-inc will change/substitute into a new form/type/model.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="pántes: could be read &quot;not one"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">pántes: could be read "not one of us will die" NRSV: Listen, I will tell you a mystery! We will not all die, but we will all be changed,<span class="Italic">(51)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="52" />Waktu tarompet pung bunyi paling tarahir, samua ni jadi deng takuju sa. Lebe capát dari lu pung kadíp mata. Te waktu tarompet babunyi, itu waktu ju orang mati dong idop kambali. Deng kalo dong su idop kambali, dong sonde mati ulang lai, deng sonde rusak ulang. Bagitu ju deng kotong yang masi idop. Kotong samua jadi model baru.<bt>When a/the trumpet (makes) its last sound, all this will happen suddenly. Faster than your-sg blink of an eye. Cuz (elaboration) when the trumpet sounds, at that (same) time dead people will have come back to life. And if/when they have come back to life, they will not die again, and they won't decay again. It's the same way with us-inc who are still alive. All of us will become a new model/type/form. [EXEG: Gk meaning is ambiguous between last trumpet (object) or last trumpet (sound). (see Ex. Summ. “the last trumpet sound”) But note that the first reading ‘last trumpet (object)’ is vague (e.g. the last Stradavarius remaining today was first played in 1728), whereas the KM rendering is pretty unambiguous that this is the final trumpet sound (therefore by implication the last trumpet that plays). I could accept either /tarompet pung bunyi paling tarahir/ or /tarompet paling tarahir pung bunyi/, but since this part of this verse already shows evidence of reworking, and the grammar of the TB (while slightly ambiguous) leans toward /bunyi/ “the final sound of the trumpet” being in focus, I'm inclined to leave it as it. “who are still alive” restored, CR Amarasi 2014]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="kajáp = kedip"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z">kajáp = kedip</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="NRSV: in a moment, in the"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">NRSV: in a moment, in the twinkling of an eye, at the last trumpet. For the trumpet will sound, and the dead will be raised imperishable, and we will be changed.</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Samua ni jadi deng takuju sa."><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z">Samua ni jadi deng takuju sa. Lebe capát dari lu pung kajáp mata. Tarompet pung bunyi paling tarahir, baru jadi.</Message></Annotation><note reference="15:51-52" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">1 Tesalonika 4:15-17</note><v n="53-54" />Te kotong pung badan yang sakarang bisa rusak, mau roba jadi model yang sonde bisa rusak lai! Deng kotong yang sakarang bisa mati, mau roba jadi model yang sonde bisa mati lai! Itu bekin iko apa yang tatulis memang dalam Tulisan Barisi bilang,<bt>Cuz (elaboration) our bodies which now are able to decay, are going to change becoming a form/type/model which is not able to decay anymore! And we-inc who now are able to die, are going to change becoming a form/type/model which is not able to die anymore! The is according to what was written beforehand in the Holy Writings saying,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">&lt;&lt;Tuhan su kasi ancor mati pung kuasa,<bt>God2 has already destroyed the power of death,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">deng su manáng dari dia!<bt>and has already overcome/conquered it!</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Andia ko kotong su sonde mati lai.&gt;&gt;<bt>That is why we-inc are not going to die anymore.&gt;&gt;</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Can /dia/ refer to /mati/?"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z">Can /dia/ refer to /mati/?</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="NRSV: For this perishable body must"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">NRSV: For this perishable body must put on imperishability, and this mortal body must put on immortality. When this perishable body puts on imperishability, and this mortal body puts on immortality, then the saying that is written will be fulfilled: “Death has been swallowed up in victory.”</Message></Annotation><note reference="15:54" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Yesaya 25:8</note></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">
      <v n="55" />&lt;&lt;He, Mati!<bt>&lt;&lt;He, Death! [NOTE: Yes, we realise it's personification.]</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Lu pung kuasa ada di mana?<bt>Where is your power/authority?</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">He, Mati!<bt>He, Death!</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Lu pung dedek di mana lai?&gt;&gt;<bt>Where is your bite/sting (e.g. wasp, snake, sunburn, ember) now?&gt;&gt;</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="NRSV: “Where, O death, is your"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">NRSV: “Where, O death, is your victory? Where, O death, is your sting?”</Message></Annotation><note reference="15:55" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Hosea 13:14</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="56" />Akurang ko mati ada bawa rasa saki kasi kotong manusia? Itu tagal kotong ada bekin sala. Andia tu! Akurang ko kotong pung sala-sala ada pung kuasa bagitu? Itu tagal Tuhan Allah pung Atoran kasi tunju bilang, kotong pung sala-sala ada langgar Dia pung Parenta. Andia tu!<bt>Why is it that death brings pain to we-inc humans? That is because we do wrong. That's why! Why is it that our wrongs have power like that? It is because God's Law shows that our wrongs violate His Commands. That's why!</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="NRSV: The sting of death is"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">NRSV: The sting of death is sin, and the power of sin is the law.</Message></Annotation><v n="57" />Ma sakarang samua su jadi laen! Ais kotong samua minta tarima kasi bam-banya sang Tuhan Allah. Te Dia yang bekin kotong bisa manáng atas hal jahat dong, lewat apa yang kotong pung Bos Yesus Kristus bekin. Deng Kristus yang manáng batúl!<bt>But now everything has become different! So all of us give lots and lots of thanks to God. Cuz (elaboration) He is the one who makes us able to overcome/conquer evil things, through/by means what of our-inc Bos, Yesus Kristus, has done. And Kristus is the one who really won/overcame!</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="NRSV: But thanks be to God,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">NRSV: But thanks be to God, who gives us the victory through our Lord Jesus Christ.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="58" />Jadi sodara sayang dong! Batahan kuat! Jang tagoyang! Bosong pung karjá kasi sang Tuhan musti batamba bae, deng batamba banya. Te bosong su tau bilang, bosong pung karjá banting tulang kasi sang kotong pung Bos, sonde parcuma.<bt>So (consequently) dear siblings! Persevere/endure strongly! Don't be shaken (by an outside force)! Your-pl work for God2 must get increasingly better, and increasingly more. Cuz (elaboration) you already know that your hard work (idiom: work throwing bones) for our Bos is not pointless/useless/in vain.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="NRSV: Therefore, my beloved, be steadfast,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">NRSV: Therefore, my beloved, be steadfast, immovable, always excelling in the work of the Lord, because you know that in the Lord your labor is not in vain.</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="sonde tabuang parcuma"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z">sonde tabuang parcuma</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Doi yang orang kasi ko bantu Tuhan pung orang dong<bt>Money which people give/gave to help God2's people</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <c n="16" />
      <v n="1" />Sakarang beta mau tulis so'al itu doi yang bosong su kumpul ko bantu Tuhan pung orang dong di Yerusalem. Beta su kasi tau orang parcaya dong di propinsi Galatia, karmana dong musti kumpul itu doi. Sakarang bosong ju musti bekin iko bagitu.<bt>Now I want to write about that money which you-pl collected to (financial)-help God2's people in Yerusalem. I have already told the believers in the province of Galatia, how they must collect that money. Now you-pl must do accordingly as well. [EXEG / background-foreground: Jerusalem from v.3, see NLT also]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="*** (2009) pake in 1nd sentence"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z">*** (2009) pake in 1nd sentence changed to kumpul</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="NRSV: Now concerning the collection for"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">NRSV: Now concerning the collection for the saints: you should follow the directions I gave to the churches of Galatia.</Message></Annotation><note reference="16:1" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Roma 15:25-26</note><v n="2" />Tiap hari minggu, samua orang musti simpan dong pung doi sadiki, dari dong pung hasil karjá. Jang tunggu beta datang, baru bosong mulai ba'urus kumpul doi.<bt>Each sunday, everyone must/should store away a little of their money from the results of their work. Don't wait for me to come before you begin to deal with the matter of collecting money.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="euodóotai: success in business, whatever they"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">euodóotai: success in business, whatever they can succeed in saving NRSV: On the first day of every week, each of you is to put aside and save whatever extra you earn, so that collections need not be taken when I come.<span class="Italic">(2)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="3" />Ais kalo beta su datang, na, bosong kasi tunju bosong pung orang yang bosong parcaya, ko bawa itu doi bantuan kasi Tuhan pung orang dong di Yerusalem. Ais nanti beta tulis surat ko kasi kanál sang dong deng pimpinan jama'at di sana.<bt>Then if/when I have come, na, you can designate your person/people whom you trust, to take/bring that financial assistance to God2's people in Yerusalem. Then I will write a letter to introduce them to the congregational leaders there.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="di' epistolóon: could go with &quot;whoever"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">di' epistolóon: could go with "whoever you accredit [by giving them letters]" or with "I will send them on [with letters of introduction from me]" NRSV: And when I arrive, I will send any whom you approve with letters to take your gift to Jerusalem.<span class="Italic">(3)</span></Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Ais, nanti beta tulis surat ko"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z">Ais, nanti beta tulis surat ko kasi tau pimpinan jama'at di sana, bilang, ini orang dong ni, sapa.</Message></Annotation><v n="4" />Deng kalo bosong pikir ada bae kalo beta ju iko, na, botong bisa pi sama-sama.<bt>And, if you think it would be better/best if I also go along, na, we-exc can go together.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="áxion éei: worthwhile, proper NRSV: If"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">áxion éei: worthwhile, proper NRSV: If it seems advisable that I should go also, they will accompany me.<span class="Italic">(4)</span></Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Paulus susun rancana ko mau jalan pi banya tampa<bt>Paulus makes plans to go to many places</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="5" />Kalo beta su jalan kuliling di propinsi Makedonia, baru beta pi bosong sana. Ma beta masi mau pi Makedonia dolo.<bt>If/when I have gone around/throughout the province of Makedonia, only then will I go to you there (remote). But I still want to go to Makedonia first.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="NRSV: I will visit you after"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">NRSV: I will visit you after passing through Macedonia-for I intend to pass through Macedonia</Message></Annotation><note reference="16:5" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Utusan dong pung Carita 19:21</note><v n="6" />Ais itu, baru beta mau pi tenga tahan deng bosong sadiki lama; mungkin sampe satu musim dingin anteru. Ais ju bosong bisa antar beta sampe di tampa barikut.<bt>After that, only then do I want to stay temporarily with you for awhile; maybe for as long as one whole cold season. After that then you can escort me to the next place. [EXEG: ‘escort’? or ‘hospitality, including provision of food’? We're on solid ground with the meaning of the word in context, LN and BAGD descriptions of the meaning of the word, plus NRSV, NLT, CEV renderings, etc. Our rendering does not exclude these other things. But some of the Ex.Summ. sources are reading things into the text. Also here in eastern Indonesia, escorting on a trip is the height of hospitality, and often includes covering costs or meeting needs. There is no need to overtranslate.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="barikut"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z">barikut</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="NRSV: and perhaps I will stay"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">NRSV: and perhaps I will stay with you or even spend the winter, so that you may send me on my way, wherever I go.</Message></Annotation><v n="7" />Beta pung maksud datang di bosong, bukan cuma sabantar sa. Te beta mau tenga deng bosong sadiki lama, kalo itu iko Tuhan pung mau.<bt>My intention for coming to you is not just momentarily/short time. Cuz (elaboration) I want to stay with you for awhile, if that follows/is according to God2's will.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="sabantar"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z">sabantar</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="en paródooi: if he swung by"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">en paródooi: if he swung by Corinth on his next trip, he would have to just pop in and out. He wanted to spend more time with them than that, and after his next project, he thought he would have the time NRSV: I do not want to see you now just in passing, for I hope to spend some time with you, if the Lord permits.<span class="Italic">(7)</span></Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="bukan kilat sa"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z">bukan kilat sa</Message></Annotation><v n="8" />Ma beta masi mau tenga di kota Efesus sini sampe hari bae Pentakosta, [andia 50 hari lewat hari bae Paska].<bt>But I still want to stay here in the city of Efesus until the Pentakosta holiday/feast day, [that is 50 days after the Paska holiday]. [NOTE: explicated for a non-Jewish Corinthian audience, following HCE]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="kurang 50 hari = after, following"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z">kurang 50 hari = after, following</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="NRSV: But I will stay in"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">NRSV: But I will stay in Ephesus until Pentecost,</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Ma beta masi mau tenga di"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z">Ma beta masi mau tenga di kota Efesus sini sampe hari bae Pentakosta, andia hari bae Paska, kurang 50 hari lai.</Message></Annotation><note reference="16:8" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Kapala Agama dong pung Atoran 23:15-21, Carita Ulang so'al Jalan Idop 16:9-11</note><v n="9" />Tagal di sini ada banya sampát yang talalu bae ko beta masi bisa karjá banya, biar lai ada banya orang yang lawan Tuhan pung karjá.<bt>Because here there are many fantastic (too good) opportunities for me to still do/accomplish much, even though there are also many people who oppose God2's work.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="antikeímenoi: &quot;opponents&quot;, a little bit less"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">antikeímenoi: "opponents", a little bit less dramatic than "enemies" NRSV: for a wide door for effective work has opened to me, and there are many adversaries.<span class="Italic">(9)</span></Message></Annotation><note reference="16:8-9" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Utusan dong pung Carita 19:8-10</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="10" />Kalo Timotius jadi datang di bosong, tarima sang dia deng bae-bae, ko dia sonde usa pikir-pikir. Te dia tu, kotong pung Bos pung orang karjá, sama ke beta.<bt>If/when it works out for Timotius to come to you, receive him well, so he doesn't need to worry/be anxious. Cuz (elaboration) he is our-inc Bos' worker, just like me.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="NRSV: If Timothy comes, see that"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">NRSV: If Timothy comes, see that he has nothing to fear among you, for he is doing the work of the Lord just as I am;</Message></Annotation><note reference="16:10" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">1 Korintus 4:17</note><v n="11" />Jang kasi biar orang lia sang dia deng mata sablá. Tolong sang dia, sampe dia pulang deng salamat, ko dia bisa datang kambali di beta. Te beta deng sodara laen dong, ada tunggu-tunggu sang dia.<bt>Don't let people despise him (idiom: look one-eyed at him). Help him, until he goes back (home) safely, so he can come back to me. Cuz (elaboration) I and other siblings are waiting (eagerly) for him.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="exoutheneéseei: act like he is worth"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">exoutheneéseei: act like he is worth nothing NRSV: therefore let no one despise him. Send him on his way in peace, so that he may come to me; for I am expecting him with the brothers.<span class="Italic">(11)</span></Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="12" />Ada lai satu hal. Beta su buju sang kotong pung sodara Apolos, ko dia pi lia sang bosong deng sodara laen dong. Ma dia balóm mau pi sakarang. Nanti sa, kalo dia dapa waktu yang bae, baru dia pi situ.<bt>There is one more thing. I have tried to coax/persuade/cajole our-inc sibling Apolos, so he would go look after/see the the needs of you and other siblings. But he isn't wanting to go yet at this time. So later, if/when he gets a better time, only then will he go there.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="NRSV: Now concerning our brother Apollos,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">NRSV: Now concerning our brother Apollos, I strongly urged him to visit you with the other brothers, but he was not at all willing to come now. He will come when he has the opportunity.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Bekin satu hal lai<bt>Do one more thing</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="13" />Bosong musti jaga diri bae-bae! Bosong musti batahan ko parcaya tarús sang Tuhan! Jang taku! Bekin kuat diri!<bt>You must watch/guard yourselves carefully! You must persevere/endure to keep believing in God2! Don't be afraid. Strengthen yourselves!</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="greegoréite: keep looking out for these"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">greegoréite: keep looking out for these things that have to do with the end of the world, which should happen soon NRSV: Keep alert, stand firm in your faith, be courageous, be strong.<span class="Italic">(13)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="14" />Bosong bekin apa sa, na, kasi tunju bosong pung sayang.<bt>Whatever you do, na, demonstrate/show your love.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="NRSV: Let all that you do"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">NRSV: Let all that you do be done in love.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="15" />Sodara sayang dong! Bosong samua tau bilang, bu Stefanus deng dia pung isi ruma jadi orang partama yang parcaya sang Kristus di propinsi Akaya sana. Dong ju karjá banting tulang ko layani samua orang parcaya di sana. Jadi beta minta ko<bt>Dear siblings! You all know that older brother Stefanus and his household were the first people who believed in Kristus in the province of Akaya there (remote). They also worked hard (worked throwing bones) to serve all the believers there. So (consequently), I ask that</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="étaxan heautoús: they saw a need,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">étaxan heautoús: they saw a need, and took the responsibility of meeting it upon themselves -- nobody asked them to do it NRSV: Now, brothers and sisters, you know that members of the household of Stephanas were the first converts in Achaia, and they have devoted themselves to the service of the saints;<span class="Italic">(15)</span></Message></Annotation><note reference="16:15" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">1 Korintus 1:16</note><v n="16" />bosong dengar-dengar sang orang macam bagitu. Andia orang yang karjá ukur kuat ko sama-sama layani orang parcaya dong.<bt>you-pl keep listening to/obeying people of that type. That is, people who work with all their might (work measure strong) together to serve the believers.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="NRSV: I urge you to put"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">NRSV: I urge you to put yourselves at the service of such people, and of everyone who works and toils with them.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="17" />Beta rindu mau lia sang bosong. Ais beta pung hati babunga, te bu Stefanus, bu Fortunatus, deng bu Akaikus ada datang di sini. Deng bagitu, dong ganti sang bosong.<bt>I yearn to see you-pl. So then my heart is overjoyed (liver flowers), cuz (elaboration) our-inc older brother Stefanus, older brother Fortunatus, and older brother Akaikus have come here. In that way, they replace/substitute for you.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="tò hyméteron hystéreema: missing you all,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">tò hyméteron hystéreema: missing you all, feeling out of touch (like the telephone company commercials) NRSV: I rejoice at the coming of Stephanas and Fortunatus and Achaicus, because they have made up for your absence;<span class="Italic">(17)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="18" />Dong kasi kuat beta pung hati, sama ke dong kasi kuat bosong pung hati ju. Bosong musti taro hormat kasi orang macam bagitu dong.<bt>They strengthen my liver (=encourage), in the same way/s that they encourage you-pl. You must give respect/honour to people of that sort/type.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="epiginoóskete: recognize that they are somebody,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">epiginoóskete: recognize that they are somebody, pay attention to what they say NRSV: for they refreshed my spirit as well as yours. So give recognition to such persons.<span class="Italic">(18)</span></Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Paulus titip salam kasi samua<bt>Paulus passes on greetings to all</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="19" />Jama'at-jama'at di propinsi Asia ada titip salam kasi bosong. Bu Akila, dia pung bini, susi Priskila,<bt>The various congregations in the province of Asia pass on greetings to you-pl. Older brother Akila, his wife, older sister Priskila,</bt><note reference="16:19" class="Note General Paragraph" usfm="f">Alkitab bahasa Yunani di sini tulis bilang, &lt;&lt;Priska&gt;&gt;. Priska deng Priskila tu, andia satu nama.<bt>The Yunani language Bible here writes saying, “Priska”. Priska and Priskila are the same name.</bt></note>deng samua orang laen yang biasa bakumpul di dong pung ruma ju ada titip salam, te dong ju ta'ika tarús deng kotong pung Bos.<bt>and all the other people who normally gather in their house also pass on greetings, cuz (elaboration) they are also bound/linked with our-inc Bos. [NOTE on ftn: Priscilla is the diminutive form of Prisca.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="NRSV: The churches of Asia send"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">NRSV: The churches of Asia send greetings. Aquila and Prisca, together with the church in their house, greet you warmly in the Lord.</Message></Annotation><note reference="16:19" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Utusan dong pung Carita 18:2</note><v n="20" />Samua orang parcaya di sini ju ada titip salam.<bt>All the believers here also pass on their greetings.</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Kalo bosong bakumpul, na, basambut satu deng satu pake ciom manis yang pantas kasi orang parcaya dong.<bt>If/when you are gathered together, na, mutually greet each other using a sweet kiss that is appropriate for believers.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="phileémati hagíooi: the kind of greeting"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">phileémati hagíooi: the kind of greeting appropriate for God's peopo -- not a lover's kiss, but the way friends greet each other warmly NRSV: All the brothers and sisters send greetings. Greet one another with a holy kiss.<span class="Italic">(20)</span></Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="21" />Coba lia doo! Te beta, Paulus ni, pake beta pung tangan sandiri ko tulis ini kata bagini: <span class="Italic">Saloom!</span><bt>Have alook at this! Cuz (elaboration) I, Paulus here, am using my own hand to write this: <span class="Italic">Saloom!</span></bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="NRSV: I, Paul, write this greeting"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">NRSV: I, Paul, write this greeting with my own hand.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="22" />Sapa yang sonde ada pung sayang sang kotong pung Bos, nanti Tuhan Allah kasi hukum sang dia.<bt>Whoever has no love for out-inc Bos, God will punish him.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="anáthema: excluded from Christian fellowship, set"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">anáthema: excluded from Christian fellowship, set up to be destroyed when Christ comes back</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Beta suka togor sang orang, pake botong orang Yahudi pung bahasa Aram bilang, <span class="Italic">&lt;&lt;Marana ta!&gt;&gt;</span> Dia pung arti bilang, &lt;&lt;Bos, é! Datang su!&gt;&gt;<bt>I like to greet2/warn/admonish people, using the Yahudi people's Aram language saying, <span class="Italic">&lt;&lt;Marana ta!&gt;&gt;</span> It means, &lt;&lt;Bos, é! Come!&gt;&gt; [EXEG: : Is “Marana tha” to be taken positively “we really look forward to your coming, Lord”, or negatively “hurry up and come judge these accursed people, Lord (that I was just talking about)”. Commentators are divided (see Ex. Summ.). But note a) these verses have a string of relatively unrelated exortations, and b) elsewhere in the Biblical and extra-biblical literature the use of “Marana tha” is overwhelmingly positive. In this light, the paragraph break to set up communicating to RL audiences what “Marana tha” is appropriate.] [NOTE to daughter translations: the Kupang word /togor/ is polysemous: 1) greet, 2) admonish. The first is the one intended. CHECK.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="*** (2009) notes added"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z">*** (2009) notes added</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="NRSV: Let anyone be accursed who"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">NRSV: Let anyone be accursed who has no love for the Lord. Our Lord, come!</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="23" />Beta minta ko Yesus, kotong pung Bos, kasi tunju Dia pung hati bae sang bosong.<bt>I ask that Yesus, our-inc Bos, show His good liver (goodness/grace/kindness/generosity) to you-pl.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="NRSV: The grace of the Lord"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">NRSV: The grace of the Lord Jesus be with you.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="24" />Beta sayang sang bosong samua, tagal kotong sama-sama ta'ika deng Kristus, yang Tuhan su kirim datang.<bt>I love you all, because we-inc are together bound/linked with Kristus, who God sent.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="NRSV: My love be with all"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:49:14Z" status="Information">NRSV: My love be with all of you in Christ Jesus.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Sampe di sini sa. Saloom!<bt>That's all up to this point. Saloom!</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Dari beta,<bt>From me,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Paulus<bt>Paulus</bt></p>
  </book>
</bible>